name: Grand Rapids Head Start Itasca Resource Center
Little Blessings of Anoka Early Childhood Learning Center
details:
Little Blessings of Anoka Early Childhood Learning Center (ECLC) started serving families as Elim Christian Learning Center in 1965 as a subsidiary of Elim Baptist Church in Anoka. On October 1, 2013, the learning center changed its name and was officially incorporated into the ministries of Anoka Community Mission (www.anokacommunitymission.org). We continue to strive to provide the same high quality educational and spiritual care. We feel we are an extension of your family, while supporting and serving local community and families in love. We believe the first five years of a child’s life are very important to forming the attitudes and traits which will carry with later in life. We teach Christian values where every child is upheld as a Child of God.

We are designed to provide excellence in the child’s social, emotional, physical, intellectual and spiritual development for infants, toddlers and preschool for success in life. We strive to balance the demands of work and family. We believe that children learn best through their play.  Our preschool program offers a kindergarten readiness standard that balance teacher directed and child initiated opportunities.

Our environment is warm and welcoming; children feel a sense of belonging.  We have a low teacher to child ratio; small groups within classrooms allow for more individual attention.  All our teachers are certified in Pediatric First Aid and CPR.  We are monitored by a registered nurse who visits us monthly for health and safety practices.  We have the protection of a security door and fenced in play areas.  We also have access to a full size gymnasium where the children can play if the weather does not permit them to go outside.

name: Hand in Hand Child Care Center
details:
Hand in Hand Child Care Center offers a Christ-centered curriculum, which focuses on the development of social, emotional, physical, cognitive, and spiritual skills.

As a laboratory school of Concordia University-Saint Paul, Hand in Hand shares the Gospel and love of Jesus Christ and focuses on the total growth and development of young children.  The center offers care for children six weeks until they enter Kindergarten.  Our facility offers a unique learning experience for Concordia University students, especially those entering the Early Childhood Education program, through our work study programs, student teaching experiences and volunteer work.

Hand in Hand offers Christ-centered, developmentally appropriate practices. Our play-based curriculum focuses on the development of social, emotional, physical, cognitive and spiritual skills. The center’s programs are designed to include spiritual and social living, communication arts, expressive arts, wellness and discovery about the world.

name: Head Start Family Development Center
details:
Head Start is a multi-faceted child and family development program for income-eligible households in Anoka and Washington Counties in Minnesota. The program is designed to help pregnant women and children, aged birth to five, and their families achieve their full potential.

The Head Start program literally gives children a head start on their journey of lifelong learning. The program also gives parents a head start in maintaining family continuity and self-sufficiency.

name: Hibbing Parent's Nursery School
details:
HPNS is a non-profit nursery school and daycare committed to providing a safe, nurturing, and educational environment for children. We believe that the most important aspect of early childhood education is to create a space in which children can make discoveries, solve problems, and think independently.
HPNS both values and depends on parent participation and volunteer involvement. Our Board of Directors consists of parents and local volunteers. The Board supports the school through policy making and fundraising. ALL parents are welcome (and encouraged) to join the board meetings and be actively involved in their child's school.

name: Newport Head Start
details:
Head Start is a multi-faceted child and family development program for income-eligible households in Anoka and Washington Counties in Minnesota. The program is designed to help pregnant women and children, aged birth to five, and their families achieve their full potential.

The Head Start program literally gives children a head start on their journey of lifelong learning. The program also gives parents a head start in maintaining family continuity and self-sufficiency.

name: WCCA Head Start-Howard Lake
details:
The Wright County Community Action (WCCA) Head Start Program provides your 3-5 year old child with a head start. Community based child and family development programming through the Head Start program is available to eligible households throughout Wright and Western Hennepin County.

WCCA Head Start services promote cognitive, social, and emotional growth and development of 3-5 year old children from income eligible families and for age eligible children with special needs. Activities centered around health, education, nutrition and socialization are focused on children’s growth and development in language, literacy, math, science social functioning, creative arts, physical skills, overall learning abilities and more. Parent involvement and participation is a key element to each child’s success and actively promoted in Head Start.

WCCA provides Head Start programming at centers and through a Home/Parent based model. Daily schedules at centers vary by location and include 4 hour, 6 hour and extended day.

name: Immanuel Lutheran Preschool
details: Immanuel Lutheran school is an educational environment that promotes excellence and growth in the Lutheran Christian Faith where each child can strive to reach his or her potential. We believe that the parent is the child’s first teacher. It is only through parents and teachers working together and showing mutual respect that we hope to achieve what is best for each child at Immanuel Lutheran School.

name: International Falls Head Start
details:
KOOTASCA is a non profit human service agency serving Itasca and Koochiching counties in Northern Minnesota. We serve low-income people providing ways for families to get connected to the community with a plan to get out of poverty. Our mission is “Building Community to End Poverty”. Our services include:
    Housing Programs - crisis housing, rehabilitation, energy assistance, home ownership workshops, down payment & financial counseling, closing cost assistance.

    Head Start - and early Head Start, project read early literacy, family services & involvement, health services. Check out our report to the public.
    Click Here to see the report

    Crisis Services - family support program in our community designed to provide emergency or short-term care for children 0-12 years while families address crisis situations and includes Crisis Housing.

name: Sabes J.C.C. Early Childhood Center
details: Early Childhood programming at the Sabes JCC seeks to foster within our children a positive self-concept, a joy for learning, and the ability to work and play well with others. Using the "learning through play" approach, children and parents have the opportunity to learn about themselves, their environment, people and the world around them.

name: Kasson-Mantorville Nursery Group
details: KASSON MANTORVILLE NURSERY GROUP is a non-profit child care center and preschool located in Kasson, Minnesota. We strive to provide learning experiences through a variety of materials, which stimulates each child's physical, intellectual, social, and emotional development. We invite you to join our family and come grow with us!

name: Kid's Depot
details: Kids Depot offers three programs, all designed to provide a loving, Christian, secure environment in which children can learn and play.

name: Kids Korner
details: We are Newly Accredited!! This means we have met the standards and are now classified as a High Quality Preschool and Daycare. Kids Korner provides preschool and daycare for 3-5 year olds, as well as before and after school care for school age children. A summer program is also offered for all ages.

name: Kiddy Karousel
details: Kiddy Karousel Provides: Nursery School and Day Care under the supervision of licensed teachers and child care professionals, 2) Special Programs encouraging health, education, and social skills, and 3) An Affordable Food Program * including hot lunch, free breakfast before 7:30 AM, and two free snacks served daily.

name: King of Glory Christian Preschool
details:
Our Mission: "Linking Children With Christ"

Our Purpose: Our purpose at King of Glory Preschool is to provide a quality education with the guidance and teachings of our Christian beliefs. Our program is committed to helping your child grow socially, emotionally, intellectually, physically, and spiritually.

name: Kinder Korner
details:
Our Center is pleased to welcome you and your
child (or children). We appreciate the thought and concern which you have given in the making of your choice. We want you to know that the philosophy of this child care center stems from our efforts of a decade in the business of creating "AN ATMOSPHERE OF LOVE AND APPROVAL" for children. Our certified staff of teachers and aides will support your child as he/she explores, expresses, and grows. We have chosen to work in this field because of the tremendous importance of the early childhood years. We know that this is a special time in your child's life and we are happy to be a part of it.

name: King of Grace Preschool
details:
King of Grace Lutheran School in Golden Valley, Minnesota is a private, Christian elementary day school focused on academic excellence. We achieve this through a challenging curriculum, partnering with parents for success and anchoring our daily instruction with God’s Word.

King of Grace offers Preschool and Kindergarten options along with comprehensive classes in 1st – 8th grade. During the school year parents may utilize our before and after school care, and a full day Summer Program nurtures children between grades.
 
King of Grace School provides opportunities to grow outside of the classroom as well, through extra-curricular activities. Our goal is for each student to emerge from school academically, spiritually and physically prepared to be productive Christian adults.

name: King's Kids
details:
King's Kids Preschool is a mission outreach program of Atonement. The mission of King's Kids Preschool is to offer a growth experience that includes teaching Christian attitudes and values, and allows for the physical, emotional, intellectual and social development of each child through cooperation with others of the same age.


For children 4 years old by Sept. 1, there is a M-W-F class from 9:15 to 11:30 a.m. and a T-Th. class from 12:45 to 3 p.m. For children 3 years old by Sept. 1, there is a T-Th. class from 9:15 to 11:30 a.m.


Our program is licensed by the Minnesota Department of Human Services.
The preschool relates to the church council through its education committee.

name: Lake Harriet Christian Child Care Center
details: We have been providing child care within walking distance of 50th and France for almost 30 years. Our NAEYC accredited center believes in keeping ratios low, imaginations and creativity active, and communication open. We are a small center with very close-knit families and teachers. We currently provide child care to children between the ages of six weeks and six years.

name: Lakes Head Start
details:
Head Start is a multi-faceted child and family development program for income-eligible households in Anoka and Washington Counties in Minnesota. The program is designed to help pregnant women and children, aged birth to five, and their families achieve their full potential.

The Head Start program literally gives children a head start on their journey of lifelong learning. The program also gives parents a head start in maintaining family continuity and self-sufficiency.

name: Learn And Grow Child Care Center, Inc.
Learning Tree Preschool
details: Welcome to Learning Tree Preschool, a Literacy-Enriched program of First Lutheran Church. Learning Tree is open to all 3-5-year olds on a first-come, first-served basis. We invite you to enroll your child(ren) to grow in learning and friendship in this wonderful preschool in a Christian setting.

name: Little Eskomo Lutheran Preschool
details: The Little Eskomo Lutheran Preschool is committed to providing a preschool program that promotes strong school readiness skills for children ages 3 to 5.  Each child will grow in spirit, mind and body with the sharing of God's freely given grace and the love of our Savior, Jesus Christ.

name: Little Falls Head Start
details: Local decision-making is the principle, which dictates the structure of the TCC Board of Directors and advisory committees. A unique coalition of local people initiates policy and ensures responsiveness of TCC's services to the needs of the citizens of Crow Wing, Morrison and Todd counties. One-third of the eighteen member TCC Board of Directors is composed of county commissioners. An additional one-third are democratically elected community representatives, and the remaining one-third represent a variety of community groups. Programs operated by TCC are planned and evaluated by community based advisory committees to the board.

name: Little Lambs Preschool
details:
The purpose of the preschool is to aid in the child’s spiritual, mental, social, emotional, and physical development. To accomplish this, our goals are:

    To teach the child about God and his plan of salvation
    To acquaint the child with letter and number concepts
    To develop the use of language
    To encourage creativity through art and music
    To foster cooperation and respect for others through social learning experiences
    To aid in exploring the environment through indoor and outdoor play

We provide both enrichment experiences to foster self-confidence, and new experiences which allow the child to question, seek and explore. The program strives to teach independence, responsibility, cooperative and self-awareness within the framework of Christian teaching.

name: Little Lambs Christian Preschool
details: Little Lambs Christian Center (part of Peace Lutheran Church) provides children opportunities for small group and individual time as appropriate for each age group. Children will explore in the following centers: literacy, math, dramatic play, science, technology (computer and smart board), art, large muscle and small muscle play, and sensory play. The Creative Curriculum will be utilized, along with Concordia Publishing materials, teacher created lessons. Prayer and Scripture lessons will be an important part of each day.

name: Lutheran Church of Peace Preschool
details: The purpose of Lutheran Church of Peace Preschool is to further each child's spiritual, intellectual, emotional, social and physical development by providing a program that will encourage and challenge the child to his or her fullest potential.  The program incorporates a Christian-based curriculum that fosters children's faith.

name: Macalester Plymouth Preschool
details:
A recent survey given to the parents of Macalester-Plymouth Preschool found that the top 3 reasons they chose Mac-Plymouth Preschool are:

1. Teachers

2. Curriculum

3. Student/Teacher Ratio

name: Macdonald Montessori School
details:
MacDonald Montessori School is a unique non-profit early childhood program located in the culturally vibrant West 7th area of St. Paul. Our urban location also brings us into close relation with the Mississippi River and many other environmental inspirations.

At MacDonald Montessori, parents, teachers and children are all partners of a learning community with strong emphasis placed on each child’s unique abilities in thinking, reasoning, questioning and experimenting in life.

All three protagonists, the teachers, the children and the parents come from many varied cultural and educational backgrounds but together they form one community that sees all children as powerful and competent individuals deserving of an exceptional environment and many varied and complex materials.

name: Mankato Head Start Center
details: Head Start is a child development program that serves eligible children and families. Head Start programs promote school readiness by providing educational, health, nutritional, social and other services to enrolled children and families. At Head Start, children learn to accept themselves, explore their world, and learn individually and as part of a group. Head Start responds to and supports each child's unique needs. All services provided by Head Start are of no cost to families.

name: Mary T Wellcome Child Development Center
details: Mary T. Wellcome Child Development Center is a licensed, nationally accredited and Four Star Parent Aware rated early child  development center established in 1929. Staff provide a comprehensive, educational and developmentally appropriate child care program for children ages six weeks to six years. Classroom teachers work to develop student’s skills in math, language, reading and creative arts, and encourage growth in social and emotional development and cultural awareness. The goal of the center is to prepare each child for Kindergarten and school success.  98% of our graduates have tested ready for school over the past 5 years based on Dynamic Indicators of Basic Early Literacy, Individual Grwoth and Development Indicators and other assessments.
business hours: 6:30 am to 5:30 p.m. Monday through Friday

name: Mc Donough Head Start
details:
Head Start and Early Head Start are comprehensive child development, health and social service programs for low-income families.  Since 1965, Head Start has been serving the needs of disadvantaged infants, children, and pregnant women across America.

Over 1400 children, from prenatal through age 5, are enrolled in Community Action’s programs each year throughout Ramsey County.  Options include full-day, half-day, therapeutic, and inclusion classrooms, and home-visiting programs.  Families who meet our eligibility requirements and families with children with special needs are encouraged to apply.

    The prenatal to age 3 program, Early Head Start, offers a home-based design for families. Early Head Start Home Visitors meet regularly with parents and children to nurture child development and parenting skills. Families who qualify for childcare assistance may also choose full-day, center-based enhanced childcare for children ages six weeks to five years.
    Head Start children between the ages of 3 to 5 attend center-based programming. Classes are offered in either half-day or full-day options at centers conveniently located throughout Ramsey County. Eight centers operate half-day classes, 4 days a week from September through late May. A full-day, full-year option is also available at the Bigelow Head Start Center, or through partnership contracts with community childcare facilities.

name: Meadow Park Day Care Center
details:
Our Mission: 
Christ-centered beginnings for a life of learning.

Personalized Program: 
MPPCCC limits enrollment to 39 children in the building at any given time.  The children are divided into age-specific classroom settings.  As a result, we provide a personal relationship with each child and their family.  We encourage family involvement and believe early childhood education is based on a partnership between parents, teachers and students.

Dedicated Professionals: 
The MPPCCC teaching staff are committed, degreed professionals and their longevity provides families and children with consistency and continuity.

name: Minnetonka Learning Center
details:
Established in 1987, MLC is a small, owner-operated preschool located north of Groveland Elementary School in St. Luke Church.  Although not affiliated with the church, our sunny classrooms are ideally located on the first floor of the church building overlooking Groveland school.  With a quiet neighborhood setting and backyard-style playground, we offer a preschool program and child care for children aged 33 months to 5 years. Our dedicated staff has been working together for 15 years preparing children for Kindergarten!

We recognize that each child is a unique individual. Our program offers the opportunity to grow and learn while providing a comfortable and secure environment.  We prepare children for Kindergarten; through caring and guidance, each child is encouraged to progress socially, emotionally, intellectually, and physically.  We strive to make each child’s experience a positive and successful one.  It is the goal of our staff to meet and exceed your expectations.

name: Montevideo Head Start
details:
MISSION STATEMENT
Our mission is to strive together to foster strong healthy children and their families and to promote staff excellence through dynamic programming.

name: Early Education Center Moorhead State University
address: 106a Lommen Hall 13th St Nd 6th Ave S
details:
The Early Education Center offers educational opportunities for young children to explore and learn about themselves and their environment. Children will be able to participate in activities designed to promote their emotional, social and physical growth.

We believe that every child is entitled to experiences and education appropriate to her/his individual needs. Therefore, we are continually striving to provide the environment and activities in which facilitate optimal growth and development of the whole child.

Our Center policies and practices support diversity among children, families, and staff. We encourage the acceptance of each person as an individual. The adults and children will help each other become aware of stereotypes and biases and work to eliminate them from relationships in our program.

Each group of children will have a certified teacher plus at least one teacher aid. Our teachers are professionals with a college degree and specific training in early childhood. They are able to promote the acceptance of "self" and others, encourage problem solving, communication, and provide a caring, consistent role model for young children. The child's teacher will be the main contact for the parents. However the directors are also available to confer with parents.

We also believe parents are an integral part of their child's program. Our goal is to have them involved in their child's activities, whenever possible. We encourage them to grow in their parenting skills through educational programs, interaction with professionals, and through sharing with other parents.

The program seeks to work with other university departments, students, and the community to meet the needs of the children enrolled and their families. We value cooperation and collaboration as effective means to solving problems and we encourage adults and children to learn and practice these skills.

name: WCCA Head Start-Mound
details:
The Wright County Community Action (WCCA) Head Start Program provides your 3-5 year old child with a head start. Community based child and family development programming through the Head Start program is available to eligible households throughout Wright and Western Hennepin County.

WCCA Head Start services promote cognitive, social, and emotional growth and development of 3-5 year old children from income eligible families and for age eligible children with special needs. Activities centered around health, education, nutrition and socialization are focused on children’s growth and development in language, literacy, math, science social functioning, creative arts, physical skills, overall learning abilities and more. Parent involvement and participation is a key element to each child’s success and actively promoted in Head Start.

WCCA provides Head Start programming at centers and through a Home/Parent based model. Daily schedules at centers vary by location and include 4 hour, 6 hour and extended day.

name: Mount Calvary Preschool
details:
Mount Calvary Preschool mirrors the core values of Mount Calvary Lutheran Church. Our preschool is built on grace, built for service, and builds up community. As a part of Mount Calvary's Faith Formation Department, our preschool is an outreach to our community.
 
We at Mount Calvary Preschool believe that each child is an individual. Our curriculum encourages children to explore their world through imagination, artistic and musical expression, physical movement, teacher-led activities, and social interaction. All domains of a child's development are met through our curriculum. We believe that early meaningful relationships with peers and adults benefit a child's social and emotional development throughout life, and also these early relationships enable a child's faith formation.

name: Mt. Airy Head Start
details:
Head Start and Early Head Start are comprehensive child development, health and social service programs for low-income families.  Since 1965, Head Start has been serving the needs of disadvantaged infants, children, and pregnant women across America.

Over 1400 children, from prenatal through age 5, are enrolled in Community Action’s programs each year throughout Ramsey County.  Options include full-day, half-day, therapeutic, and inclusion classrooms, and home-visiting programs.  Families who meet our eligibility requirements and families with children with special needs are encouraged to apply.

    The prenatal to age 3 program, Early Head Start, offers a home-based design for families. Early Head Start Home Visitors meet regularly with parents and children to nurture child development and parenting skills. Families who qualify for childcare assistance may also choose full-day, center-based enhanced childcare for children ages six weeks to five years.
    Head Start children between the ages of 3 to 5 attend center-based programming. Classes are offered in either half-day or full-day options at centers conveniently located throughout Ramsey County. Eight centers operate half-day classes, 4 days a week from September through late May. A full-day, full-year option is also available at the Bigelow Head Start Center, or through partnership contracts with community childcare facilities.

name: New Horizon Academy
details: It is not an average mission to provide the best child development on the planet, but then New Horizon Academy is not an average company. New Horizon Academy is an exceptional company, grown out of the commitment to children and families that Sue Dunkley, our founder, made in 1971 when she opened her first child care program. Sue's ongoing belief is that there is nothing more important than the self-esteem of every child. We invite you to see why New Horizon Academy is so much more than day care.

name: Broadway TAPP
details: At Broadway High School we provide a personalized learning environment for students to complete their high school education and build a strong future through an emphasis on attendance, academic achievement, and positive relationships. By encouraging critical thought, providing prenatal and parenting education, and partnering with community services we support diploma-driven parents and kindergarten ready children as they establish the groundwork for lifelong learning.

name: Normandale Preschool
details:
Our Mission
We at Normandale Preschool,
An outreach of Normandale Lutheran Church,
Provide excellence in education
In a safe, loving Christian environment
Through activities that promote readiness for success
At school, at home and in the community

name: North Oaks Preschool
details: The mission of North Oaks Preschool is to supplement early home experiences in a warm, loving, healthy and safe environment as well as to develop a strong, positive self-concept through interaction with peers and supportive adults. We teach and model positive self-image, individuality, independence and respect of others. Children are offered the opportunity to grow and develop socially, emotionally, cognitively and physically.

name: Northome Head Start
details:
KOOTASCA is a non profit human service agency serving Itasca and Koochiching counties in Northern Minnesota. We serve low-income people providing ways for families to get connected to the community with a plan to get out of poverty. Our mission is “Building Community to End Poverty”. Our services include:
    Housing Programs - crisis housing, rehabilitation, energy assistance, home ownership workshops, down payment & financial counseling, closing cost assistance.

    Head Start - and early Head Start, project read early literacy, family services & involvement, health services. Check out our report to the public.
    Click Here to see the report

    Crisis Services - family support program in our community designed to provide emergency or short-term care for children 0-12 years while families address crisis situations and includes Crisis Housing.

name: One of a Kind Children's Center, Inc.
details:
ONE OF A KIND Children’s Center has been a staple name in the community of South Minneapolis for more than 30 years. Established in 1979, ONE OF A KIND is your child’s home away from home. Our mission is to provide quality care to every child that enters our center. Your child will be cared for by some exceptional individuals, many of which have been part of the staff family for more than 10 years. We strive to create an atmosphere that is physically, mentally, and spiritually as well as emotionally healthy for the children in our care. We provide an environment where each child is respected and accepted as an individual.

Our center is licensed for children from 33 months to 12 years. As part of their developmental curriculum, your child will learn phonics, math, social skills, conflict resolution, ethics, manners, motor skills, computer skills, art, and self care. We offer pre-school programs, Kindergarten, and before/after school-age care. Call us today for more information!

name: Our Redeemer Christian Children's Center
details: The Christian Children's Center experienced and qualified staff provides a safe, warm, loving Christian environment for your child to explore and build on their intellectual, social and emotional developmental skills.  Specific areas of interest in our programs include music and story time, outside activities, gym time, art, math, science, dramatic play, and Christian activities.
business hours: 6:45 AM to 5:45 PM  Monday through Friday

name: Our Savior Early Childhood Center
details:
Our Objectives
    Work and play in a Christian atmosphere with other children.
    Be aware of the daily presence of Christ in their lives.
    Express themselves through art and play materials freely and constructively.
    Provide opportunities to develop large and fine motor skills.
    Provide a healthy environment, proper nutrition, rest, and physical exercise.
    Provide developmentally appropriate curriculum including experiences in many areas (Readiness skills in reading, math, language skills, science)
    Learn to be independent--to solve their own problems and do things for themselves.
    Learn to establish relationships with adults other than family.
    Learn developmentally appropriate limits of behavior.
    Build feelings of self-esteem and security.
    Increase their ability to handle their emotions constructively.
    Learn respect for others' feelings and belongings.
    Enjoy a Preschool and/or Child Care Program experience that will simplify adjustment to elementary school and other social situations.

name: Semcac Head Start-Owatonna
details: We are committed to building bright futures by enriching young   children, ages Birth – 5 years old, and empowering their families. Comprehensive services and community opportunities support healthy families.

name: South Education Center Early Learning Center
Playhouse Nursery School
details: Playhouse Preschool is for children 3, 4 and 5 years of age. Children must be 3 years of age by September 1st of the current school year. Children must be toilet trained. Pull-ups may not be worn to school.

name: Rainbow School and Child Care
details: Rainbow is a friendly place "where everyone knows your name" with a value system that accepts children as they are while encouraging the total development of the child and fostering individual needs, interests, and abilities. Rainbow is supportive of parents by encouraging involvement and open communication.

name: Southeast Head Start A and B
Ready, Set, Grow
details:
King of Kings is the sponsor of this Christian environment through which your child can grow, explore, experiment, and discover their world.  We promote the social, intellectual, emotional, and spiritual development of each child.  Classes are for children age 3 (by Sept. 1st) through 5-years-old.

Our goal is to provide a Christian atmosphere of warmth, understanding, and caring: a place for your child to be that special, unique person that God so lovingly created, and a place where learning is fun as well as meaningful.  A place where children can learn how to make a friend, and how to be one!
 
At Ready, Set, Grow, we believe that early learning is important and essential.  Research in child development indicates that children learn as they interact with other children, adults, and their environment; an active learning literacy process.  Our program provides opportunities for children to learn through a variety of experiences in language, math, science, dramatic play, music, and movement.  We allow children to make choices and guide them to solve problems in a safe, positive environment to promote independence, healthy self-esteem, and emotional and social development.

name: Redeemer Lutheran Preschool
details:
Preschool program which coincides with the public school calendar.
For children 33 months – five years.
Creative theme-based education.
Daily “Praisetime”.
Opportunities to grow in the Christian faith.
Age-appropriate academic activities.
 Music, dramatic play, sensory and arts & crafts.
Strong emphasis on play and literacy.
Bright comfortable classroom with restroom, kitchenette, and lots of windows.
Large indoor motor room.
Fenced-in playground with climbers, sandbox, riding toys, a riding track, and shade trees. 
Community garden and green space.
Field trips and resource people.
Family events.

name: Roseville Nursery Group/After-School Kids at Calvary Church
Seed Early Learning Academy
details:
Our Mission:
To instruct, empower, enable and guide Scholars to achieve superior academic, social and moral development.

name: Shirley G Moore laboratory School
details:
The Shirley G. Moore Laboratory School at the University of Minnesota is sponsored by the Institute of Child Development. The Institute has been a national focal point of child study since its inception in 1925; the Lab School has made a substantial contribution to this effort.

Its primary goals are:

    Demonstrating exemplary early childhood practices and providing a sound educational setting for preschool children
    Training teachers of young children at both the graduate and undergraduate levels
    Serving as an active center of child study and research.

name: Small World School for Young Children
details:
Did you know that children do their most important learning before the age of five?  That’s why, in addition to lots of love and attention, everything we do at Small World School involves early childhood development.  We cultivate intentional environments that nurture each child's social, emotional, spiritual, and intellectual development.

 

We begin with age-appropriate environments that encourage children to learn, play and explore. You name it -- books, blocks, puppets, paper, toys and tambourines, they are all here ready for your child to experience. There are sticks for counting, seeds for planting and places for exploring. Your young child will find an endless assortment of activities that engage their interest and stimulate their mind, heart, and hands.

 

At the heart of every project and activity, there are specially trained teachers and age-appropriate curriculum to lead the way.  Your child will benefit from the exceptional staff of teachers at Small World School.  They are caring, intentional, artful and highly experienced. They are gifted at identifying and nurturing your child's gifts, abilities, and unique personality.

 

Children learn differently than adults.  They need hands-on experiences and teachers that are actively engaged and participate with them. Children need warmth and attention. They need enthusiasm and encouragement. Most of all, they need the joy and challenge of doing activities themselves, because that’s what helps children learn and grow, and that’s our mission at Small World School.

name: Little Giants
details: Early Learning Center that provides quality care and preschool enrichment for children 6 weeks up to 5 years old.

name: Teenage Pregnancy and Parenting Programs South High
Preschools of St. Andrew's Half Day (The)
details:
The key to establishing a Christian environment is employing teachers who have committed their lives to Jesus Christ.

Teachers will assist the children in:
     Becoming more familiar with Jesus Christ through prayer and with bible stories
     Helping them understand that God loves them.
     Helping them understand that God makes them uniquely special.
     Growing in their ability to love one another.

name: St. Anthony Park Co-op Preschool
details:
We celebrate families!
    Parents and teachers create a caring community to nurture children and families. Parents get acquainted with other families at picnics, holiday parties, and other social events. Those parents who are available are invited to our Parent Group that meets once a month during school hours, with younger siblings welcome.
    Parents are always welcome at the school. Some parents serve on our elected Parent Board, others may share their talents in music, dancing, or woodworking, while others may help with ethnic or other celebrations. All forms of parent participation are always appreciated.

We encourage children to learn to solve problems.
    We help children learn to resolve conflicts peacefully.
    We create a safe, nurturing environment where children can express their own needs and feelings, and learn to appreciate the needs and feelings of their friends.
    We help children become more self-reliant.
    We talk about their ideas and questions, and we all observe nature.

name: St. Anthony Park UMC Nursery School
St Francis Xavier Child Development Center
St. Mark's Preschool
details:
It is the philosophy of St. Mark’s Preschool that early childhood should be a time of fun, warmth, security, exploring, and discovery. Preschool children are creative and receptive; the staff strives to nurture and encourage these qualities in the children who attend. The preschool’s purpose is to provide an atmosphere that encourages social, emotional, physical, and intellectual growth and development of the child as a whole.

Planned within the framework of philosophy and purpose, St. Mark’s Preschool’s curriculum includes sharing and conversation time, stories, songs, and fingerplays: creative art activities and crafts; games and large muscle activities; field trips throughout the community; food preparation; science and nature activities: exposure to shapes, colors, numbers, and letters; and celebration of birthdays and holidays.

name: St. Michael's Lutheran Preschool
details:
St. Michael’s Lutheran Preschool is a Christian education facility.  At our preschool young children participate in experiences away from home before entering the elementary school. The objective of St. Michael’s Preschool is to provide each child a safe, loving and positive environment where faith is naturally integrated into the curriculum.

Our program of education considers the whole child-his/her spiritual, emotional, social, intellectual, and physical welfare. We desire to assist parents in developing Christian character and the citizenship of their children.

name: St Paul Preschool
details:
Our pre-school is open to all children aged 3-5. We offer half day classes five days a week.

The three year old class is offered Tuesday and Thursday with a morning session (8:30-11:15) and an afternoon session (12:15-3:00).

The four and five year old class is offered Monday, Wednesday, and Friday. There is a morning session (8:30-11:15) and an afternoon session (12:15-3:00).

Our curriculum is developed to teach children the core concepts to prepare them for kindergarten. We offer these concepts in a Christian environment with the teachings of our Lord as a centerpiece.

Our facilities are located within the educational wing of St. Paul Lutheran Church. We provide an excellent learning environment staffed by trained educational professionals.

name: St. Paul's Childhood Center
details:
SPCC provides developmentally appropriate learning experiences and care, in a safe, nurturing, engaging, and interactive environment. The environment and guidance from teachers fosters positive growth and development. Teachers collaborate with parents to create an inclusive atmosphere, develop strong  relationships with families, creating a community of advocates for families, children, early childhood learning, and early childhood educators.

 The classroom environments we offer help to build a strong self-esteem through positive interactions, and encouraging individuality. Teachers offer learning experiences that challenge young minds, as well as set them up with opportunities for success. Respect for one’s self and others is a core value at SPCC, and we celebrate individuality of all persons regardless of age, gender, ethnicity, ability, sexual orientation or religion.

Our center uses a family-centered approach, research shows resoundingly how addressing the family system holistically is exponentially beneficial for the child. We are a resource for families and welcome families to collaborate with us through any challenges they are facing. We see ourselves as collaborators and partners with each family we work with.

name: St. Paul's Lutheran Preschool
details:
Welcome to St. Paul's Lutheran School!

Founded in 1910, St. Paul's Lutheran School is a nationally accredited elementary school that provides an unparalleled educational experience for students in preschool through sixth grade.

St. Paul's has been providing quality education for students of Perham and the surrounding area for over 100 years, and the tradition and excellence continues today.  Many of the top students in the public school honor rolls are alumni of St. Paul's.  Our school gives students the chance to reach their full academic potential, understand their self-worth, develop a positive attitude, and grow in their Christian faith.

Our doors are open to all students and families.  We welcome the opportunity to serve your child and family.

name: Semcac Head Start-St. Charles
details: We are committed to building bright futures by enriching young   children, ages Birth – 5 years old, and empowering their families. Comprehensive services and community opportunities support healthy families.

name: Sugar Plum Child Care and Preschool Center, Inc.
details:
We provide the Saint Cloud, Minnesota area with a complete range of pre-school and childcare services. Our long time staff provides a safe and fun learning environment for children to develop skills for social interaction, school readiness and personal growth. A place where everyone is accepted, everyone is important, everyone is equal, and everyone is respected.

We have a strong commitment to our community. At Sugar Plum Child Care & Preschool Center, children always come first. We have many long time staff of 10 to 26 years. This creates a very stable, consistent and happy atmosphere for the children. It also reflects the love that our staff have for the children in our care.

Sugar Plum Child Care & Preschool Center has been serving the Saint Cloud, Minnesota and surrounding area for over 26 years. Our mission statement is to provide a safe and fun learning environment for children while their parents work or attend school. It is our goal to encourage children in their individualities and culture, while appreciating their classmates and their individualities and culture. We are committed to helping your child achieve a strong self worth.

name: Sunny Days Preschool
details:
The aim of the Sunny Days Preschool is to supplement the home in providing experiences that promote intellectual, social, religious, emotional, and physical development of your child.

It is the combination of playmates, creative experiences, a Christian atmosphere, and a friendly, competent teacher, which makes preschool a valuable experience. Our hope and prayer is that a child will come to know Jesus through association with caring Christian adults.
business hours:
Monday/Wednesday/Friday classes 8:45-11:45 A.M. and 12:15-2:45 P.M.

Tuesday/Thursday classes 8:45-11:15 A.M. and 12:15-2:45 P.M.

name: Trinity Lone Oak Lutheran School Preschool
details:
The Preschool Program at Trinity Lone Oak Lutheran serves as an introduction to education for 3- and 4-year-olds and a strong foundation for learning.

Children who attend preschool at TLO have a chance to practice social interactions, discover new interests, develop their independence and learn more about God and Jesus. Preschool prepares them for future education, and in particular, helps with Kindergarten readiness.

Teachers and staff in our Preschool Program recognize the importance of helping children discover how to learn and succeed in the school culture. They focus on fostering self-confidence, developing the whole child and encouraging exploration.

TLO offers 3-year-old and 4-year-old preschool with the option to register for a morning program or a full-day preschool option wherein you can choose the number of days and sessions you would like. Our full-day options include early drop-off, lunch and afternoon enrichment opportunities.

name: Trinity Nursery School
details: Growing Little Disciples for Christ”-TNS is an outreach of Trinity Lutheran Church. Trinity Nursery School offers a caring Christian atmosphere where children learn by doing. TNS is a non-profit preschool for children age 3, 4, or 5 by September 1 of the preschool year. Children must be fully toilet trained by the first day of school.
business hours:
Morning Classes                   
8:15 – 10:45 am 

Afternoon Classes                           11:45 – 2:15 pm

name: Li'l Lumberjacks' Learning Center
details:
Li'l Lumberjacks Learning Center is a year-round program serving children six weeks to the first day of Kindergarten.
    We are licensed by the Minnesota Department of Human Services.  
    Your child will participate in one of four age appropriate program offerings: Infant, Infant/Toddler Transition, Toddler, and Preschool.

name: St. John's Wee Care Learning Center
Wee World Preschool
details:
Wee World Preschool has been a part of the city of Tracy Minnesota for over 35 years. It began as a daycare for the community and has seen many changes over the years. Currently, Wee World is a preschool with 2 separate classes. Our class for 3 year old turning 4 is held on Tuesday and Thursday mornings from 8:30-11:00. Our classes for 4 year olds turning 5 are Monday, Wednesday and Friday mornings in the month of September only then switching to an extended day format beginning the first Monday in October. That class is 8:30 until 2:30 .

We have a wonderful, caring staff that is able to help each child grow and develop into lifelong learners!  Our curriculum is designed and modeled after the Creative Curriculum which focus’ on the whole child and their innate desire to explore and create.  Our job is to make your child’s first experience with school the most positive experience possible.  Together, we can make that happen.

name: Trinity Children's Center
details:
Trinity Children’s Center is a non-denominational Christian childcare/preschool Center. Enrollment is open to all children regardless of religious preference. We incorporate the preschool program throughout your child’s day.

TCC is open year around from 7:00 am-5:30 pm Monday through Friday.
TCC is Licensed by the Minnesota Department of Human Services.
We pray before meals, sing Christian songs, read Bible stories and celebrate Christian Holidays.
We are open for part time or full time enrollment
We are licensed for 54 children, we are divided into 5 classrooms

name: St Olaf Wee Learning Center
details: The St. Olaf Wee Learning Center is a non-profit Licensed Christian preschool.  Our center is proud to be a 4 star parent aware rated site.   Our goal is to provide children with the opportunity to learn about the love of Christ and help them prepare to enter kindergarten. We aid them in the development of social, cognitive, and motor skills, along with helping them find confidence in themselves. Come join us and watch your children grow in ways you've never imagined.

name: Anoka Child Care Center
details:
Anoka Child Care Center provides activities that are appropriate for the age of your child.  

Our center encourages parent's participation in the child's center days.  Early Childhood educators work with the children, parents and staff to provide a stimulating and educational environment for each child.

These early interactions will help the young child to know how to think, feel, behave and learn for the rest of their lives.

name: King's Kids Preschool
details:
It is our goal to provide:
1.  Opportunities for Christian learning of Jesus Christ.
2.  Opportunities and activities to help children develop healthy self-concepts.
3.  Experiences and activities that fufill a child's basic needs:  spiritual, emotional, intelletual, psychological and physical.
4.  Learning which will broaden a child's aptitude for future schoolwork with activities in motor perception, math, science, religion, social studies and art.

Our objective at King's Kids is to provide a school readiness curriculum in a Christian environment.  We believe childhood is a journey, not a race.  We strive to pave the path for each child's future through faith.  King's Kids is dedicated to sering as a foundation for Christian values and future learning.

name: Eden Prairie Montessori Learning Center
details: At Eden Prairie Montessori we are committed to providing quality education and care for young children, to prepare them to become responsible, respectful, and independent individuals and life-long learners.

name: Cobber Kids
details: Cobber Kids, located on the campus of Concordia College, Moorhead, Minn., earned accreditation from the National Association for the Education of Young Children (NAEYC) – the nation’s leading organization of early childhood professionals. To earn NAEYC accreditation, Cobber Kids went through an extensive self-study process and on-site visit, measuring the program and its services against the ten NAEYC Early Childhood Program Standards and more than 400 related Accreditation Criteria. In the 25 years since NAEYC Accreditation was established, it has become a widely recognized sign of high-quality early childhood education.
business hours:
7 a.m.-5:30 p.m. Monday-Friday

Summer: 7:30 a.m.-5:30 p.m. Monday-Friday

name: St. John's Preschool
details: St. John the Evangelist Catholic School is a community of faith-filled people dedicated to providing educational excellence for the mind, body, and spirit.

name: Parents Choice For Kids
details: We believe that every child is unique and special. Our nurturing staff and carefully designed work settings enhance children’s intellectual, physical and social growth; children are offered a wide variety of activities to enhance their learning. Our program is teacher directed and child initiated, encouraging children to explore and discover within a controlled and structured environment. We are the #1 Daycare and Preschool serving Burnsville, Prior Lake, Eagan, Savage, Lakeville and Apple Valley. We are your choice for daycare in Burnsville.

name: WCCA Head Start-Rogers
details:
The Wright County Community Action (WCCA) Head Start Program provides your 3-5 year old child with a head start. Community based child and family development programming through the Head Start program is available to eligible households throughout Wright and Western Hennepin County.

WCCA Head Start services promote cognitive, social, and emotional growth and development of 3-5 year old children from income eligible families and for age eligible children with special needs. Activities centered around health, education, nutrition and socialization are focused on children’s growth and development in language, literacy, math, science social functioning, creative arts, physical skills, overall learning abilities and more. Parent involvement and participation is a key element to each child’s success and actively promoted in Head Start.

WCCA provides Head Start programming at centers and through a Home/Parent based model. Daily schedules at centers vary by location and include 4 hour, 6 hour and extended day.

name: Sugar Plum Child Care and Preschool Center, Inc.
details:
We provide the Saint Cloud, Minnesota area with a complete range of pre-school and childcare services. Our long time staff provides a safe and fun learning environment for children to develop skills for social interaction, school readiness and personal growth. A place where everyone is accepted, everyone is important, everyone is equal, and everyone is respected.

We have a strong commitment to our community. At Sugar Plum Child Care & Preschool Center, children always come first. We have many long time staff of 10 to 26 years. This creates a very stable, consistent and happy atmosphere for the children. It also reflects the love that our staff have for the children in our care.

Sugar Plum Child Care & Preschool Center has been serving the Saint Cloud, Minnesota and surrounding area for over 26 years. Our mission statement is to provide a safe and fun learning environment for children while their parents work or attend school. It is our goal to encourage children in their individualities and culture, while appreciating their classmates and their individualities and culture. We are committed to helping your child achieve a strong self worth.

name: Child Care Resource and Referral Head Start
Highland Park Montessori School
details:
WHY CHOOSE MONTESSORI?
Because it works! Montessori education is a progressive, scientifically based method that was developed by Dr. Maria Montessori through decades of observing how children learn. In its 107th year, Montessori education continues to inspire children and celebrate their love of learning, individual growth and independence in the context of a social community.

name: Children's Ark Hourly Child Care Program (The)
Semcac Head Start-Preston
details: We are committed to building bright futures by enriching young   children, ages Birth – 5 years old, and empowering their families. Comprehensive services and community opportunities support healthy families.

name: Pipestone Head Start Center Peace United Methodist Church
Kids at Heart Child Care Center
details: Kids at Heart is a Child Care Center that cares for children ages 6 weeks to 12 years. Our hours are 6am to 6pm Monday through Friday. We also have a preschool program to get your child ready and prepared school!

name: Sunshine Tree
details: Sunshine Tree is a ministry of Northridge Church. We are a Christian day care center that believes that the Bible is the inspired word of God and prayer is an essential part of our ministry here. We strive to meet the intellectual, physical, social, and emotional progress of each child. We try to create an atmosphere of love and understanding for your child through happy songs, exciting stories out of the Bible, during our chapel time. The children pray before each meal time and during chapel time.

name: Brainerd Head Start
details: Local decision-making is the principle, which dictates the structure of the TCC Board of Directors and advisory committees. A unique coalition of local people initiates policy and ensures responsiveness of TCC's services to the needs of the citizens of Crow Wing, Morrison and Todd counties. One-third of the eighteen member TCC Board of Directors is composed of county commissioners. An additional one-third are democratically elected community representatives, and the remaining one-third represent a variety of community groups. Programs operated by TCC are planned and evaluated by community based advisory committees to the board.

name: South Branch Early Childhood Family Evelopment Center
Fraser Early Childhood Family Development Center
details:
Children enter the world ready to learn. PICA’s Head Start and Early Head Start programs help children build on this natural ability. PICA respects each child’s individuality and honors his/her cultural, ethnic, and family heritage. Our child-centered curriculum, the New World Curriculum, focuses on the interests, learning styles, and developmental needs of the individual child and helps each child develop self-esteem, self-help skills, and socialization skills.

Parent involvement is the most important part of Head Start and Early Head Start. At PICA, parents have decision-making power and are involved in all parts of the program.

name: Scandia Preschool
details: As an outreach program of Elim Lutheran Church, Scandia Preschool will be open to the community at large. All children will be welcomed and given equal opportunity regardless of sex, religion, or race. It is the objective of Scandia Preschool to provide enriching experiences to help each child develop spiritually, physically, emotionally, cognitively and socially. The School is licensed through the State of Minnesota. As part of Elim Lutheran Church, the Preschool will celebrate religious holidays, incorporate Christian stories and say a prayer before snack.

name: Kids and Company Child Care Center
details: Kids & Co. Child Care Center (KCCCC) is a licensed and insured day care center established in 1992. It is designed to meet the needs of the working parent whose children need care. The goal of this program is to provide an environment conducive to learning and growing through hands on experiences. It provides a structured recreational environment in which learning is experienced through a multiple range of activities.

name: Appletime Child Care, Inc.
details:
We at Appletime believe that nothing is more precious than your child. Therefore, our caring, qualified staff is committed to providing a safe and secure learning environment designed to foster self-esteem and personal growth.

Appletime has been serving families of children aged 6 weeks through 12 years since 1989. We offer, first and foremost, a dedication to children. Our age-appropriate curriculum includes a wide variety of activities. Each age group has a weekly curriculum designed to promote social, emotional, and academic development. Our trained staff are knowledgeable and devoted to creating a stable environment where parents can trust that their child’s individual needs and goals are being met. We emphasize open communication between parents and staff. These commitments pave the way for building personal, nurturing relationships with the children in our care.

name: Epiphany Preschool
details:
The main objective of Epiphany Preschool is to provide the highest quality learning experience possible for young children, in a Christian environment.  We meet this goal by nurturing each child's own love of learning.

We learn through play!  What better way to educate children than through play?  Our hands on approach to early childhood education provides the children the opportunity to develop emotionally, intellectually, socially, spiritually, and physically - at their own pace. Through a positive learning environment, children grow to feel good about themselves and others. This allows their attitudes, skills, and curiosities to expand and grow, just as they do. Group cooperation, concern for others and responsible behavior are all concepts we encourage among the children.

Epiphany Preschool welcomes children ages 3 through 5. Our program is licensed by the Minnesota Department of Human Services to serve 20 children per session with one lead teacher and one assistant. Enrollment is filled on a first-come-first serve basis of registration.

name: Preschool U
details: Our preschool LOVES children. Children are our future and we strive to make their preschool experience one that will create their love for learning. We are located in Corcoran, MN (which is near Maple Grove and Rogers). We are a Christian based preschool. Not only do we prepare our children for their educational career through social learning, but we also teach stories from the bible. We love celebrating Thanksgiving, Christmas and Easter with our young friends at Preschool “U”. Preschool “U” was established in 1992 by Nancy Sanford. Nancy has a B.S. degree in Music K-12 and is a qualified preschool teacher.

name: Zumbrota Head Start Center
details:
Head Start is a comprehensive preschool program focusing on child development and serving 3- and 4-year-old children and their families. Head Start establishes relationships that promote growth and development in young children and encourages the self-sufficiency of families.

The program is family-centered, strength-based and designed to foster the parent's role as the principle influence on their child's development and to assist families in developing and achieving self-reliance.

name: Roosevelt Head Start
details:
Head Start and Early Head Start are comprehensive child development, health and social service programs for low-income families.  Since 1965, Head Start has been serving the needs of disadvantaged infants, children, and pregnant women across America.

Over 1400 children, from prenatal through age 5, are enrolled in Community Action’s programs each year throughout Ramsey County.  Options include full-day, half-day, therapeutic, and inclusion classrooms, and home-visiting programs.  Families who meet our eligibility requirements and families with children with special needs are encouraged to apply.

    The prenatal to age 3 program, Early Head Start, offers a home-based design for families. Early Head Start Home Visitors meet regularly with parents and children to nurture child development and parenting skills. Families who qualify for childcare assistance may also choose full-day, center-based enhanced childcare for children ages six weeks to five years.
    Head Start children between the ages of 3 to 5 attend center-based programming. Classes are offered in either half-day or full-day options at centers conveniently located throughout Ramsey County. Eight centers operate half-day classes, 4 days a week from September through late May. A full-day, full-year option is also available at the Bigelow Head Start Center, or through partnership contracts with community childcare facilities.

name: Walker Head Start
details: BI-CAP’s Early Head Start (EHS) program is an intensive, comprehensive, flexible program that is designed to reinforce and respond to the unique strengths and needs of each individual child (age 0-3) and his/her family.  EHS programs promote healthy prenatal outcomes for pregnant women, enhance the development of very young children, and promote healthy family functioning.  Head Start is a national program that promotes school readiness by enhancing the social and cognitive development of children through educational, health, nutritional, social and other services for enrolled children and families.  Classroom teams focus on helping preschoolers develop the early reading and math skills and the social skills they need to be successful in school.  Head Start has a long tradition of delivering comprehensive services designed to foster healthy development in the most vulnerable young children, including those with special needs.

name: First Discoveries Preschool Center
details:
We believe...
    All children are unique and special creations of God.
    Developmental stages of children are important considerations in creating appropriate learning environments and activities.
    Children learn through play.
    The key to establishing our Christian environment at First Discoveries is through teachers who have committed their lives to Jesus Christ. Bible stories are incorporated into the program as well as a faith-based curriculum.

name: Campus Playhouse St. Cloud Technical College
details:
We provide an enriched environment where children flourish and positive relationships are formed. Our structured, yet playful environment provides a safe and nurturing atmosphere. Partnerships are formed between professional staff, children, families, and the community fostering lasting relationships.

Early care and learning opportunities enhance each child’s educational, social, emotional, and physical needs preparing them for their future.

name: Kids ABC Learning Center Inc
details:
Michele Birdsall and Lynda Trenberth, owners of Kids ABC Learning Center Inc are committed to providing each and every child that comes through our door with a safe and fun environment and aim to offer the highest quality child care services throughout the Chisholm MN area.

For over 18 years, Kids ABC Learning Center Inc has been proudly taking care of children throughout the Chisholm MN area. We provide the most caring and attentive child care services and know that each day your child visits us, you’ll both feel completely at ease! We specialize in assisting childhood development and truly care about the well-being and education of the children we supervise.

We offer a daily preschool curriculum for kids from at 33 months – 5 years, consisting of art projects, language arts, large and small muscle activities, math, music, reading, science, snacks, writing and much more. We also offer before care and after care for busy parents with kids as old as 12 years.

It’s not easy to leave your child in a new environment, which is why we welcome you to give us a call and we will happily set up an interview for you and your child to come meet our friendly teachers. You will also be able
Little Girl with Pen and Paper

to tour the facility where your child will be learning and growing. We know that once you enter our building, you’ll know our school is the best choice!

name: Tomorrow's Kids of Eagan, Inc.
details: For 20 years Tomorrow's Kids Montessori has been dedicated to helping children to develop their natural sense of curiosity and wonder through exploration, discovery and creativity. At TKM we believe that a child learns best in an enriched, supportive environment with the guidance and encouragement of a trained and caring staff. Tomorrow's Kids Montessori is designed to be the perfect beginning to a lifelong tendency to embrace learning.

name: Red Balloon Child Care Center
details:
We are licensed under Rule 3 by the State of Minnesota.  Our license is for:
    12 infants: 6 weeks to 16 months; ratio 1 to 4
    21 toddlers:  16 months to 33 months; ratio 1 to 7
    91 preschool/School-age
       Preschool: 33 months to first day of Kindergarten; ratio 1 to 10
       School-age: first day of Kindergarten to age 12; ratio 1 to 15

name: Celebrating Children Preschool
details: Shepherd of the Valley invites all people to experience the Welcome, Transformation, and Sending of Jesus Christ

name: Northwestern College Child Development Center
details:
The Child Development Center (CDC) at University of Northwestern offers a warm and welcoming environment where children feel a sense of belonging. It is a safe and loving family atmosphere full of music, fun and learning. We teach with Christian values where every child is upheld as a beloved child of God.

Your child's well-being is our top priority. We have a bright and cheery facility—where your child will feel safe and secure—designed specifically for the comfort and ease of young children with the protection of a security door and fenced play areas.

The CDC helps your child to thrive and grow—this goal is at the heart of the care each child receives at the University of Northwestern Child Development Center.
business hours: Monday through Friday from 7 a.m. to 6 p.m.

name: Visitation Child Care Center
details:
Visitation's Child Care Center is guided by the same mission as the entire school, to provide "an excellent education within a Catholic environment permeated by Salesian Spirituality."  We offer child-centered care through developmentally appropriate activities intended to help foster each child’s unique and individual potential as a human being. 

Visitation Child Care Center is situated in a multi-generational environment: six week old infants through 90 year old Sisiters get to spend their days together at Vis!  Visit each of the classrooms through the links on the left.

name: Owatonna Migrant Head Start
details:
Head Start is a program that helps young children between the ages of three and five grow up ready to succeed in school and in life. Programs work to meet high standards for delivering quality services to children and their families. Children who attend Head Start programs participate in fun activities while developing social skills. Head Start children also receive nutritious meals and the necessary health care in a safe environment.

Early Head Start is a program for families with infants and toddlers ages birth to three. Families who are expecting a new baby may enroll in Early Head Start. Families do not pay a fee for Head Start or Early Head Start.

Parents with children in Head Start participate in all aspects of the program. They help to govern, plan what children learn, and provide advice about needed services. Parents and other community members also volunteer in classrooms and other parts of the programs.

Head Start and Early Head Start welcome children with disabilities. Parents of children with disabilities are strongly encouraged to participate in their children’s daily routines and activities.

Migrant & Seasonal Head Start program provides comprehensive Head Start services, including child development, and social and health services, to low-income families working in agriculture, or families who migrate for the purpose of working in agriculture.

name: Children's House
details: Children’s House provides early learning opportunities and all-day care for infants through preschoolers in a secure, fun and educational environment. Our high ratio of staff to children allows our caring, credentialed teachers to build relationships with each child. We offer play-based learning opportunities for all ages in our classrooms and a spacious outdoor playground. Children’s House has been nationally accredited since 2011.

name: Salem Lutheran Preschool
details:
Mission Statement
We believe Salem Lutheran Preschool will be a visible witness to the community by providing a nurturing, Christian environment for children and their families, that supports each child’s spiritual, social, intellectual, and physical development.

name: Bethlehem Lutheran Preschool
details: Since 1965, Bethlehem Lutheran ECC has been, and continues to be, a welcoming environment where children are given the tools needed to grow in God’s love and experience the world around them.  As stated in our mission, “Bethlehem Lutheran Early Childhood Center will inspire creativity and nurture the social, emotional, intellectual, physical and spiritual development of children in a Christian environment”

name: WCCA Head Start-Annandale
details:

WCCA Head Start services promote cognitive, social, and emotional growth and development of 3-5 year old children from income eligible families and for age eligible children with special needs. name: We Love Kids
details:
We Love Kids has been in operation since 1981 providing quality care for children ages 6 weeks until 12 years.

We strive to make a difference in the lives of children as well as their families. Our focus is the whole child. We work with each child to enhance social, emotional, and physical development.

We Love Kids provides a safe and secure environmentwhere children can express themselves. Children will participate in group time, art, outdoor play, meal times, field trips, and more while attending our facility.

Our teachers are experienced and trained in Early Childhood Education and continue their education throughout the year by participating in in-service training regarding children and their development.

We strive to provide a thematic based unit in order to five each child an opportunity to enjoy what they are learning. Our themes change monthly. When exploring each theme, children will experience many different ways of learning such as through books, art, writing, dramatic play, science, sensory, and so forth.

name: Stewartville Christian Church Child Care Center
Creation Station
details: The philosophy here at Creation Station is based on our belief that all children share certain needs and have a drive to be self-confident, self-motivated individuals, seeking out an understanding of the world around them. It is our goal to provide a learning environment which will empower children and enhance self-esteem by creating an atmosphere where social, emotional, physical, and cognitive development can take place. This goal is met by providing a variety of activities and experiences which allow the child to be creative, to discover, and to solve problems. We will accept all children regardless of race, color, creed, sex, religious or ethnic backgrounds.

name: Precious is the Child
details:
Our preschool was founded by church members in 1997 as an outreach tool for our community to help fulfill the command from God to "Go and make disciples of all nations...." Matthew 28:19.

Precious is the Child serves families of any background with children aged 3 1/2 to 5 years old with a maximum of 20 (usually less) children at one time. Our curriculum includes early childhood skill development in a Christ-centered environment.  We are located in southeast Rochester at Ascension Evangelical Lutheran Church, with which we are also affiliated.

name: Angels Unlimited Preschool
details:
Angels Unlimited Preschool located in Red Wing, Minnesota offers children a variety of learning experiences that will enhance your child’s physical, social, intellectual and skills development.  This Red Wing preschool provides a creative child-centered setting that seeks to motivate the abilities of four to five year old children in a learning environment.  Focusing on the growth of a child’s self-esteem, this preschool curriculum will stimulate your child’s innate curiosity.

Admission Policy: We do not discriminate on the basis of race, color, religion, national or ethnic origin. You do not have to have any religious affiliation in order for your child to attend Angels Unlimited Preschool.

Class Activities: Encourage development of abilities in the areas of language, math skills, reading skills and scientific discovery. Enhance social skills through group activities and sharing experiences. Promote a positive self image that encourages children to ask questions and make positive choices. Improve gross motor development through various physical activities. Develop fine motor skills through arts and crafts and manipulative toys.
