name: Children's Workshop
details:
Children have repeated this phrase again and again, throughout time, all over the world. Dr. Maria Montessori believed that education should be an “aid to life” – the transformation of the total personality. Therefore, the Montessori approach is more than a teaching method, it is also a philosophy of life–a vision of humanity–that emerged from Dr. Montessori’s discovery of the child.

Since 1987, the aim of Children’s Workshop Montessori has been to develop within the child a global vision, a life-long love of learning and a sense of responsibility toward humanity. All aspects of the Montessori experience come together to foster the development of integrated, committed, respectful, loving and caring human beings.

name: Little Lakers Montessori Preschool and Child Care, Inc.
Servant Schoolhouse Christian Preschool
details:
Servant Schoolhouse Preschool is a Christian ministry for our congregation and an outreach to the surrounding community.  Our school provides Early Childhood education to young children in a Christ-filled atmosphere where they can rejoice and grow in God’s grace.


Our developmentally appropriate curriculum is based on the Word of God.  Daily curriculum is designed through a multitude of activities based on play that fosters creative expression and world discovery.  We work to develop important pre-reading skills such as phonics, sequencing, and number and letter recognition.  Our program emphasizes self-help skills and problem solving techniques as well as developing friendships and positive social skills. Throughout each preschool day the children are encouraged to grow closer to Jesus and learn more about Christian life.  The educational curriculum enhances the child spiritually, emotionally, cognitively, physically and socially.

name: Mahube Community Council, Head Start Campus Child Care
WCCA Head Start-Clearwater
details:
The Wright County Community Action (WCCA) Head Start Program provides your 3-5 year old child with a head start. Community based child and family development programming through the Head Start program is available to eligible households throughout Wright and Western Hennepin County.

WCCA Head Start services promote cognitive, social, and emotional growth and development of 3-5 year old children from income eligible families and for age eligible children with special needs. Activities centered around health, education, nutrition and socialization are focused on children’s growth and development in language, literacy, math, science social functioning, creative arts, physical skills, overall learning abilities and more. Parent involvement and participation is a key element to each child’s success and actively promoted in Head Start.

WCCA provides Head Start programming at centers and through a Home/Parent based model. Daily schedules at centers vary by location and include 4 hour, 6 hour and extended day.

name: Happy Hearts Child Care and Development Center
Teddy Bear Care of Isanti, Inc.
details: At Teddy Bear Care, Inc. our mission is to provide the best child care service possible at a reasonable price. We are dedicated to exeptional quality childcare thats also flexible and convenient to serving the community.

name: Kids at First
details:
Mission Statement
The congregation of First English Lutheran Church joins with families to fulfill the promises made at Baptism to our children. Providing a nurturing, Christian preschool program in which young children can grow in body, mind, and spirit.

name: Kiddie Kampus Preschool
details:
Kiddie Kampus Preschool, a ministry of Zion Lutheran Church, provides a warm and stimulating environment where children can come to explore and discover the world in which they live. We exist to teach children to gain confidence in their skills as learners, adapt to group experiences, and to respect others.

We believe that young children learn best through hands-on experiences which provides a strong foundation in their ability to learn new things.

name: Bigelow Head Start
details:
Head Start and Early Head Start are comprehensive child development, health and social service programs for low-income families.  Since 1965, Head Start has been serving the needs of disadvantaged infants, children, and pregnant women across America.

Over 1400 children, from prenatal through age 5, are enrolled in Community Action’s programs each year throughout Ramsey County.  Options include full-day, half-day, therapeutic, and inclusion classrooms, and home-visiting programs.  Families who meet our eligibility requirements and families with children with special needs are encouraged to apply.

    The prenatal to age 3 program, Early Head Start, offers a home-based design for families. Early Head Start Home Visitors meet regularly with parents and children to nurture child development and parenting skills. Families who qualify for childcare assistance may also choose full-day, center-based enhanced childcare for children ages six weeks to five years.
    Head Start children between the ages of 3 to 5 attend center-based programming. Classes are offered in either half-day or full-day options at centers conveniently located throughout Ramsey County. Eight centers operate half-day classes, 4 days a week from September through late May. A full-day, full-year option is also available at the Bigelow Head Start Center, or through partnership contracts with community childcare facilities.

name: Town Square Head Start
details:
Head Start is a comprehensive preschool program focusing on child development and serving 3- and 4-year-old children and their families. Head Start establishes relationships that promote growth and development in young children and encourages the self-sufficiency of families.

The program is family-centered, strength-based and designed to foster the parent's role as the principle influence on their child's development and to assist families in developing and achieving self-reliance.

name: Agape Child Development Center
details:
AGAPE Child Development Center is located on site at school and provides safe and loving care with staffing from the YMCA.  We care for for infants six weeks old through 33 months exclusively for student parents enrolled at Agape.   The classrooms for childcare incorporate stimulating toys and activities appropriate for different ages.  All children have access to both indoor and outdoor playground equipment.  

We work with teen parents to obtain their childcare funding through Ramsey County's Minnesota Family Investment Program (MFIP) or Resources forChild Caring's Basic Sliding Fee program to pay for the costs ofchildcare.  The school and Childcare Center have many resources for teen parents.  We help students get connected with parent support groups, resources in the community and social work services available during the school day.  The Childcare Center is open from 9 am until 4:00 pm.

name: Semcac Head Start-Kasson
details: We are committed to building bright futures by enriching young   children, ages Birth – 5 years old, and empowering their families. Comprehensive services and community opportunities support healthy families.

name: Prior Lake Montessori School
details:
Since 1984, the Prior Lake Montessori School has helped children reach their full potential. Our mission is to provide excellence in education in a motivating environment. 

At Prior Lake Montessori, our Preschool and Kindergarten programs are ​specifically designed to meet the unique needs of children at each stage in their development. The school curriculum introduces children to the joy of learning at their own pace and provides a framework in which intellectual and social discipline go hand in hand. 

We believe in a well-rounded program for your child. Children need opportunities to learn as well as to play games, be social, engage in make-believe, joke with friends, explore nature, sing, dance, draw, build, and just daydream.

​​As the first Montessori school in Prior Lake, we bring 27 years of academic experience. We believe that Montessori education is not simply a system of teaching, but a method of helping children develop their personality and understand the world.

name: Elbow Lake Head Start-West Central Area North School
Martin Luther College Early Childhood Learning Center
details:
Welcome to the Martin Luther College Early Childhood Learning Center!  We are a non-profit, state licensed, college-run early childhood program for ages 6 weeks-5 years.   We have been serving families in the New Ulm area for the past 13 years.

Our overall goal is to provide early learning experiences that assist parents in nurturing the spiritual, physical, intellectual, emotional, and social development of their young children.  We believe this goal can be reached through hands-on, active experiences that are developmentally appropriate for young children. We further believe children develop best when all experiences occur in an atmosphere of Christian love and respect.

In October 2013 we moved into a new Center that will includes two preschool classrooms, an infant and toddler room, art studio, movement room, and college classroom.   Our programs are currently full but please call or e-mail for future enrollment information.

name: Apple Lane Community Child Care Center
details: Apple Lane opened its doors in June, 1986, known as Apple Lane Child Care of St. Edward's. It started with 14 children and two classrooms. It was operated by four employees from the former Children's House which closed in the spring of 1986. The Montessori preschool and the Early preschool room were the two programs that started Apple Lane. The four co-directors were responsible for the decision making and planning of the program. Rent was paid to St. Edward's Catholic Church for the use of their facilities. The Church provided the child care center with insurance and did the building maintenance. Through the years the center grew to a licensed capacity of 60 children, 12 staff, and five classrooms. In the spring, 1997, the St. Edward's Church Board of Directors decided that it was not a priority for the Church to "be in the day care business" and negotiations ensued with the staff at Apple Lane. After negotiations, it was a very resound group decision among the staff and directors at the time that the child care operations remain open to continue to provide care for the 109 children served on a part-time, limited drop-in, summer care, and full-time basis from 97 families who attended Apple Lane of St. Edward's. The newly formed non-profit agency, Apple Lane Community Child Care Center, was created on October 29, 1997. In January 2006, Apple Lane expanded opened a second location at Riverland College. This site offers child care services to 52 children ages 6 weeks through age 5. This decision was made based on the need for toddler and infant care as well as the prevelant waiting list for preschool age children. Apple Lane made this transition when Austin Public Schools Kids Korner child care program made the decision to close its doors.

name: St. Mary's School
details: St. Mary's is an accredited school with a strong emphasis on helping each child grow to their full potential, but God is at the center of our academic curriculum building.  We expand our Religion curriculum by offering daily religion classes, morning prayer, service projects, character training, and weekly Mass.

name: Wholechild, Inc
details: Our center is located at 1901 Ford Parkway in Saint Paul. Our split entry space includes 4 self-contained classrooms and a large motor room on the upper level; and a self contained classroom, a double inner connected self-contained classroom, and a large community room on the lower level. Additionally we have four separate enclosed outdoor play areas for each age level. The school age structure was new in 2009, the PreK structure was rebuilt in 2009, the 3 year old structure was new in 2008 and the toddler play area and equipment was also new in 2010. We have a security code keyless entry system that is tied into our phones so that staff and our families are the only ones with access. This also means that no staff has to leave an area to answer the door.

name: Semcac Head Start-Winona
details: We are committed to building bright futures by enriching young   children, ages Birth – 5 years old, and empowering their families. Comprehensive services and community opportunities support healthy families.

name: Prairie Land Daycare/Headstart
details:
MISSION STATEMENT
Our mission is to strive together to foster strong healthy children and their families and to promote staff excellence through dynamic programming.

name: Sonshine Christian Preschool
details: Sonshine Christian Preschool believes each child is to be accepted as an individual child of God. Each child has unique qualities and abilities that make them special. The sharing of Christian beliefs and values will be integrated in a natural way, into every facet of the preschool. We will provide a safe, nurturing environment, fostered and supported as part of the mission and ministry of Holy Trinity Lutheran Church.

name: Blue Earth Head Start
details: Head Start is a child development program that serves eligible children and families. Head Start programs promote school readiness by providing educational, health, nutritional, social and other services to enrolled children and families. At Head Start, children learn to accept themselves, explore their world, and learn individually and as part of a group. Head Start responds to and supports each child's unique needs. All services provided by Head Start are of no cost to families.

name: Little Saints Preschool
details: Little Saints Preschool (LSP) is a non-profit cooperative preschool. It has been in existence since 1956, when it was organized by a group of mothers who wanted to provide preschool social and educational experiences for their children.  The group met in the basement of family homes. Over the years the name and location had been changed, but the main educational goals remained the same. In the 1980′s the group was renamed the Central Community Preschool but soon would be changed to Little Saints Preschool. The preschool is currently located in the Church of St. Peter, but is not affiliated with the Church. LSP is licensed by the State of Minnesota and meets all state requirements for preschools.

It is our philosophy to first develop partnerships with families and trusting relationships between teachers, children, and parents. Little Angel Pre-School

East Creek Child Care helps children learn and develop by providing opportunities for individualized concrete, experiential learning to encourage the formation of a love-to-learn attitude. The mission is to provide the best care possible and to support parents.
Highly trained and experienced staff members use Creative Curriculum to plan for and support each child's early learning. The program is small and unique. The philosophy is to foster high quality experiences for children, parents, and staff while we connect and interact as a team.

name: Educare Kids Montessori & Child Care LLC
details: Our mission is to equip our children with the necessary tools to promote positive early childhood development. Educare aims to combine the concepts of hands on learning with support of trained personnel within a safe and educationally nurturing environment.

In 2011 Little Treasures partnered with Ecumen Lakeshore to consolidate services and create an innovative intergenerational care community. Little Treasures became a program of the Duluth YMCA.  Building strong kids, families and community is at the heart of our services.

name: Northside Child Development Center
details:
Catholic Charities’ Northside Child Development Center is a North Minneapolis learning center for children six-weeks to 12-years-old. Northside Child Development Center provides early education, preschool, school readiness and school reinforcement experiences, all designed to combat the negative impact poverty can have on children.

To strengthen the family, Northside Child Development Center provides family-focused events, parent education, parent support groups and extensive family visiting. Individual family service plans are developed during home visits to identify and respond to barriers that may interfere with parents’ efforts to work and care for their children.
business hours: 6:30 a.m. to 5:30 p.m. Monday through Friday.

name: Little Beginnings Learning Center
details: We know that making child care and preschool decisions can be a very difficult and emotional process. We would LOVE to help! We pride ourselves as a child care center that strives to offer lots of love, a safe environment, and developmental appropriate experiences. Communication is of utmost importance, as well as a place where all children and their families are treated with respect. We hope that after visiting our site that you will see that Little Beginnings would be a great choice for your family and your child!

name: Alphabet Junction Child Care Center
details:
Thank you for your interest in Alphabet Junction Learning Center! Choosing a child care provider is one of the most important decisions you will make for your child. The first few years of a child’s life are the most formative and it is vital that you choose a provider that will meet and exceed your expectations. We truly cherish each and every child in our programs.

We have been in business since 1999 and currently operate centers in Chaska, Victoria, Shakopee, Jordan and Waconia. At Alphabet Junction Childcare Centers, we pride ourselves in providing children with an educational, nurturing, safe and clean learning environment. Our certified teachers and staff are energetic, caring and patient individuals who are committed to teaching your child the necessary tools to promote strong self-esteem and life-long learning. Many of our teachers have been teaching with us since we originally opened our doors!

Our unique curriculum and structured programs are designed to help your child reach his or her optimal potential. We view each day as new and exciting. The activities in our creative daily curriculum reflect this and allow your child to grow and learn in positive ways each day. In addition to our enriching educational curriculum, we offer our students Music Classes, Spanish Class and Baby Sign Language!

name: Kindernook Preschool, Inc.
details: The mission of Kindernook Preschool is to prepare students to be confident learners and caring individuals in a Christian environment.  It is our intent to ensure each child has a successful preschool experience with lots of fun, laughter, and joy.

name: All God's Children Preschool
details:
A fully licensed Christian preschool that began in September of 1999. It is a ministry of
St. Paul Lutheran Church in Wyoming, MN which provides quality education for children
ages 3-5.

name: Family Learning Child Care at Lehmann
details: The Child Care Center at Lehman College is committed to providing the children and families of the College's student body with the highest quality early child care programs and support possible. The Child Care Center's philosophy is to provide an environment where a child’s growth is supported and stimulated in all areas of development. Our program is rich with experiences in art, music, movement, science, language arts, and math, with plenty of room for nurturing individual interests. The teachers feel it’s important for the children to build their understandings through their own individual experiences, thus enabling them to think for themselves and question thoughtfully. In this way, the children know they are competent to learn, to grow, and to trust themselves as well as others.

name: Precious Corner Preschool
details:
Children are a gift, and at Precious Corner Preschool your child will be lovingly led on a journey of growth—socially, emotionally, intellectually, physically, and spiritually. We provide a safe, Christian environment where every child is able to celebrate who they are, explore the world around them, and learn about Jesus.

Every day children will have opportunities to interact with peers and teachers in small group settings. These times allow children to plan their day, build relationships, strengthen skills, and participate in special projects. Children also meet in a larger group setting for devotions, snack, outdoor play, and celebrations. Details of daily activities and groupings are available from each classroom.

name: St.Elizabeth Ann Seton Preschool
details: St. Elizabeth Ann Seton School (SEAS) makes Jesus Christ known and loved through living our sacramental way of life in partnership with families and fostered in: Spirituality, Excellence, Academics and Service.

name: Kids Country Day Care and Learning Center
details: Kids Country Child Care and Learning Center is a value-guided center that realizes every child is special and has unique learning needs.We enroll children ages 6 weeks through 11 years old, while catering to the individual needs of each different age group by providing separate classrooms, playgrounds and programming. Kids Country enriches children's lives by providing high quality child care. Our nurturing staff provides a foundation for children to accelerate while building self-esteem, independence, and respect in a safe, dependable environment. Kids Country strives to enhance children's intellectual, physical, social, and emotional development through a variety of activities developed and designed around the needs of each individual child.

name: Little Lamb's Christian Daycare and Preschool
details:
Welcome to Little Lambs Christian Learning Center

…a place where caring and learning are inseparable. We believe it is a privilege to serve Christ and families. We chose to do that in a caring and loving manner, nurturing each child that enters our doors with integrity and distinction.

Our program provides a variety of age appropriate cognitive and physical development for infants, toddlers and preschoolers.

Little Lambs is licensed though the Department of Human Services to provide care for children ages Infant (6 weeks) – Preschool (5years).

name: INSTEP A Center for Families
details:
INSTEP is a one-of-a kind childcare center that provides high quality part-time care focused on early childhood education and school readiness for children that fall through the cracks of traditional childcare assistance. For parents, it provides family support advocacy and parent group learning sessions.

INSTEP is a licensed, part-time childcare program serving children and families who fall through the cracks of traditional government programs. INSTEP makes care accessible to families who do not qualify for subsidy, are seeking or waiting for permanent childcare, or cannot afford or require traditional full-time models. For many children, INSTEP is the only formalized education they will receive before entering kindergarten. Our curriculum is based on Creative Curriculum, which has been shown to promote the cognitive, language, social/ emotional, and physical development of young children. We know that an investment in early childhood education is a good investment. According to economist Art Rolnick of the Federal Reserve Bank of Minneapolis, a $1 invested in early education and childcare brings a $12 to $16 return to the community.

name: Three Rivers Head Start
details:
Head Start is a comprehensive preschool program focusing on child development and serving 3- and 4-year-old children and their families. Head Start establishes relationships that promote growth and development in young children and encourages the self-sufficiency of families.

The program is family-centered, strength-based and designed to foster the parent's role as the principle influence on their child's development and to assist families in developing and achieving self-reliance.

name: Appleseed Montessori School & Child Care Center, Inc.
Praise the Children
details:
​Praise The Children's mission is to be an extension of your family in the important task of teaching young children cooperation, deveoloping good moral habit, conveying a sense of responsibility, and instilling a love of learning.

﻿Where young minds can bloom through education and faith!

name: Kids' Care Connection
details:
Established in 2000, Bloom Early Learning & Child Care (formerly Kids’ Care Connection) is an accredited, award-winning, non-profit early learning center with a special mission to make the highest quality childcare, programs and curriculum (and fun!) accessible to the entire community.

AboutBloom
    Serving children from 6 weeks to age 5 and their families.
    Nurturing, safe, friendly and family-like environment.
    Delicious and nutritional food program.
    Well-educated, dedicated staff with a passion for children and teaching.
    Values-based programs and excellent curriculum with stellar learning and social outcomes that exceed state standards.
    Committed to community through scholarship and financial aid.
    Accredited by NAEYC Academy for Early Childhood Program Accreditation and 4-Star Parent Aware rated.

Most parents must rely on childcare on a daily basis, and leaving your child with someone else is a necessary but often difficult decision.  For many single parents and low-income families meeting the cost of trustworthy childcare is simply impossible. These children are at risk of entering school unprepared to succeed.

Bloom consists of a unique blend of private-pay and scholarship families. This arrangement fosters a diverse mix of kids and an opportunity to strengthen our community as a whole.
community-funded scholarship program 50% of enrollment spots dedicated to families needing financial assistance.

Since 2000, Bloom has provided care and learning for over 300 children. More than 150 of those children received financial assistance, totaling over $1 million in scholarships.

Bloom is non-profit, a 501(c)3 organization, and is partially supported by individuals, businesses, and other organizations through gifts for our scholarships and with volunteer work. We also partner with Interfaith Outreach Community Partners (IOCP), Caring for Kids Initiative (CfKI), the Wayzata School District and government agencies to help empower families who are struggling financially and help them achieve self-reliance and independence.

name: Central Cass Head Start Family Resource Center
Monarch Montessori School
details: Our mission at Monarch Montessori School is to create an environment that inspires children to develop inner discipline, self-assurance, and a love of learning.  We respect the uniqueness of each child by helping them develop skills at periods of greatest readiness and sensitivity.

name: Helen H. Taylor Early Childhood Education Center
details:
Children enter the world ready to learn. PICA’s Head Start and Early Head Start programs help children build on this natural ability. PICA respects each child’s individuality and honors his/her cultural, ethnic, and family heritage. Our child-centered curriculum, the New World Curriculum, focuses on the interests, learning styles, and developmental needs of the individual child and helps each child develop self-esteem, self-help skills, and socialization skills.

Parent involvement is the most important part of Head Start and Early Head Start. At PICA, parents have decision-making power and are involved in all parts of the program.

name: Heights Head Start Center
details:
Head Start is a multi-faceted child and family development program for income-eligible households in Anoka and Washington Counties in Minnesota. The program is designed to help pregnant women and children, aged birth to five, and their families achieve their full potential.

The Head Start program literally gives children a head start on their journey of lifelong learning. The program also gives parents a head start in maintaining family continuity and self-sufficiency.

name: BBE Jaguar Kid Connection Childcare Program
Bassett Creek Montessori and Daycare Center
Zakia, Inc.dba Pumpkin Patch Daycare and Learning Center, Inc.
details:
At Pumpkin Patch Childcare & Learning Center, we work each day with the shared purpose of keeping the joy of childhood alive through high quality care and education that allow for whole child development in a loving, safe, and enriching environment.

We achieve this purpose by:
•Acting as an extended family by providing support and education to our families.
•Developing and maintaining strong relationships with our families and their children.
•Supporting each child’s development and growth with knowledgeable educators and care providers who are passionate about child development, education, and play.
•Providing exciting learning and play opportunities that allow children to develop socially, emotionally, physically, and intellectually while learning about the world around them.
•Helping children develop positive values including good manners, compassion, kindness, honesty, and respect.
•Providing a community that nourishes creativity, friendships, diversity, sense of self, and a love of learning.
business hours:
Monday through Friday
6:00 a.m. to 6:30 p.m.

name: Early Advantage Developmental Child Care Center LLC
details: Early Advantage Developmental Child Care Center offers a safe, nurturing, developmentally appropriate environment for children 6 weeks to 12 years of age.  Our mission is to partner with you in the care and development of your child.  We recognize that each child has unique talents, learning styles and personalities.  That is why we are committed to working within each child’s comfort zone to ensure optimal social,emotional and educational results.

name: Children First Christian Preschool
details:
Children First Christian Preschool provides a variety of developmentally appropriate activities, through individual and group experiences, which encourages each child to discover who they are and develop a positive self-image. We recognize that children learn by discovery through active engagement.
We believe play has intent and purpose.

name: Southside Head Start A and B/Southside Early Head Start
Our Savior's New Horizons Christian Pre-school
details: New Horizons Christian Preschool was awarded a 4-star rating in July 2014.  This rating indicates  our program is using the best possible practices to prepare children for Kindergarten, as determined by the MN Department of Human Services; Parent Aware. Please click on the link below to read more about Parent Aware, New Horizons rating and information on how you can apply for state funded scholarships to pay for your child's preschool education.

name: Baby Zone, Inc.
details:
Established in 2001 by Owner/Director Mary Jo Cocchiarella, Baby Zone is a family owned childcare facility located in Maplewood, Minnesota.  Mary Jo has worked for over 20 years in the childcare field as a nanny, preschool teacher, and clinical nurse, in addition to being a loving mother and grandmother.

Originally situated at Highway 36 and English Street, Baby Zone relocated to its brand new facility next door to the Maplewood Community Center on White Bear Avenue in 2014. Baby Zone is camera secured with an advanced card reader entry system to ensure the highest level of security.

Children are cared for in a clean, spacious facility with separate areas dedicated to cognitive skills, arts, story time, music, and focused learning time. Infant sign language and Spanish are also included as part of the curriculum. Supervised outdoor play is emphasized when weather permits and Baby Zone has two fenced in play areas outside with many activities and toys.

name: Urban Arts Academy
details:
The Vision of  Urban Arts Academy is to develop successful artists in our neighborhoods.

The mission of Urban Arts Academy is to bring together neighborhood people  from diverse cultures by providing creative experiences in the arts with children and families to develop the gifts of self-expression and community.

Our purpose: Urban Arts Academy is a place that strives for education equity through the arts and the modeling of social, economic and racial justice.

name: Kingdom Kids
details:
Kingdom Kids Christian Preschool is licensed by the Minnesota Department of Human Services and is accredited by the Association of Christian Schools International (ACSI). ACSI is one of the nation’s largest and most stringent accrediting agencies.
We partner with your family to educate, nurture, and encourage the development of the whole child. Every child is made in God’s image and has incredible intrinsic value. Our goal is to build a strong foundation in God’s word from which your child will benefit for life. Students are prepared for Kindergarten through our academic, developmentally appropriate curriculum.

name: Noah's Ark Child Care
details: Noah's Ark Child Care Center offers Infant, Toddler, Preschool, and School Age child care.

name: 3R's Early Childhood Learning Center Inc
details: 3Rs Mission Statement:  To provide child care in a safe, comfortable and clean environment with an educational program that relates to the traditional Three Rs.

name: Central Lutheran Church Child Care Center
details:
Our Mission
Providing the building blocks of child care by creating learning opportunities infused with faith while supporting the whole family.

 Our Philosophy
To provide a Christ-centered learning environment where Christ’s abundant love and teaching is reflected through our staff in their loving care, guidance, and teaching of all children.

name: Seeds of Faith Preschool, a Ministry of St. Luke's
Oakdale Head Start
details:
Head Start is a multi-faceted child and family development program for income-eligible households in Anoka and Washington Counties in Minnesota. The program is designed to help pregnant women and children, aged birth to five, and their families achieve their full potential.

The Head Start program literally gives children a head start on their journey of lifelong learning. The program also gives parents a head start in maintaining family continuity and self-sufficiency.

name: Western Community Action, Inc.-Tracy Head Start
Portland Village Early Childhood Family Development Center
details:
Children enter the world ready to learn. PICA’s Head Start and Early Head Start programs help children build on this natural ability. PICA respects each child’s individuality and honors his/her cultural, ethnic, and family heritage. Our child-centered curriculum, the New World Curriculum, focuses on the interests, learning styles, and developmental needs of the individual child and helps each child develop self-esteem, self-help skills, and socialization skills.

Parent involvement is the most important part of Head Start and Early Head Start. At PICA, parents have decision-making power and are involved in all parts of the program.

name: Learning Tree Development Center
details:
Learning Tree Development Center is licensed through the State of Minnesota to provide care for children ages 6 weeks - 12 years.

 The center provides full time, full day and hourly care. Priority is given first to students of Normandale, then to faculty and staff, and finally the community. You do not have to be a student of Normandale to use our services.

 Learning Tree provides a structured program within a play-based setting designed to meet the children's developmental needs. Children express their ideas and feelings through a well-rounded, developmentally appropriate curriculum which includes activities in art, music, language, math, science, writing, large motor, etc... A balance of active, quiet, individual and group activities assist the child's social, emotional, physical and cognitive development.

 The center is staff by teachers who meet or exceed Minnesota Department of Licensing standards, Work Study students, and Parent Volunteers.

name: Bright Beginnings Learning Center
details: Bright Beginnings Learning Center is a privately owned child care center and our mission is to foster your child's development in such a way as to ensure a sense of 'trust' and 'love of learning'.  Our mission is to foster your child's development in such a way as to ensure a sense of 'trust' and 'love of learning'. Providing quality pre-school education in a loving environment, which encompasses various teaching styles, enabling each child to experience the unique talents and gifts of our staff.

name: Seeds to Seedlings Child Development Center
St Pius X Preschool
details:
At Rochester Catholic Schools, students celebrate their Catholic faith as an integral part of their school experience. You can trust that your child will receive a values-based education, where they will flourish academically and spiritually. We believe that your child’s first school experience should be one of discovery and adventure, building confidence that helps students grow to love learning.

Much more than day care, Rochester Catholic Schools Preschool is a premier childcare program that builds active minds, healthy bodies, and happy hearts for children of all faiths. RCS Preschool is licensed and staffed with dedicated teachers who create a safe and respectful learning environment filled with creative play and age appropriate learning opportunities.

name: Orono Discovery Center-ISD #278
details: At Orono Discovery Kids Childcare we provide children with a nurturing atmosphere that promotes self-esteem and encourages social interactions based on respect and kindness.

name: Minnesota Chinese Day Care Center
details:
MCDCLC is committed to provide a loving, safe, positive, supportive and cultural diverse environment where children can play, learn and grow.

We offer immersion Mandarin Chinese program and teach math, arts, dance, music and provide wide variety of activities to stimulate children to develop physically, mentally, socially and academically. We serve 3 locations – Roseville, St. Paul and Northeast Minneapolis with enrollment of children from all over Twin City area of Minnesota.

Head Start is a multi-faceted child and family development program for income-eligible households in Anoka and Washington Counties in Minnesota. The program is designed to help pregnant women and children, aged birth to five, and their families achieve their full potential.

name: St. Bernard Catholic School Preschool Program
Sunshine Station Childcare and Preschool
details: We are a childcare center located in Rockford, Minnesota.

name: YWCA Early Childhood Center-Spirit Valley Site
details: The YWCA’s early childhood education center uses an early literacy and developmentally appropriate curriculum to ready children for school. In 2012 there were 85 children and their families that were served through the YWCA’s early childhood education center. The YWCA has partnered with Head Start since 2005, offering Head Start and Early Head Start services that monitor health, growth, learning and developmental milestones to income eligible families. The YWCA also collaborates with Early Childhood Family Education to provide support to parents with children in the YWCA Center. In the fall of 2011 we started a new project called Circles of Security with parents and caregivers at our Center. Focused on attachment theory and research, it works with the parents and child-care staff to give them new skills and tools to provide quality care and parenting. Successful attachment is the basis of future emotional and mental health in children and affects every aspect of their lives including the ability to learn. We are very excited about this project and are repeating it in 2012-13.

name: Kumi's House of Children
details: The basic idea in the Montessori philosophy is that children carry within themselves the person that they will become. Dr. Maria Montessori developed what she called a "prepared environment" which already possesses a certain order. This environment alows children to learn at their own speed, according to their own capacities, and in a  non-competative atmosphere. Montessori teaches children to observe, to think, and to judge. It introduces children to the joy of learning at an early age and provides a framework in which intellectual and social discipline go hand in hand.

name: Zion Lutheran Preschool
details: At Kids in Christ Preschool, our mission is to share God’s grace by providing early childhood training in an enriching, Christ-centered atmosphere. Zion Lutheran strives to provide a safe and loving atmosphere where each child is nurtured and taught to rejoice and grow in God’s grace while preparing them for kindergarten.
business hours: Monday & Fridays 8:45-11:15 and all day Wednesdays 8:45 – 2:45

name: Little People Learning Center
details:
Mission Statement:
To provide the working parents of our community a superior childcare program that will enhance their child's social, emotional and intellectual development in a safe, clean environment and with a highly qualified and caring staff.

name: Montessori School of Melrose
details: The Associated Montessori Schools specialize in Montessori Education for children from 3 to 6 years of age, including both pre-school and kindergarten. Children must be completely Toilet Trained, able to go on their own without assistance. Our education, experience, dedication, and commitment to the teachings of Dr. Maria Montessori enable us to provide schools ideally suited to young children. At the Associated Montessori Schools, we emphasize love of learning, concentration, self-esteem, respect for others, self-direction, and basic skills in a Christian atmosphere. We incorporate music, art, movement, practical life, sensorial development, language, mathematics, geography, science, and social studies. The children choose eagerly from this broad scope of activities.

name: Learn and Grow Child Care Center South, Inc.
Our Redeemer's Little Lambs Preschool
details:
Our Mission
Our Redeemer Little Lambs Preschool provides an early childhood education with a Christian foundation in a safe, nurturing Lutheran environment that offers developmentally appropriate experiences for preschool families in our church and community.

name: St. John's Roots to Wings Learning Center
Hallelujah Childcare Center
details: Our childcare center is state licensed and staffed with highly qualified teachers. We provide a nurturing and safe Christ-centered environment for your child.

name: Peppermint Fence Preschool
details:
Peppermint Fence is a Wayzata Public Schools' preschool that provides for the academic, social, emotional, and physical development of children ages 2 - 5 years. Peppermint Fence is licensed by the Minnesota Department of Human Services (DHS), accredited through the National Association for the Education of Young Children (NAEYC), and has earned the highest rating possible from Parent Aware (ages 3-5) (see video below).

We offer part-time classes mornings and afternoons from September through June. These classes are intended for children who will be enrolled for the full school year. If you are not able to commit to the full 34 weeks, please choose a session of Block Time.

name: Grace Garden Childcare
details:
Grace Garden is a Christian childcare affiliated with Grace Lutheran Church, and we serve children 6 weeks till 5 years old (until they go to kindergarten). We also have a school age program during the summer for children going to kindergarten through age 12.

Our mission is to assist families in our congregation and community to care for and educate their young children in the context of a “faith-based, value-driven ministry which answers both our Lord’s call to serve and our community’s need for…social, moral and spiritual formation of its children.”

name: Kids Count Daycare and Learning Center, Inc.
Lit'l Sprouts Child Care Center Inc.
details: Childcare with a purpose! Quality childcare services and programs which provide a safe and secure environment to allow each child to "blossom" and develop as a whole person; physically, emotionally, intellectually and socially, helping children prepare for their early years of schooling and beyond under the careful guidance of excellent childcare practitioners. Our program is unique. Lit'l Sprouts strives to give your child the best opportunities in learning. We strive to meet the core competencies standards for Early Childhood Education set forth by the Minnesota Association for Education of Young Children (MnAEYC). These standards are designed as a framework for understanding and learning for young children. Throughout the day, children are taught and are able to participate in fun "hands-on" activities and learning games, which shape, but are not limited to their intellectual, physical, social, or emotional development on a daily basis. From Infant to School Age, our staff has age-appropriate weekly lesson plans designed to be within the abilities of the child, yet challenge's their creative talents and imagination. Individuality is encouraged, as our goal is to help children within this diverse community understand and develop as well-rounded individuals. Our curriculum we use is Creative Curriculum. This curriculum allows for teachers to assess children's progress, individualize or adapt learning when necessary, and is used as a guide for our teachers' development and implementation of learning opportunities which are consistent with the program's goals and objectives. Curriculum is implemented in a manner that is reflective to the responsiveness of each family home values, beliefs, and experiences and language. Our day is fairly structured in nature. This is to help prepare and give children the school readiness skills they will need for the early years of schooling. Variances can arise occasionally to accommodate the changing needs and interests of the class and will be noted on lesson plans. A weekly lesson plan will be posted in each classroom, and is in your child's daily file so you and your child can engage in conversation about their day and most importantly skills learned!

name: Mrs. Lali's Little Friends Montessori LLC
YWCA Children's Center at Abbott Northwestern Hospital
details: The YWCA Children’s Center at Abbott Northwestern Hospital is located inside the hospital campus. In addition to our traditional center, the Abbott Northwestern location is home to the Somali and Spanish Child Care Bungalows, where children of various ages are taught in Spanish or Somali language immersion bungalows. Neighborhood residents work in the bungalows, learning the business of child care. When participants complete the program, they are ready to open high-quality, licensed home daycare centers to support themselves and their communities.

name: Community of Hope Preschool
details: Community of Hope Preschool seeks to nurture the spiritual, emotional, cognitive, social and physical growth of young children. Our program is a Christian education program and is provided in a safe and loving environment

Westview Head Start

Westview has enjoyed a long tradition of academic excellence. We strive to grow and

Twenty book-loving 3rd, 4th and 5th grade readers earned the priviledge of attending our 6th annual Maud Hart Lovelace Overnight. Twleve book nominees for the MN Youth Reading Award make for twelve fun and creative activities. Congratulations!

Children have opportunities to make new friends, explore, play outdoors, build, paint and do what they do best…play! Our Mission is to give each child a warm environment that encourages the development of socialization skills, independence, and a positive self-image.

details: Welcome to the Faith Works Preschool & Childcare. A t Faith Works we work hard to help children develop positive attitudes toward themselves and others. We believe that children’ who gain a sense of security, self-worth and personal accomplishment when they are young, are much more likely to be successful learners and happy people throughout their lives.

name: Child Development Center at Blue Cross and Blue Shield of MN
details:
Bright Horizons is the world's leading provider of employer-sponsored child care, back-up care, education and work/life solutions with more than 700 child care and early education programs and schools for employers and working families across the US, UK, Ireland and Canada. Committed to creating great work environments for its 18,000 employees, the company has been named 12 times as one of FORTUNE magazine's "Best Companies to Work for in America."

Bright Horizons provides work/life solutions for more than 800 leading employers to help them address challenges across key life stages. Programs include child care, back-up care, college counseling, elder care, and work/life consulting.

The first few years of life are an extraordinary time that sets the stage for all the years that follow. Our program for learning creates educational environments that empower children to be confident, successful, lifelong learners and socially responsible citizens. Bright Horizons' innovative programs help children, families, and employers work together to be their very best.

name: Grow With Us Day Care Center
details: At Grow With Us Childcare Center, we strongly believe in quality care. Children need to believe in themselves and know how special they are. We believe every child can learn through play as long as they have good role models. Children are unique individuals, we just need to guide and direct them through physical, social, intellectual and emotional developments. Children will learn by having fun.

details: In business since 2000, All Aboard Child Care & Preschool is a trusted child care center in the Marshall, MN area. Our special services include motor sensory development and individualized assessment. Your child can enjoy various activities, games, arts and crafts, field trips, and more!

name: Jesus' Lambs at Peace Preschool
details: Jesus’ Lambs at Peace wishes to provide the continued warmth and security your child receives at home as well as a creative hands-on learning experience of God’s wonderful world.  Come join us for stories, songs, letters, numbers, art, cooking, field trips, science, and play.

name: Little Huskies Day Center & Preschool & Paws' School Age Program
Sonnet Montessori, Inc.
details:
At Sonnet Montessori we are dedicated to the Montessori philosophy, the care and the education of children. Individual growth and independence are fostered. The teaching staff provide personal attention, helping each child to progress at his/her own rate.

Sonnet began in Prior Lake in 2006 with the mission of educating children through the Montessori philosophy and providing a safe and nurturing environment.  Most of our students come through referrals by Sonnet alumni or current families who have been delighted with the academic level their children achieve when they graduate from Sonnet.  From our beginning we worked closely with the local schools, principals and superintendents to prepare our children for a smooth transition into public and parochial environments beyond Kindergarten.

While at Sonnet, the children learn to respect each other, their environment and begin to understand the importance of peace. Below are our goals and how we strive to achieve them.

name: Kidz Place
details:
Kidz Place is committed to excellence in early childhood education! We understand that each child is special and unique so we design our programs with your child’s needs in mind!

Did you know that the early years of a child’s life lay the foundation for future learning? Research shows that the human brain develops the majority of its neurons, and is at its most receptive to learning, between birth and three years of age (Shonkoff & Phillips, 2000).  That’s why we strive to partner with you to provide quality care during your child’s formative years. We know you have high expectations- and so do we!

name: Baby's Space/Tatanka Academy
details: Baby’s Space is created from the baby’s point of view – in which responsive, consistent, sensitive, and warm relationships with adults are necessary for the child to succeed. Our neighborhood-based setting supports the development of the whole child and her family. We feature research-based best practices, proven birth through 3rd grade educational models, holistic care including early childhood and elementary education, parenting support, and a trauma-informed mental health approach with culturally relevant programming.

name: Briar Patch Corner
details:
Briar Patch Corner was designed and developed with children in mind. Our program’s philosophy is children develop socially and emotionally when exposed to an environment that offers quality learning experiences.

Briar Patch Corner feels it is very important that each child develop a positive self-image. We achieve this through positive reinforcement, tender care, loving teachers, and a child friendly environment. The children in our care will be secure in knowledge that they are special!

name: Eagan Montessori & Childcare
details:
Eagan Montessori and Amazing Beginnings Montessori Child Care & Preschool are unique Montessori based schools and care centers located in Eagan and Inver Grove Heights. In business since 1974 we are considered one of the oldest and well established Montessori schools in Minnesota.

We are unique in that, along with Montessori Method of education we also incorporate the S.M.A.R.T. curriculum for children. This program was designed by the Minnesota Learning Resources Center, a result of A Chance to Grow and New Vision School.

Eagan Montessori and Amazing Beginnings Montessori schools are the only Montessori schools in the Twin Cities that incorporate the S.M.A.R.T. program into their Montessori curriculum.

name: Fun Factory Child Care Center LLC
details: Our Primary Corporate Mission is to have our EnDucate™ Learning System in every Licensed Private Childcare center and Head Start classroom throughout the USA and Canada. This specialized Resource Material will be donated at no cost to these facilities.

name: Christ's Kids Preschool
details:
Christ's Kids Preschool is located 3 1/2 blocks N. of 169 on Marystown Rd. across the street from Lions Park and Sweeney Elementary in Shakopee, MN. 

We consider it a privilege to partner with you and your family in the education of children. Christ's Kids Preschool offers a rich classroom environment where children are encouraged to explore and are challenged to learn, while making friends and developing self-confidence. These early years cement a foundation for their lives. Now is the time to foster a love of learning. We seek to serve God by providing quality early childhood education in a faith based learning environment.

name: West Central Family Service Center
details:
Head Start is a program that helps young children between the ages of three and five grow up ready to succeed in school and in life. Programs work to meet high standards for delivering quality services to children and their families. Children who attend Head Start programs participate in fun activities while developing social skills. Head Start children also receive nutritious meals and the necessary health care in a safe environment.

Early Head Start is a program for families with infants and toddlers ages birth to three. Families who are expecting a new baby may enroll in Early Head Start. Families do not pay a fee for Head Start or Early Head Start.

Parents with children in Head Start participate in all aspects of the program. They help to govern, plan what children learn, and provide advice about needed services. Parents and other community members also volunteer in classrooms and other parts of the programs.

Head Start and Early Head Start welcome children with disabilities. Parents of children with disabilities are strongly encouraged to participate in their children’s daily routines and activities.

Migrant & Seasonal Head Start program provides comprehensive Head Start services, including child development, and social and health services, to low-income families working in agriculture, or families who migrate for the purpose of working in agriculture.

name: Dei Spring Academy and Child Care
details:
If you are looking for a place where your child can be taught in a loving Christian environment, please consider Dei Spring Academy.

 

God commands us to raise our children properly:  "Train up a child in the way he should go, and when he is old, he will not depart from it." Proverbs 22:6

The members of Gloria Dei Lutheran Church feel strongly about the importance of providing that Christ centered academic foundation to nurture our children spiritually, mentally, and physically.  We also felt that many in our community would be interested in a Christian academy, where their children would be raised in God’s Word, “to the Glory of God”.  Out of this need arose Dei Spring Academy. 

After much praying, planning, and plenty of hard work; our preschool opened on September 4th, 2007 with one student.  The Lord has since blessed us with more students and an additional child care center. 

A little bit about our name…  Zachariah spoke these words at the naming of his son, John the Baptist:  “And you, child, will be called the prophet of the Highest; for you will go before the face of the Lord to prepare His ways, to give knowledge of salvation to His people by the remission of their sins, through the tender mercy of our God, with which the Dayspring from on high has visited us; to give light to those who sit in darkness and the shadow of death, to guide our feet into the way of peace.”  (Luke 1:76-79)  Dei is the Latin word for God, which comes from the name of our church Gloria Dei: to the glory of God.  Spring comes from our location, Cold Spring, Minnesota.  We chose the name both to indicate a connection to our church and a connection to our community.  We also chose the name Academy to depict our willingness to educate our children according to the highest standards of traditional learning and methodology. 

 A little bit about our logo… The cross of Christ is the center of our crown of life.  Through Him, we raise daily in His love.  From Luke 10: 41-42:  “Jesus answered and said to her, ‘Martha, Martha, you are worried and troubled about many things.  But one thing is needed, and Mary has chosen that good part, which will not be taken away from her.’”  We learn from this that there is one thing more important than anything else:  Knowing Jesus as our Savior from sin and death.

name: Madina Academy LLC
details:
Madina Academy is an academy administered by a  community of educated leaders that oversee teachers, qualified teachers, qualified aids, volunteers and parents as care takers to instill their knowledge to the children they take care of.

The main goal is to produce successful and ready for school better yet ready for life children that will surpass their expectations in every step they take.  We are committed to each and every one of those children to become very successful in life early on, therefore we strive the way their brain is stimulated for the time that they are with us at the academy and we hope to teach them how to retain and use that knowledge throughtout their life.

We have many different programs that the children make very busy throughtout the day.  For the school age we have quran memorization,  islamic education, lecture giving, math, social studies, history and other brain development discussions.  They take pride in participating in all and they are very eagar to attend each and every class that they attend.  They are always hungry for more for the informations presented to them and they all eagerly participate in the question and answer sessions.

It teaches them how to be a leader in the community that they live in.  It teaches them to respect themselves and to respect others and finally and most importantly it teaches them to be humble no matter how much knowledge they have.

We also have preschool children that are as eagar as their predecessors.  The programs that we present to our preschool is of course little different from the ones presented to our school age children.  Even though we try to follow a miniture of the school age program, it is little flexible and is governned by their age, meaning age appropriate.

The curiculum for our preschool children also includes quran memorization, islamic education, history, fine motor skills, painting, beginning arabic language, math, intensive one on one english reading program, beginning somali language speaking, art, music, story telling, and other brain stimulating games. Both visual and audio media is utilized in their program to facilitate their learning process.

We have two english programs that we utilize and introduce to our preschool children.  One is Hooked on phonics and the other is my child can read.  Both programs are followed throughly to give maximum brain retention to increase the learnng curve for the child.  The result of those combined programs and the commitment and tireless effort of their teachers have produced many success in our preschool program and can be seen on the number of kids that can read both arabic and english by age five in a second grade level.

For our toddler program, we have age appropriate learning, even though they also are introduced to my baby can read program, their teachers mostly concentrate on how to make them ready for the task ahead of them in preschool.  We focus in teaching them alphabet letters and beginning letter recognition both in english and arabic, fine motor skills, painting, story telling, etc.  Both visual and audio media is utilized in their program to facilitate their learning process.

For our infants, they are the luckiest of all, as they have the most caring parents as care takers that are hand selected for them.  For their commitment in caring our infants, they make sure that infants have the best environment that are closest to home if not better when it comes to caring.  At the infant room, they are introduced in story telling, languages both english and somali, differen t objects are introduced to them for touch and feel, etc. They have the most human interaction in all programs as needed in their developing brain.

In addition to commiting to our children’s learning process, we also strive to encourage and educate their parents that participate in parents as care takers program by giving them fifty percent scholarships of getting their child development certificate and we left the other fifty percent for their responsibility so they can commit the program and follow through it untill they get their certiificate from the state.  These combined efforts create a community that are eagar to learn all the time and professional parents as care takers as they are learning not only from their CDA class but also from educated administration that are willing to build its community to produce a healthy functioning individuals to raise a healthy functioning children to become leaders for tomorrow in every community they happenn to live in.

It is and evnironment of learning that is desciplined and fruitfull.

We follow the best way of life.  Alxamdulillaah.

name: CAP Head Start
details:
Head Start and Early Head Start are comprehensive child development, health and social service programs for low-income families.  Since 1965, Head Start has been serving the needs of disadvantaged infants, children, and pregnant women across America.

Over 1400 children, from prenatal through age 5, are enrolled in Community Action’s programs each year throughout Ramsey County.  Options include full-day, half-day, therapeutic, and inclusion classrooms, and home-visiting programs.  Families who meet our eligibility requirements and families with children with special needs are encouraged to apply.

    The prenatal to age 3 program, Early Head Start, offers a home-based design for families. Early Head Start Home Visitors meet regularly with parents and children to nurture child development and parenting skills. Families who qualify for childcare assistance may also choose full-day, center-based enhanced childcare for children ages six weeks to five years.
    Head Start children between the ages of 3 to 5 attend center-based programming. Classes are offered in either half-day or full-day options at centers conveniently located throughout Ramsey County. Eight centers operate half-day classes, 4 days a week from September through late May. A full-day, full-year option is also available at the Bigelow Head Start Center, or through partnership contracts with community childcare facilities.

name: Peter Pan Preschool & Childcare
details: Our purpose is to offer positive experiences for a healthy self concept. We strive for a program that fills each child's individual needs. Explore with us and find childhood a rewarding experience for family and children. "We Care and it Shows."

name: St Peter Community Childcare Center
details:

name: Beaver Lake Head Start
details:
Head Start and Early Head Start are comprehensive child development, health and social service programs for low-income families.  Since 1965, Head Start has been serving the needs of disadvantaged infants, children, and pregnant women across America.

Over 1400 children, from prenatal through age 5, are enrolled in Community Action’s programs each year throughout Ramsey County.  Options include full-day, half-day, therapeutic, and inclusion classrooms, and home-visiting programs.  Families who meet our eligibility requirements and families with children with special needs are encouraged to apply.

    The prenatal to age 3 program, Early Head Start, offers a home-based design for families. Early Head Start Home Visitors meet regularly with parents and children to nurture child development and parenting skills. Families who qualify for childcare assistance may also choose full-day, center-based enhanced childcare for children ages six weeks to five years.
    Head Start children between the ages of 3 to 5 attend center-based programming. Classes are offered in either half-day or full-day options at centers conveniently located throughout Ramsey County. Eight centers operate half-day classes, 4 days a week from September through late May. A full-day, full-year option is also available at the Bigelow Head Start Center, or through partnership contracts with community childcare facilities.

name: Prairie Hill Montessori LLC
details:
The Montessori Method is based on 100+ years of proven scientific observation and individualized teaching. Each skill is broken down into small components, which are taught in a child-friendly, hands-on way. Children use the Montessori materials to build a concrete understanding of each skill. Individualized lessons and continued practice create a mastery of knowledge and a strong foundation toward higher-level thinking.

Unlike traditional education, the Montessori approach is toward mastery and not a set curriculum, within a set time. In Montessori, when a child is developmentally ready, they advance to the next level of learning. No child is forced ahead or held behind within a group lesson. This is why it is not uncommon for three year-olds to become readers, and 4 and 5 year-olds to develop math skills beyond traditional expectations. A true Montessori program is multi-age. Children between the ages of two-and-a-half to six-and-a-half all share the same learning environment. In the mixed-age setting, the children learn from one another.  Younger children get a preview of future work by watching the older children.  Older children reinforce their knowledge by sharing it with younger children. All the children learn to work with others of different ages and abilities, to respect each other’s work, and to treat each other with courtesy.
