name: Little Minds Learning Center Woodbury LLC
details:
We are thrilled to have expanded into Minnesota to provide the Oakdale community with a premier children’s learning center that is both educational and affordable. Director Maria Buche is working to ensure that we deliver only the best LMLC experience across the river. 

Tucked back on 470 Imperial Drive North in Oakdale. LMLC is conveniently located just off I-94 and Radio Drive. We invite you to come take a tour of our facility and discover how LMLC provides the premier experience in child development.

name: Smiling Faces Child Development Center
details: Smiling Faces Academy, LLCstaff strives to provide the highest quality of Childcare and educational service that promotes and enhances each child’s development; while assuring our parent’s peace of mind in the care and services we render.Our program focuses on building positive self-esteem, self-confidence and positive body image in each child. We promote and model healthy eating lifestyles, along with incorporating healthy practices into daily meals and curriculum. We promote and model active movement through physical fitness and integrate movement in our schedule throughout the day.

name: SonShine Learning Center St Paul
details: SonShine Learning Center, the 501(c)(3) non-profit organization and vision of Mendota Heights United Church of Christ, provides children a safe and secure, supervised, educational and recreational learning environment in a Christian atmosphere. The staff, program and facilities create a warm and friendly environment for channeling children’s energies and meeting their individual needs.

name: St Johns Lutheran Preschool
details: St. John’s Lutheran Preschool believes that children are a blessing from the Lord, and he has given us the privilege to feed his lambs.  God has given parents the primary responsibility for the nurturing of their children.  Our preschool is here to assist in that process by providing a Christian environment with an atmosphere of love, trust, care and respect.  We provide developmentally appropriate experiences and “hands-on” activities that facilitate their growth in the areas of spiritual, cognitive, social, emotional and physical development.  These goals will be achieved through a strong partnership with parents, teachers and children.  We pray that God will bless our guidance of his precious lambs.

name: Tierra Encantada Inc
details: We are a warm, community-oriented Spanish Immersion Daycare and Preschool that has an international view of education. We focus on the growth of the whole child and believe children learn best by doing. We strive to be environmentally friendly by offering cloth diapering for children in our care and providing wholesome, organic foods cooked fresh daily in our commercial kitchen on-site.

name: Super Star Child Development Center
details: Super Star Child Development Center was opened in 2013 to serve the needs of our growing community. Over the years, the school has earned praise for its continuous improvement in student test scores AND consistently high levels of parent satisfaction. In 2008, the school won the Mayor’s award of distinction for its after-school arts program. A number of the founding teachers still teach at Super Star Child Development Center – a testament to the warmth and spirit of this learning community.

name: Stepping Stones Childcare Learning Center Inc
details:
A leader in Early Childhood Education
When it comes to your children, nothing less than the highest standards will do. Our center provides a safe environment for your child to explore his or her full potential. If you're looking for a childcare center that meets these stringent demands, look no further!

name: El Bosque Encantado
details:
El Bosque Encantado is a Spanish Immersion Early Learning Center for children ages 16 months to 8 years.

Combining immersive Spanish instruction with a thoughtfully balanced early childhood curriculum, EBE opens doors to opportunities that span a lifetime.

name: St Francis Xavier School
details: St. Francis Xavier Catholic School is committed to providing students with a quality education emphasizing spiritual growth, academic excellence and community service. We follow the teachings of Jesus by loving and respecting each person in everything we do and say.

name: St Dominic Preschool
details:
The curriculum uses themes of study centered on the young child and his or her world. The readiness skills taught throughout these themes include:

    Social/Emotional: Separation from parent, respect, sharing, using words to express feeling and solve conflict…
    Language Skills: Speaking in complete sentences, colors, name objects, listening, following directions, sharing stories…
    Reading Readiness: Interest in books and how a book is read, recognizing letters…
    Number Readiness: Recognize numerals one to ten, make a simple patterns, copy simple geometric shapes…
    Self-Help Skills: Large muscle: walk a line, hop, catch & throw Small muscle: block building, scissors use, draw, copy, paste…
    Religious Skills: Awareness of God in our lives, Bible stories, sing and prayer…
    Social Skills: Sharing, listening, patience, respect, responsibility…

name: St Als Pals
details: The mission of St Alphonsus Parish School is to provide a quality Catholic education for all of its students.

name: Semcac Head Start LeRoy
details: We are committed to building bright futures by enriching young   children, ages Birth – 5 years old, and empowering their families. Comprehensive services and community opportunities support healthy families.

name: Sam & Abes Childcare Learning & Development Center
details: The mission of Sam & Abe's Child Care, Learning and Development Center is to provide high quality child care that will enhance the children's physical, social, intellectual and emotional growth in a safe and nurturing environment. Children will have opportunities for learning and development scheduled into each day that will allow them to express their unique personalities.

name: Rise N Shine Childcare Center Inc
Playhouse Child Care Center Inc
details: Rise N Shine Childcare Centers provides a safe and healthy environment for children and their families within our community. Our focus is helping each child develop his/her personality, mind and body to his/her full potential, as well as providing quality care and a safe environment. Your child will also gain an understanding of the world around him/her that will help him/her in later years when staring school. It is a time when a child learns about socializing and how to co-operate with the other children. Sharing with them and enjoying each other’s company as well as adapting to the various adults who care for them. Knowledge and curiosity are developed through language stimulation, art and music activities, and by the way of challenging simple problems. Creative and constructive activities are provided in both free and guided play.

name: Peace in Christ Christian Preschool
details: Our mission is to provide preschool age children with a Christ-centered school readiness education. We help children grow in their love for Jesus as they serve and follow Him.

name: Notre Dame Academy Catholic School Preschool
details: Notre Dame Academy is a Pre-K–8th grade regional Catholic school serving families in the western suburbs of Minneapolis, MN, which fosters an education rooted in Catholic tradition. As a community of educators, staff, parents and parishioners, we challenge our students through academic excellence, spiritual formation, social development and moral growth.

name: New Life Academy Early Childhood Program
details: Our mission at New Life Academy is to educate and energize each student to impact their world for Jesus Christ and to reach their full potential in scholarship, leadership and service out of love for God and one another.

name: Mounds Park Academy
details: Mounds Park Academy's history is filled with innovation and dedication. Educators Bob and Sandy Kreischer founded the school with the belief that the best way for students to realize their full potential is by making learning joyful. Since the school opened its doors in 1982, MPA students have been joyfully engaged in their own intellectual, social, physical, and moral growth. The idea that a school could be nurturing and rigorous was new, but after 30 years, the hallways of MPA continue to be filled with vibrant, happy, challenged students.

name: Mis Amigos Spanish Immersion
details:
Full Immersion - Not Bilingual

We believe that children learn a second language best through immersion. We work with our teachers to eliminate English in the classroom. Our curriculum focuses not only on the skill development of the children, but also intentionally works to teach the language.

Healthy Foods Matter

We believe that the food we put into our bodies is important - much more so for growing little bodies! Our snacks contain no trans fats, no high fructose corn syrup and are often organic. The milk we serve is rBGH-free. Our lunches are catered and don't provide as much control over the ingredients but we are actively working towards this goal.

Teacher and Child Bonding

We believe that children learn best when they feel safe and loved. We pay special attention to ensure that children develop a bond with their teacher throughout the year. Children are placed with one primary teacher for the entire school year. We are careful with our hiring decisions to ensure our staff believe in our mission. Then we do our best to provide an environment that makes people want to stay. If a teacher decides to resign, we ask that it is done only at the end of the school year.

Reusing Resources

We believe that it is important to support the communities where we are located. One way we contribute is by choosing to use existing community spaces. Our facilities may not be the newest and most fashionable but that is a conscious choice. We want to be in the community and bring life to older buildings (like churches) that would otherwise be sitting empty during the week.

name: Kids Grow Inc
details:
As an extraordinary child care provider...
We strive to have a positive impact on
- The families of our children,
- The communities they reside in
- And the churches we occupy

name: Kandi Land Learning Center
details: KandiLand Learning Center is a licensed daycare owned by Kandi Jensen, and is for toddlers, preschool children and school-age children.  We are open from 6:45 AM-6:00 PM  each week day.  Children may come full time or part time. A family rate is provided for families with multiple children in KandiLand Learning Center. We also offer drop-in care limited to availability. Please call 444-KIDS (5437) in advance.  Your child must have required paperwork on record prior to the first visit.

name: Heritage Lutheran Church
details: Heritage Lutheran School began in the fall of 1993.  A kindergarten program was added for the 2001 school year.  We  have three large, bright, well-equipped classrooms as well as a full size gym where the children are able to learn, grow and discover.  Children do not need to be members of Heritage congregation to enroll in our Preschool or Kindergarten programs.  Heritage Lutheran School provides a learning environment with called, specially trained teachers.  They turn to God’s Word and prayer on a daily basis, collaborate with one another, and communicate with parents frequently.  Teachers strive for a mixture of structure, independence and hands-on activity to facilitate inquiry, creativity, social responsibility and higher level thinking where children feel safe, comfortable and happy as they learn.

name: Heartland Christian Academy Preschool
details:
Heartland Christian Academy Preschool is a place for younger children to explore God’s creation and to inspire fun in learning. The preschool years are a special time for kids and families to be introduced to learning in a structured, fun and engaging environment. Hands-on activities are planned for the students every day so that our students can learn and grow socially, emotionally and spiritually. 

Preschool years are an exciting time to introduce a Christian education to students. There is nothing more precious than seeing a child who is fascinated with God’s magnificent creation and learning to show His love to others. With these young minds opening up to the world around them, Heartland Preschool provides a foundation of spiritual growth, implementing a Biblical education and training. We combine that Biblical focus with excellence in preschool curriculum, giving our students a well-rounded preschool experience in a loving, welcoming place.

name: City of Lakes Child Care Center LLC
Cedar Riverside Child Care Center LLC
Burnsville Learning Center Inc
details: The Burnsville Area Learning Center (BALC) is a collection of programs throughout Burnsville-Eagan-Savage School District 191 that provide addition support to meet the needs of all learners. These services are delivered primarily through extended day and extended year programs. For more information about these programs, use the links below.

name: Bethel Child Care Center
details: Bethel Lutheran Church was built in 2000 and provides a beautiful environment for Bethel Child Care Center. The church is located on the north side of Bemidji on Irvine Ave.

name: Angels Learning Center
details: Our mission is to provide high quality child care with an emphasis on education. We strive to provide a safe, nurturing environment that will give each child the fundamentals vital to their growth, and development.

name: Apple Academy Learning Center LLC
details: Apple Academy has provided as the most trusted and reliable child care learning center in the area for over 15 years. We are committed to providing the very best in early childhood education. Apple Academy staff is committed to ensuring each child's safety and security. While at our center, your child is our number one priority. Our goal is to give children the tools to be successful and develop a positive self-esteem. Our curriculum uses themes to promote learning through age appropriate group and individual activities. Our teachers provide each child with a variety of activities in math, reading, science, social studies, health, creative arts, and music and movement. These activities are designed to help each child develop socially, emotionally, intellectually and physically.
business hours: Monday through Friday from 5:45 a.m. to 6:15 p.m.

name: Building Blocks Learning Center
details:
We believe that the first few years of life pave the way for children’s future education and it is so important to work with and nurture children. Because all children learn differently and are so diverse, we pay close attention to each child’s needs and gain knowledge of which way they learn best.

  Building Blocks Learning Center provides a daily program in which a child is encouraged to interact according to their individual ability. The rooms are divided into learning centers where children are encouraged to explore, create, inquire, and respond at their own level. Their environment is structured to provide activities for language development, manipulation of materials, developing routines and work habits, and expressing feelings and ideas. The children are grouped according to their developmental age, which enables the child to grow among his/her peers. The teacher plans and implements activities which are developmentally appropriate to ensure that the children are being challenged, yet are obtaining successful experiences to promote self-worth. The major components of the curriculum are: active learning, language, representing
experiences and ideas, logical reasoning, and understanding time and space.

name: Butterfly Hill Nature Preschool Inc
details:
Our Mission
The mission of Butterfly Hill Nature Preschool is to provide a loving, supportive and educational preschool environment for children and families that will foster a strong relationship between children and nature.

name: God's Little Treasures Childcare
details:
Hello and welcome to God’s Little Treasures! We are a Christian preschool and childcare center located in Brooklyn Center, MN. We provide children from 6 weeks to 5 years old with a safe, loving, fun and nurturing environment in an educational faith based setting. Children learn and grow through play, study, music and prayer and prepare for the challenges and opportunities that await them as they embark on their exciting journey through life on God’s planet Earth.

We are licensed by the Minnesota Department of Human Services (DHS) and meet or exceed all state standards and regulations for child care centers. Our staff has many years of experience in early childhood education and we maintain small group sizes to provide more personal attention to the needs of every child in our care.

name: Hartley Nature Preschool
details: Hartley Nature Preschool’s mission is to inspire lifelong connections with nature through education, play and exploration in a premier preschool environment that supports the whole child’s development while preparing children for school.

name: Highland Village Montessori School
details:
The Highland Village Montessori School began with Mrs. Mano Rathnayake over 23 years ago. She had worked at several childcare centers before opening her own school.

In 2015, after more than 30 years in the Montessori system and after building a wonderful, successful and well reputed school, Mrs. Mano decided to retire and give Varuni and Shamil Ranasinghe the opportunity to take over running the school.

The Highland Village Montessori School continues the great traditions of the Montessori educational system and continues to grow.

name: Lake Area Discovery Center at Annunciation School
details:
Founder Janet Miller, began LADC in 1999 to fill a need in the community for more, strong, Christian-based early childhood programs.  Striving to offer the highest-quality pre-primary education, the decision was made to hire only 4 year degree, early-childhood education/ kindergarten certified lead teachers with a current MN teaching license. Janet created a unique blend of the “Bank Street”, “High Scope”, “ECFE” and “Montessori” models of learning together with a Christian emphasis for the daily operating philosophy. LADC lead teachers from all locations team together to write monthly lesson plans from the LADC Curriculum.

Janet, with the LADC Board of Directors, has built partnerships with area churches and schools. LADC provides the education, licensing and accreditation expertise for high-quality care and Kindergarten-readiness programs. Our partners provide beautiful buildings and spaces plus partner in family fellowship events. These partnerships enable LADC to hire dedicated, licensed early-childhood teachers and provide them with competitive salaries and benefits.

Since 1999, LADC has grown to 9 metro partnerships with a team of over 50 teachers and staff. 6 locations are currently NAEYC Accredited. Originally a traditional preschool program, LADC has grown to include programs for infants and toddlers. All locations offer wrap-around care and full-time schedules, with many sites providing year-round (summer) programing.

name: Lake Area Discovery Center at St Josephs School
details:
Founder Janet Miller, began LADC in 1999 to fill a need in the community for more, strong, Christian-based early childhood programs.  Striving to offer the highest-quality pre-primary education, the decision was made to hire only 4 year degree, early-childhood education/ kindergarten certified lead teachers with a current MN teaching license. Janet created a unique blend of the “Bank Street”, “High Scope”, “ECFE” and “Montessori” models of learning together with a Christian emphasis for the daily operating philosophy. Since 1999, LADC has grown to 9 metro partnerships with a team of over 50 teachers and staff. 6 locations are currently NAEYC Accredited. All locations offer wrap-around care and full-time schedules, with many sites providing year-round (summer) programing.

name: Lighthouse Learning Academy
details: Lighthouse Learning Academy believes in providing a free environment to the children in which activities are beautiful, purposeful and child size. Our mission is to give children opportunity to explore while respecting their peers and surroundings.

name: Little Lambs Learning Center
details:
Mission Statement
Little Lambs Learning Center exists to share the love of Jesus through quality childcare and early childhood education.
PURPOSE
It’s our plan at Little Lambs to keep your child in Jesus’ hands. “Let the little children come to me, and do not hinder them, for the kingdom of heaven belongs to such as these.”

name: New Creations Child Care & Learning Center
details: New Creations exists to provide a safe, developmentally appropriate, and Christ-centered environment for infants through school age children. Our focus is to provide stimulating, educational, and service-learning experiences which promote each child's social/emotional, physical and cognitive development. Our goal is to support children's desire to be life-long learners.

name: New Horizon Academy
details: It is not an average mission to provide the best child development on the planet, but then New Horizon Academy is not an average company. New Horizon Academy is an exceptional company, grown out of the commitment to children and families that Sue Dunkley, our founder, made in 1971 when she opened her first child care program. Sue's ongoing belief is that there is nothing more important than the self-esteem of every child. We invite you to see why New Horizon Academy is so much more than day care.

name: North Ridge Child Day Care LLC
Pond Early Childhood Family Development Center
Small World Learning Center
details:
Visit any Small World Child Care Learning Center Locations and you will notice the difference from the moment you walk in. Parents tell us it feels like home. Everything we do at Small World Daycare Learning Center, from our professional staff to our safe clean environment assures parents that their child will be safe, happy and learning. 

We understand that choosing child care is truly one of the most important decisions parents will ever make. Child development experts confirm that high-quality care in the formative years is instrumental in building positive relationships, self-concepts, and attitudes toward learning that will last a lifetime. Your child deserves nothing less than the best!

name: St Josephs School
details: St. Joseph’s school is the parish school of St. Francis de Sales, St. Joseph’s, and surrounding parish communities.  With a rich history stretching over 130 years, St. Joseph’s school continues to develop the pillars of faith, leadership, and service in students.  Hover over the buttons on the Wall of History Mural below to explore many of the events that have shaped our wonderful school.

name: Stay Play & Learn Childcare & Activity Center
details: We have a loving, caring, safe, and secure environment for your child while having lots of fun  learning.

name: The Little School Inc
details:
The Little School began in a church basement in 1984.
In 2000, we were able to purchase our building in the heart of Highland Park.
The building was renovated and an amazing environment for children was created.
Our classrooms are filled with natural light, neutral colors and engaging materials.
The outdoor play space includes a Children’s Garden and gazebo.
Children can chase butterflies, grow beans and carrots,
run with rainbow streamers through garden paths and develop a love of nature.
RESPECT for ourselves, our friends and our environment, is the cornerstone of
The Little School’s philosophy.

We pride ourselves on our low teacher/child ratios,
creative curriculum and the ability to see each child as a gift.

Each day the children fill our hearts with laughter and joy.
Thank you for your interest in our program.
We look forward to sharing information with you about our special “Little School”

name: Wonderland Academy Child Care Center Inc
WSU Childrens Center W-K Elementary School
Ashland YMCA- YKids Club at Walker
Champions - Hopkins Elementary
details: Champions has a great solution for busy working families: activities that combine fun and learning, together with the safety and convenience of a high-quality program right inside your school. Champions offers a variety of group and individual activities designed to keep your child exploring and growing. From art, dramatic play, math and science to problem-solving, language, motor skills and more, we help your child continue learning and developing essential life skills – whether school is in session or not.

name: Noah's Ark Early Childhood Education Program
Salem Child Development Center - North Marion
details:
SCDC strives to provide consistent environments in which children can discover their own capabilities and creativity.  Children are encouraged to develop self-discipline and a respect for others.  We maintain a nonsexist, non-racist setting for children's learning.  We believe it is important to enhance the development of a positive self-image in each child.  We accomplish this by providing warmth and nurturing in a growth-facilitating environment rich with opportunities to learn and discover. 

 

Our goal is to provide parents with an open, welcoming atmosphere to encourage and promote parent involvement and parent peace of mind.  We work to develop a one-to-one relationship with each child and parent, communicating to the child that they are "cared about" as well as "cared for".  We accomplish this by providing the best suited staff; qualified and dedicated to understanding the needs of the children and families.

Further, we seek to extend the children's environment beyond the classroom and into the community.
We are committed to advocating for all children, reaching out into the community and the state to advocate for high quality care for all families.
 

It is the policy of Salem Child Development Center that no person shall be discriminated against by reason of race, color, religion, disability, sex, age or national origin. SCDC accepts all children that are able to function within staff ratio and within the environments we maintain.
business hours: 6:45 am to 6:00 pm, Monday through Friday

name: Kids Campus
details:
Welcome to Kids Campus, "Your Neighborhood Preschool & Childcare Center"! We look forward to making life easier and more enjoyable for our parents and children. We are committed to you and your family's preschool and childcare needs.


Early experiences play a major role in a child's growth and development. We feel we can provide the best care for your child in our safe, loving, and enriching environment. Every child is a special, unique individual. Therefore, our developmental program is geared to the social, emotional, intellectual, and physical growth of each child.


We believe that established guidelines and interaction by our professional teaching staff allows development to progress smoothly.  We carefully select, train, and evaluate our teachers to ensure the best learning experiences for your child.  Our teachers create a caring and nurturing atmosphere at our centers.  They also encourage your child's creativity and positive self-image.


We look forward to a long, rewarding relationship with your family and developing a happy, well-rounded child! Contact us today to learn more about  what Kids Campus can offer your child and tuition costs.

name: Learning Years - Jenkins
details: The Jenkins Learning Years Day School welcomes your inquiry into our day school program. We have programs to meet the needs of children ages 6 weeks to 12 years of age. Our school is located in the heart of Beaverton. It is located near many businesses, including Beaverton mall, Tektronix and NIKE. This school is the largest of the Learning Years and is located on an acre encompassed by a natural habitat reserve. Our children can be found on any given day peering through the fence at ducks, squirrels, or sometimes even deer! The way this facility is situated makes for a very peaceful retreat from the hustle and bustle of city life. Bob and Lis Richardson founded Learning Years in 1973 and established this location in 1991. In 1998, their daughter Amy Kight and her husband John Kight purchased this location, taking the schools into their second generation. Gloria Stevens is the Director at this location. She has worked with children for over 28 years and she celebrated her 9th anniversary with Learning Years in 2004! She is a great mentor to her staff and has created a dedicated teaching team at this location. Our school is proud of its professionally trained teachers, who are able to gracefully combine both the academics needed in an early childhood education program and a genuine love for learning. Our goal is to provide each child with a clean, safe and nurturing environment in which (s)he can learn and grow. It is our mission to meet the growing needs of parents in our community. We strive to meet these needs by listening to our parents and staff and providing a variety of programs and events to meet their needs. Our staff enjoys preparing experiences for the children that will instill in them a love for learning. This, along with the bonds they will create with their peers and caregivers, is what makes our school a family. Come in for a tour at any time. We look forward to meeting you and your child.

name: Mayflower Montessori
details:
Mayflower Montessori is a preschool, kindergarten and child care center conveniently located in the heart of Beaverton, Oregon. We offer a structured education program for 2 to 6 year olds that excels in preparing children for 1st grade and beyond. We also offer child care for infants 6 weeks and older.

To help working parents, our facility is open Monday through Friday, 6:30am to 6:00pm year round with before-school and after-school care available. We are located near Nike, Tektronix, Intel and many other companies on the west side of Portland. Meals are prepared on premises and the children get frequent exercise in our large fenced playground with play structures and covered play areas.

Our experienced teachers closely follow the Montessori Method and work with the rest of our staff to foster a caring, nurturing environment where kids thrive. Our owners are also very involved in teaching and with the management of the school.

name: HVJA Preschool
details:
Welcome to Hood View Junior Academy, a private Seventh-day Adventist Christian School in Boring, Oregon. Sitting on 20 beautiful wooded acres, grades Preschool through 8th grade are taught not only reading, writing, and arithmetic, but morals, values and character traits.

Academically, Hood View is a leader. An accredited school, we believe in approaching a child’s education holistically – to not only educate, but enrich our children. Students at Hood View participate in Music, Art, Computer Skills, Spanish and Physical Education, all taught by specialized teachers. Students consistently score at least one grade level above the average student on standardized tests.

But Hood View isn’t just about academics. At HVJA, the staff creates a safe environment where each student will be encouraged to have a personal relationship with God and positive relationships with others. HVJA nurtures a healthy self image and teaches students to make healthy choices.

Hood View implements Love and Logic into all of our classrooms. This approach to teaching empowers students to think for themselves and prepares them to function effectively in a society filled with temptations, decisions, and consequences. It also raises the level of student responsibility, while treating each student with respect and dignity.

We pride ourselves on a ‘family feel’ environment: safe, nurturing and character building. Our small class size and caring teachers are examples of what we stand for at Hood View Junior Academy: Preparing People for a Christ-Centered Life…one child at a time.

Discover more about our school through exploring these pages, requesting an information packet, or by contacting the school for a personal tour. We look forward to meeting you soon!
business hours:
7:00 a.m.-6:00 p.m.Monday through Thursday and 
7:00 a.m.-5:00 p.m. on Friday

name: Academy For Kids
details: Academy for Kids welcomes children, from 6-week old infants through 6th graders into our day school, preschool, pre-kindergarten, private kindergarten and after-public school programs. Our certified, dedicated staff provide age appropriate activities and learning to nurture your children. Our small classes allow our staff to provide special attention needed by each and every child. Our facility is bright and clean - a happy place to be. Explore our site to learn more about our quality programs.
business hours: Monday through Friday from 6:15 a.m. to 6:15 p.m.

name: Happy Valley Montessori
details:
The school is located on the site of what was the Hubbard family farm in Clackamas, just outside of South East Portland, Oregon. It is housed in a log cabin that has been turned into a children's house. We have one Montessori Primary School classroom located inside the original farm house.  This offers a very secure and well organized prepared environment.

Our mission is to build confidence and love of learning, giving students a solid foundation for a healthy and happy life.

Our longtime teachers and staff are dedicated to helping each child discover their unique potential – academically, socially and interpersonally.

So if you are looking for a Montessori School in Portland, we invite you to learn more about us. Come and visit our classroom soon. We look forward to getting to know your child.

name: Valley View Day School
details:
Valley View Dayschool is a Christian Childcare facility located in the lower level of Valley View Church on Sunnyside Road in Clackamas, Oregon

We provide before and after school care for school age children along with daycare for infants, toddlers, preschool and kindergarten classes with a curriculum developed to minister to the educational, physical and spiritual needs of the children.   

Valley View was formed in 1991 as a ministry of Valley View Church.  We are a Non-Profit Organization and a member of the Association of Christian Schools International.

Our commitment is to provide a Christian environment in which your child can grow spiritually, socially, emotionally, developmentally, and physically.  Opportunities for this growth are available through play and routine activities.  Independent play, group involvement, and personal choices are combined with appropriate limits through interaction with adults and peers. 

The staff here at Valley View realizes the importance of child rearing.  With your help as a parent we endeavor to achieve the goals you have set.  We strive to enrich your child's life in a school setting which will supplement the love and guidance they receive at home.  Regular communication between the parents and teachers is essential to helping your child develop a positive attitude toward "going to school". 

Valley View Dayschool offers childcare with a preschool and kindergarten curriculum regardless of race, color, religion, national origin, marital status of parent, and need for special care.

name: La Petite Academy - Fairview
details:
Welcome to La Petite Academy educational daycare in Fairview, OR! My name is Rosanna Archibald and I am the academy director. I started my career in early childhood education in 1999 and have been working at this school since 2007. I have my bachelor’s degree in English literature and am thrilled that I get to share my passion for books and learning with the children in our center.

Whether it’s providing loving care for infants, participating in activities in our preschool programs, or prepping tomorrow’s first graders through our Private Kindergarten, I love coming to work and knowing my team and I are providing a safe and nurturing environment for the children in our school.

I have the most amazing team in the business here in Fairview! Our staff has more than 180 years of combined teaching experience, much of it right here in this center. My teachers are truly devoted to the children in our care. They work hard to monitor our students’ developmental milestones to ensure that they are prepared for elementary school and beyond.

I invite you to stop by or call for a tour so you can witness firsthand all the things that set La Petite Academy apart from other centers in Fairview, OR.

name: Gresham Heights Learning Center
details:
Are you looking for the perfect solution to your childcare needs?  You have found the right place! On the pages that follow, we'll introduce you to the programs and activities for the different ages of children here at Gresham Heights. Our staff consists of people who are knowledgeable and experienced in providing appropriate environments which facilitate the physical, social, emotional and intellectual development of the young children in our care.

While providing for their physical needs, such as napping, meals, lots of hugs and gross motor activity, we also have very specific goals about their cognitive and social development. Please look through the pages that follow and don't hesitate to contact us if you'd like to come take a tour or would like more information about any of our programs!

name: Small World Learning Center
details:
Welcome to Small World Learning Center's web site. We consider it a privilege for a chance to be your partner in the care and education of your child.

Small World Learning Center understands that choosing daycare for your infant, toddler, or older child is an important and exciting decision for parents. It is our goal to provide daycare for each and every child with a safe, nurturing and fun environment where your child can learn and develop their skills while engaging in the education they need for success in school. Our age-specific programs are designed to help your child grow socially, emotionally, physically, and intellectually.

name: Bethlehem Christian Preschool
details: We are a non-denominational Christian Pre-School of approximately 200 children. Attending are toddlers 9 months to 2 1/2 years and pre-schoolers ages 2 1/2 to 5. Children from many local churches attend BCP along with many children who do not have a church home. Since we are known for providing a quality program in a Christian setting, we attract families from a wide variety of backgrounds. We provide a loving Christian environment with emphasis on the developmental stages of the child. At Bethlehem Christian Pre-School we desire to provide activities that are age-appropriate and nurture the spiritual, physical, mental and social development of each child. We believe children learn as they play. Learning for children takes place when information is meaningful, and is in the context of their experiences and development. Therefore, children learn best when provided with a variety of stimulating experiences in which they may freely interact. Our Early Childhood Education program is designed to support and extend young children's learning through direct experiences. Children learn when actively engaged, so we provide a balance of teacher-directed and child-initiated activities. Bethlehem Christian Pre-School is non-denominational in nature. Jesus Christ is central to our faith and philosophy. Our Christian beliefs are best represented by the Apostle's Creed. Throughout the year we talk about how God created the world and us, and that He loves us and sent Jesus to us. At this level we pray together and learn Bible Stories with puppets, flannel graphs, dramatization and other play props.  Each month we focus on a different character trait of God.

name: Mt.Hood Meadows Daycare
details:
Mt. Hood Meadows Ski Resort is one of the only resorts in the nation to offer state-certified child care for infants as young as six weeks old. The Day Care Center operates daily from 9 AM to 4 PM and provides full-day and half-day options for children, as well as ski lessons for ages 3 to 6. Our staff to child ratio is a minimum of one staff member for every four infants and toddlers, and one staff member for every ten child preschool age to age 11.

The 3,544 square foot facility has room for up to 46 children. It was designed to be one of the most modern facilities in Oregon, and is also one of the most progressive ski resort Day Care operations in the country. In addition to age appropriate toys, the center offers activities including arts and crafts, music and snow play.

Reservations are strongly recommended for all services and are required for the Midweek Special. Reservations should be made at least 24 hrs in advance of the requested arrival time by calling 503.337.2222 ext. 1374. You will need to have the following information to make a reservation: Your child’s name and age, the date and arrival time for the reservation, your name, phone number and a credit card.

name: Bright Minds Christian Dayschool
details: Bright Minds has been joyfully impacting our community for over ten years. We believe in building children's Self esteem, Imagination and Spirit to reflect the beauty of the world God has created around them. Our educational program has been designed to inspire each child to shine and showcase their individual talents while learning teamwork and a sense of community. We look forward to sharing our winning philosophy with you.

name: Snoopeeland Child Development Center
details:
SnoopeelandChildDevelopmentCenterwas founded in 1972 as an outreach ministry of Sunset Park Community Church. For nearly 40 years the center has served the local community, as literally thousands of children have passed through our doors.

    Our aim is to provide a warm, safe place for children where they can grow socially, emotionally, physically, and spiritually. We believe that a child’s self worth develops as they learn to be responsible for their actions and are shown respect and love.
    Our trained and experienced staff helps your child learn by providing opportunities that encourage creativity and growth. They are here because they love children!
    Snoopeeland is NOT a baby-sitting service, nor are we a substitute for the family home. Rather, we want to support and come alongside the families we serve to provide a safe, wholesome environment away from home.
    In order to provide a well-rounded education, Snoopeeland features Bible stories in weekly chapel services as part of the learning experience. No reference is made to specific doctrines.
    Our purpose and vision is centered around Snoopeeland’s ministry to the community. We are a Christian center, and while our staff is not required to profess a Christian stand, we expect them to follow the moral and ethical teachings of Jesus. Staff is selected with attention to qualifications, training, abilities, and moral and ethical standards.
    As Snoopeeland is a ministry of Sunset Park Community Church, all the resources of the church are open to center families, including classes, activities, pastoral services, etc. For more information, contact Donna in the church office at 503-397-0535 or ask at the Snoopeeland office.

Educational and recreational opportunities are offered in an environment that allows children to develop at their own pace, working independently and in a group setting. The YMCA five core values of love, respect, honesty, responsibility, and service are pillars in our daily curriculum and schedule. The Sandy YMCA visits the Sandy Library on early release Wednesdays. When students enroll in after school enrichment the YMCA takes note of all enrollments and ensures students get back to the child care program when enrichment has ended.

All Day Child Care provided off site on no-school days and Winter, Spring and Summer Day Camps at Portland Lutheran School.

With the support of Oregon Trail School District Transportation, students from Firwood Elementary and Oregon Trail Academy attend this program.

Multnomah County area. Your child's care and education is of the utmost importance to us.

Our ultimate goal is to enable each child to have fun, explore and have the freedom to express their individuality, while providing a solid foundation for their future academic successes. We are a pre-school
community that values kindness and respect for each other, our school, the environment and the world around us.

From our preschool to our after school program we offer your child a nurturing, supportive and stimulating environment in which they can grow and blossom into self confident, self reliant and positive young people!

Every day MAC kids have the opportunity to explore, discover and “wallow” in all of the education offerings through their play.  The staff of MAC have established a truly child-centered learning space based on the philosophy brought to light by Bev Bos that:
“Experience is not the best teacher, it is the only teacher!”

Our teachers have worked hard to provide children with a positive, non-pressured, non-judgmental school atmosphere. The staff is particularly fluent in the following areas; Art, Science, Language, Music, Play Environments, Gardening, Brain Development and Child Development.

name: McMinnville Montessori School
details: McMinnville Montessori School was founded by two families, the Moores and the Roberts, as a single primary-age classroom in the fall of 1983. Both families were bound together by the desire for their children to have the benefits of a Montessori education. In 1985, ownership and operation of the school was transferred from the Moores and the Roberts to McMinnville Montessori School, a nonprofit, tax-exempt organization. The organization was a parent membership with a parent Board of Directors. In 1994, the school purchased the building at its present site. In 1995, members of the larger community were invited to join the board, and many changes began to take place. The school hired a full-time director in 1996, and in 1997 the building was remodeled and an elementary classroom was added to the program. In 1998, the school became a non-member organization, administered by the Director and overseen by the Board.

details:
Welcome to La Petite Academy educational daycare in Sherwood, OR! My name is Hanna Vogel and I am the academy director. I have been the director here in Sherwood since 2001 and have had the pleasure of watching many children from this community learn and grow. I cannot imagine a more fulfilling job to have.

Together, my staff and I strive to create a warm and welcoming environment in our infant care, preschool, and other early education programs. Our long-term teaching team has many years of experience and education, and partakes in yearly development training to keep our skills and knowledge current

I run this school here in Sherwood like everyone involved is an extension of my own family - the children, parents, and teachers. I strive to create a warm and welcoming environment and maintain an open-door policy at all times. name: Joyful Noise Child Care Center
details:
Together we will be partners in providing a child-oriented environment that embraces the concept of the whole child. Our activities stimulate children’s physical and intellectual development and foster social and emotional growth. Our program seeks to encourage children to think, reason, question and experiment. Through hands-on activities and challenges, the children become willing participants in their own learning cognitively, emotionally, socially, physically and culturally.

When you entrust the care and early education of your child to us, you can expect that the principles guiding that care are rooted in manifesting the following goals cited by the National Association for the Education of Young Children (NAEYC):

Relationships: That interactions between children and adults provide opportunities for children to develop an understanding of self and others and are characterized by warmth, personal respect, individuality, positive support and responsiveness. Our teachers facilitate interactions among children to provide opportunities for the development of self-esteem, social competence and intellectual growth.

Curriculum: That our curriculum implementation “reflects the knowledge that young children are active learners, drawing on direct physical and social experience as well as culturally transmitted knowledge to construct their understanding of the world around them.” Program quality is enhanced when “the curriculum encourages children to be actively involved in the learning process, to experience a variety of developmentally appropriate activities and materials. Young children learn through active manipulation of the environment and concrete experiences that contribute to concept development.”

Partnership: That teachers and families work closely in partnership to ensure high-quality care and education for children, and parents feel supported and welcomed as observers and contributors to the program. We believe in empowering parents by involving them in ongoing relationships as full partners with teachers in supporting their child’s development. “Young children are integrally connected to their families. Programs cannot adequately meet the needs of children unless they also recognize the importance of the child’s family and establish positive relationships with families based on mutual trust and respect. All communication between programs and families should be two-way, but also based on the concept that parents are and should be the principal influence in their children’s lives.”

At Joyful Noise Child Development Centers we plan activities that encourage cooperation, experimentation, and communication among children. We do not force children to operate as a large group for long periods of time. Instead we encourage children to let their curiosity and initiative drive them to make choices from a variety of classroom activities. Our teachers act as guides for these explorations, and investigators along side the children. Our Emergent Curriculum and extensive Projects speak to the children’s individual interests and allow learning within a meaningful context. The children in our centers learn to negotiate, solve problems, and construct their own code of ethics; thereby learning true compassion and developing intrinsically motivated empathy.

Parents who choose such developmentally appropriate environments for their children give them a much greater gift than any rote math or phonics lesson can. Combine this with stability, interaction, communication, and love, within the context of firm boundaries, and their children will have the foundations for successful future learning.

name: St James Child Development Center
details:
St. James Child Development Center is a non-profit private childcare in the heart of downtown Portland, Oregon. 
St. James Child Development Center was established in 1981. Our childcare center provides a safe and secure environment for over 120 children ages six weeks through kindergarten. We are committed to providing a fun-filled, rewarding program that balances each child's intellectual, physical, social, creative and emotional needs. 
Children are encouraged to be involved with the environment and learn from it. Teachers work to provide an ever changing and wide variety of activities within this setting. At each age level, themes ignite curiosity and allow children to explore their many talents. They spend their day immersed in a variety of activities that include art, music and movement, science, language, literature, and large and fine motor activities. Through all activities we seek to help the children develop self-confidence, strong academic skills and learn how to work together as a community. 
We are very proud of our program and our teachers. Our goal is to provide an environment that is safe, caring, and full of the wonder of discovery! 
Please take a look at all we have to offer! We look forward to being a part of your child's growth and development!

name: New Day School

Our curriculum is designed to allow children to gain confidence in their personal strength, an awareness of their individual gifts, and the desire to share their joy with others in society.  We involve children in both independent and collaborative tasks that teach children to develop in their own unique way while working cooperatively with others.

details: We offer school age enrichment programs to children ages 5 to 12 in more than 40 locations throughout the Portland area. name: Imagination Station Daycare Center
details: Seeking out trustworthy, reliable daycare that offers more stimulation than a typical babysitter can be a daunting and disappointing ordeal. After six years as a Certified Professional Nanny, having her own child, and braving the daycare search herself, Brandi Webber became convinced she could create a better source of child care, right in her own community. During her search, she would find a place that appeared clean, organized and well-staffed but lacked that warm, nurturing quality that every newborn needs. Or another facility would appear nurturing and friendly, but fall short of providing the clean environment and cognitive stimulation that she also felt was important. Outrageous prices for care were also an obstacle. With over ten years of child care experience, Brandi Webber decided to take matters into her own hands and, in 2001, created Imagination Station Daycare Center in her own home. Shortly after opening, Imagination Station filled up quickly, expanding in the summer of 2006. Imagination Station continues to grow, providing many families in the North Portland community with reliable, affordable, top-notch professional child care.

name: Children's Garden Day Care and Preschool Inc
details:
The Children’s Garden was incorporated in 1988 by a local family in pursuit
of quality childcare. Disappointed by the poor selection of nurturing
environments for their young daughter, the couple found most programs to be
lacking the individual, loving touch personalized childcare should emanate.
After the birth of their second child, they proceeded to open what has become
one of Portland’s most loved and adored early childhood learning centers.

Now, after developing three centers and more than 20 years later, The Children’s Garden is still mastering the fine art of childcare. It takes time, patience, motivation and passion to keep up with today’s ever-changing educational
needs of children, ensuring that each and every aspect of a program is in the
best interest of a child and their growth patterns. Constant attention to
detail and willingness to embrace new educational avenues is a must!

details: Our school exists to glorify Christ. business hours: Monday through Friday 6:30 a.m. to 6:00 p.m.

name: Portland Christian Early Childhood Education
details:
Portland Christian is first and foremost a Christian school, built upon Jesus Christ as our foundation. Standing firmly on that foundation we hold to a number of guiding principles as we fulfill our mission to educate students in the truth of God's word in every area of instruction and activity, so that their lives may be transformed by the renewing of their minds:

Independent - PCS is an autonomous, self-governing school system, receiving no funds or managerial oversight from any denomination or governmental agency. PCS is governed in its policies and administration by a Constitution which was adopted at the inception of the school. Policy is developed by the PCS Board of Trustees which consists of school parents elected by the Society (school parents). Administration is managed by the Superintendent, who oversees all operations and is accountable to the Board of Trustees.

Non-denominational - PCS is not associated with any church or denomination. With over 100 different congregations represented among our students and staff, we honor and celebrate diversity within the many Christian faith traditions.

Biblically based - At PCS we take the Bible seriously and incorporate biblical principles into every class. We strive to help our students develop critical thinking skills from a biblical perspective.

Excellence - Our standard is excellence in every area -- academics, athletics, arts...and life! Excellence may mean earning an "A" in a class, but it may also mean receiving a "C" that was earned with blood, sweat, and tears. Excellence may mean winning a championship, but it may also mean losing with grace and sportsmanship. Excellence may mean putting on a star performance, but it may also mean supporting your colleagues who falter. At PCS, excellence is about not only performance, but also character, and faith.

name: Happy Bear Day Care
details:
Happy Bear Daycare Center has provided child care services in the Portland, OR area for more than 20 years. We offer a full day care program from 5:30 A.M. to 6:00 P.M. And mid day drop ins are always ok with us. We also offer Evening Care and Saturday Care from 7:00 A.M. to 5:00 P.M. We are fully licensed and state certified center providing an early childhood development program that includes reading, music, storytelling, computers and much more. We proved healthy meals to all out children and a fenced playground for kids to have fun and let loose.


We offer summer programs, day care, activities, meals, arts, crafts, computer learning, developmental programs, music education, reading, storytelling and much more. This is a safe and loving environment that adheres to the intellectual, emotional and active side of every child’s upbringing. We care for kids from ages of 6 weeks to 12 years old and everything in between..

name: Little Lambs Preschool (Good Shephard Lutheran Chu
Markham Children's Care Association
details:
MCCA is a community of friends where the values of honesty, caring, respect and responsibility are nurtured.  Our program is designed to enrich and compliment each child's school day experience.  We strive to create a fun and safe environment which supports the individual needs and development of children.  Program components and curriculum are framed by both the National AfterSchool Association (NAA) Standards for Quality School-Age Programs and the Oregon ASK Afterschool Program Quality Standards.  
MCCA is conveniently located at Markham Elementary School.  MCCA was chartered as a nonprofit member association in 1991, and parents/guardians of children attending MCCA are members of our association.  Parent participation is encouraged and considered a valuable asset to our program.  
MCCA is licensed by the Oregon Child Care Division and is governed by a volunteer Board of Directors.   MCCA staff have passed criminal background checks and are certified in first aid/CPR and Recognizing & Reporting Child Abuse & Neglect.  Program staff complete a minimum of 15 clock hours of professional development training annually and are also enrolled in the Oregon Registry, a voluntary statewide professional development system.

name: St Johns Preschool and Daycare
details:
Welcome to St. John the Baptist Catholic School! SJB students are confident, creative and connected in faith. Our warm, caring atmosphere combines with a rigorous curriculum to inspire a dynamic community dedicated to the development of each individual child.

The academic program at St. John the Baptist Catholic School provides a rich, comprehensive learning experience. In addition to the core curriculum, students participate in Spanish, Music, Physical Education, and Library classes. The first Apple Distinguished School in Oregon, SJB incorporates technology on a one-to-one basis starting in Kindergarten!

The caring community composed of dedicated teachers, parents, and students cultivates a climate of respect and kindness. Optimal class sizes permit teachers the opportunity to meet the individual needs of each student. Parents appreciate the way that teachers both encourage and care for their students. They sense the balance between high standards and grace. All students participate in community service opportunities and are challenged to grow both intellectually and spiritually.

What do students have to say about SJB? Recently, a group of Middle School students shared their thoughts on what makes our school special:

"It's a safe, supportive, and caring place."

"Teachers give us extra time and attention."

"Classmates are like brothers and sisters." 

"SJB is my second home!"

details:

name: Willson House Child Development Center
details: Willson House Child Development Center is a non-profit organization operated by United Methodist Retirement Center and is open to all children regardless of race, religion, sex, or ethnic background. Our intergenerational program is one of the first of its kind in the state of Oregon and has been a place for generations to learn and grow together since 1985. Unique to our program is the opportunity for your child to build relationships with seniors as they engage in special daily activities. It is truly a relationship to be treasured.   At Willson House Child Development Center you will find children and seniors interacting daily. Children and seniors will be together singing songs, telling stories, making crafts or participating in annual events like our Tea Party or Carnival. Seniors also frequent our classrooms to say hello, lead projects, or serve as volunteers. No matter what the interaction may be, the young and young at heart will be learning and growing, together.

name: Creative Kids learning Center
details: Your children are the focus of our work, and everything we do at Creative Kids is geared towards helping them to learn, grow and develop into the people that they will become. In this day and age, you can’t be too careful. Our staff makes sure to identify parents and guardians of the children we care for. That way, we can ensure that each child is leaving with the appropriate adult. Additionally, our building features an alarm, so we know when someone tries to gain unauthorized access to our facility.

name: Iris Valley Learning Center
details:
Give your little ones the individual care and attention they need to expand their potential. Our kindergarten and preschool service offers this level of service to children ages 6 weeks to 12 years.

At Iris Valley Learning Center, we consider developing your child's potential our number 1 priority.

Our certified childcare center operates under the highest standards, provides all meals, and only employs trained and experienced teachers. This ensures your children are always safe, secure, and growing as a person when they are in our care.

name: West Salem Kids Care
details:
In 1994, owner Nancy Mueller began providing childcare in her home. As a mother of three, Nancy noticed the importance of providing childcare that felt personal and a place where parents were comfortable leaving their children. As her business grew, Mueller opened her first center in 2000 in the Westgate Shopping Center. She then moved her business across the street to a building she had specifically built for her center in 2005. Most recently, she opened a toddler center next to Annette’s Restaurant in West Salem in 2008. Parents and families keep coming back to WSKC as it provides quality childcare in a homey atmosphere.
 

Today, West Salem Kids Care (WSKC) prides itself in being affordable, engaging and a welcoming environment for children and their families. WSKC offers year round care for ages two to twelve years of age. We’d be more than happy to offer you a tour, feel free to give us a call today!

name: West Salem Kids Care Toddler Center
SCDC Yoshikai Latchkey Program
details:
SCDC strives to provide consistent environments in which children can discover their own capabilities and creativity.  Children are encouraged to develop self-discipline and a respect for others.  We maintain a nonsexist, non-racist setting for children's learning.  We believe it is important to enhance the development of a positive self-image in each child.  We accomplish this by providing warmth and nurturing in a growth-facilitating environment rich with opportunities to learn and discover. 

 

Our goal is to provide parents with an open, welcoming atmosphere to encourage and promote parent involvement and parent peace of mind.  We work to develop a one-to-one relationship with each child and parent, communicating to the child that they are "cared about" as well as "cared for".  We accomplish this by providing the best suited staff; qualified and dedicated to understanding the needs of the children and families.

Further, we seek to extend the children's environment beyond the classroom and into the community.
We are committed to advocating for all children, reaching out into the community and the state to advocate for high quality care for all families.
 

It is the policy of Salem Child Development Center that no person shall be discriminated against by reason of race, color, religion, disability, sex, age or national origin. SCDC accepts all children that are able to function within staff ratio and within the environments we maintain.
business hours: 6:45 am to 6:00 pm, Monday through Friday

name: Presbyterian Child Care Center and Preschool
details:
Presbyterian Child Care Center and Preschool (PCCCP) and the Learning Loft are extensions of the United Presbyterian Church of Albany. PCCCP welcomes children from six weeks to five years of age. We offer a variety of schedules and are available from 6:45 a.m. to 5:45 p.m., Monday through Friday. The Learning Loft is a school year program for 3- to 5-year-olds. This is a part time program running from 8:45 a.m. to 12:00 p.m. The Learning Loft offers two-, three- and five-day-a-week schedules. Both preschools focus on growth in socialization along with activities and classrooms that promote development in language, cognition and motor skills.

PCCCP and the Learning Loft are located in the heart of downtown Albany – only minutes away from any part of Albany. We also have a large parking lot with space reserved for PCCCP and the Learning Loft families.

United Presbyterian is an Equal Opportunity Provider and Employer.

name: Little Beavers Preschool
details: Little Beavers Preschool was founded by Al and Jan East in 1973. As OSU graduates and avid Beaver sports fans (Al played in the 1964 Rose Bowl) they knew the perfect name for their business had to be “Little Beavers”! The preschool was designed to provide quality childcare in a loving and home-like atmosphere.

name: OSU Child Development Center
details:
The Child Development Center is dedicated to discovering and communicating knowledge that contributes to the optimal development and well-being of young children and their families.

As part of Human Development and Family Sciences, the Child Development Center prepares professionals in early childhood development and family services; generates and transmits knowledge on family-focused early childhood programs through research, program development, and evaluation; and provides a developmental program of the highest quality for young children and their families that serves as a resource for the community-at-large.

name: Presbyterian Preschool and Child Care Center
details:
Presbyterian Preschool and Child Care Center provides, with no discrimination, all families an opportunity to receive affordable, quality education in an environment designed to nurture every child's emotional, social, creative and intellectual development.

Since 1969 & 1989, the preschool and child care center has been serving as an inclusive, community program and a Benton County United Way Agency.
business hours: Mon. - Fri., 7:00 am to 5:30 pm, January-December.

name: OCDC-Head Start Seasonal
details:
Our Mission
Oregon Child Development Coalition (OCDC) provides early childhood education, care and advocacy with unique and supportive services to enhance family growth and community success.
Our Vision and Values
We believe that every single child should be cared for, educated and loved. We prepare young children for success in school, which prepares them for success in life. We also support parents to help families learn and grow together, and we help families engage with their community.

name: Family Tree Relief Nursery - Lebanon
details:
Since inception in 2004 the Family Tree Relief Nursery has helped hundreds of children and their families to stay together as a family unit. Family Tree Relief Nursery is the only private, nonprofit organization in the area that provides these complete, integrated services: a therapeutic classroom and nursery, an outreach program and respite, home visitation, parent education and support. Multiple scientific longitudinal studies prove that integrating these services is effective in reducing recurrences of abuse and neglect in high-risk families by 80%

Family Tree Relief Nursery is a child abuse and neglect prevention program offering free services to low income families with children under the age of 6. We support family stability, and work with children and parents to minimize the need for children to removed from their home

name: Teaching Reasearch Child Development Center
details:
The major goal of our program is to provide a safe, secure and stimulating environment that meets the developmental and individual needs of all children. It is our goal to foster and instill the joy of learning within each child.

Program planning reflects the following basic beliefs:

• Children are active learners

• Each child is a unique individual

• Children learn in a developmental sequence

• Children learn through concrete and meaningful experiences that are relevant to their personal backgrounds and interests

• Parents are their child’s first teacher
business hours: 7:30 a.m. to 5:30 p.m. Monday through Friday

name: Nye Beach Montessori
details:
Nye Beach Montessori School is a special preschool and kindergarten for children 3 to 6 years of age.

Morning and afternoon classes are offered along with an after school childcare program. Before school childcare is also available.

An advanced kindergarten program is offered for children ages 4 1/2 ro 6 years of age.

We at Nye Beach Montessori are proud to provide an atmosphere where a child's physical and emotional security are safeguarded and where self esteem and natural curiosity are appreciated and nurtured.

name: Samaritan Early Learning Center
details:
Children are explorers, adventurers, learners and much more. They learn through play with adult support and encouragement. Samaritan Early Learning Center (SELC) offers hands-on learning experiences for children that reflect their developmental stage.
In 2011, SELC constructed a new learning center designed specifically to meet the developmental and educational needs of young children. With the new building, the children and families of the Lincoln City area have access to high-quality childcare in an environment ideally suited for early childhood education and development.

name: Central Coast Child Development Center
details: Central Coast Child Development Center is located in Toledo, Oregon. We accept children from the age of 6 weeks all the way up to fifth grade.

name: Eugene Montessori School
details:
Eugene Montessori School, founded in 1962, is a well-established program.

We have a loyal parent group, many of whom attended the school as children and who have fond memories of their time here.

In our Montessori preschool classrooms, every piece of equipment takes advantage of a child’s inherent desire to learn; to cater to the child’s sensitive period, as Maria Montessori described certain periods of intense interest in certain aspects of development.

Children may work in groups or on their own. They may sit at a table, or work at a rug on the floor. The classroom environment and teachers’ role are all carefully designed to enable each child’s self-paced growth.

details: KinderCare Learning Centers is committed to your child's future. name: Parkside Community Preschool
details:
Welcome to Parkside Community Preschool!  We hope to share a little bit about our program on these web pages, but we always welcome your visit - in person - for a more in depth look at our school.    

Parkside Community Preschool (known as Child Care Inc. until 2002), is a community based, 501 (c) (3) non-profit preschool and has been providing high quality care since 1967.  In 2004, we moved into a new facility built especially for children! 

Our bright and cheery school provides nurturing and developmentally appropriate care and education to children from ages 3 months to 6 years. 

Our classrooms include an Infant Room, Toddler Room, Preschool Room, and Pre K Room.  Age and developmental stage determine which room best meets the needs of your child.

With tuition based on a sliding scale, flexible scheduling, parent education, family support services, and a developmentally appropriate program geared toward children’s individual needs, we are unique and vital to the community. 

We nurture the growth and healthy development of each child, providing them with the opportunity to succeed.  We have been located in the Whiteaker neighborhood of Eugene, Oregon since 1967 and are the longest continuously running child care program in Lane County.

name: South Lane Family Relief Nursery
details:
The Relief Nursery model seeks to stop the cycle of child abuse and neglect through prevention and early intervention that strengthens parents, builds successful and resilient children, and preserves families by offering comprehensive and integrated support services.

Since 1994, the Family Relief Nursery has been serving families in the greater Cottage Grove area. In 1993, members of the Rotary and Kiwanis Clubs of Cottage Grove, Cottage Grove Healthcare Community, Relief Nursery of Eugene, local social service agencies, churches and community business leaders responded to two horrific cases of child abuse to bring Relief Nursery services to South Lane and North Douglas Counties. The Family Relief Nursery began serving children in August of 1994. Since then, hundreds of children and their families have received family strengthening services.

Substantial contributions from the Woodard Family Foundation, the Doyle & Donna Shepherd Foundation, Meyer Memorial Trust, Ford Family Foundation, Oregon Community Foundation, Siuslaw Valley Bank, US Bank, and the McKay Foundation were instrumental in building our permanent site which opened its doors in 1997. Continued financial support form the State of Oregon, Oregon Early Learning Council, Lane Country Commission on Children and Families, City of Cottage Grove, Cottage Grove Rotary Club, Children’s Trust Fund of Oregon and numerous local businesses and individual donors.

details:
we provide care for ages 6 wks to 10 yrs old
