name: Just Kids Early Learning Center
details:
Our goal has always been to provide the highest quality child care and early childhood education. We offer early childhood education in a fun and challenging learning environment.

Just Kids presents age-appropriate infant, toddler and preschool age activities that nurture and engage your child. We implement programs which offer hands-on experiences in a safe and secure learning atmosphere. We also offer a school age program for before and after school and no-school/break days!

Compare Just Kids to your traditional child care center and learn why so many parents have chosen Just Kids as their first choice in Coos County.

name: The Village Day Care
details:
You’ll give your children an excellent start in a happy, healthy environment with daycare and prekindergarten at The Village Daycare in North Bend, OR.

Whether you need full- or part-time daycare, we can meet your needs with flexible scheduling for any child ages 2½ to 12. Preschool is available full- or part-time for 3- and 4-year-olds and pre-kindergarten class for 4-year-olds.
You’ll rest easy knowing your child is being cared for by a well-trained, well-screened staff in a state-licensed and certified facility that has served the area since 1987.

We provide a healthy, stimulating environment for your child.

Securely located inside the Pony Village Mall, your child’s natural curiosity and urge to learn will be encouraged with our educational programs, toys and fun activities. After-school programs are available, with busing provided from 5 local schools.

You’ll find our state-certified facility clean and well-maintained, with up-to-date furnishings. Free meals are provided and special-needs children are accommodated.

name: Springfield Learning Tree
details:
Springfield Learning Tree is a Certified Childcare Center serving children ages 3 months to 10 years.
It has always been a goal of the Learning Tree to become a home away from home for all children who enter it. Nurturing, quality staff members and balanced educational programs promote children's healthy development. Communication between home and school, in both directions, is a key element of the Learning Tree's success.
We know that finding quality child care can be a challenge.  Not all day care institutions are alike.  Learning Tree Day School, located in Springfield, Oregon, offers both preschool and after-school programs that help foster growth and confidence in your child.  From infants to school-aged kids, we have a dedicated staff that enjoys teaching and nurturing your children.  Our school is clean, spacious, and engaging inside, combined with a modern outdoor playground area.   After-school care is available for kindergarten children, and we even bus to and from certain elementary schools in the Eugene-Springfield area.

name: Thurston High School Child Development Center
UCAN Head Start - Sutherlin
details:
UCAN Head Start Mission Statement
Partnering with families and communities to provide comprehensive developmental services to preschool children to increase social competency in school and life.

name: Kid's Akademy Christian Preschool
details: Here at Kid's Akademy, we believe that children are the most important and precious thing we have in our lives! They are the most valuable resource for the future. They need a firm foundation in their lives so they can grow to become effective, productive, caring, loving members of our society. What a child believes about himself or herself affects everything they do. They need to be assured of their worth as individuals, and this depends largely on the experience of love. A small child needs love that can be shown in practical ways. Kid's Akademy has been founded to give children and grown-ups hope for the future by helping them discover the meaning of the greatest gift of all – God's love.

name: Rogue Valley Family YMCA - Pre K
details: The YMCA Afterschool Program offers a family-centered, values-based program for kids at local elementary schools in the Medford, Phoenix-Talent, and Central Point school districts. The afterschool program is offered for children in kindergarten to sixth grade. Program components include physical education, homework assistance, art, science, recreation, character development and more. A healthy snack is provided every day. We work together with schools and families to help balance the needs of each individual child. Staff members are positive role models who ensure that children are given a unique mix of activities that focus on Developmental Assets and engage children in a variety of fun, learning opportunities. There is a balance between academic enrichment and playful, recreational activities. 15:1 maximum ratio.
business hours:
Monday to Friday: 4:30am to 10:00pm

name: Sarah Corson CC and Learning Center
details:
The child care center is a memorial in the name of Sarah Corson who died in Tokyo, Japan in 1997. This young woman was raised in the First Presbyterian Church and loved children. Her parents generously gave the initial funds to start this project. Many others contributed toward this $1.6 million dollar project. Sarah is pictured here with her two nieces, Mallory and Madeline. who are now in college.

The Sarah Corson Child Care & Learning Center has been in operation since 2001. The facility was purpose-built as a child care facility and is a state of the art, fully accredited child care institution providing quality childcare for for children as young as six weeks of age.

name: Coalition for Kids CC Center
details:
Coalition for Kids has been providing affordable, high quality child care in Grants Pass since 1994. Our mission is to prepare children to be ready to learn in kindergarten by providing developmentally appropriate child care and education in a safe, nurturing environment.  Our program is designed to address the whole child. It meets the needs, extends the interests, and provides for individual abilities at each developmental level. We are dedicated to creating a safe and stimulating environment where children can play, learn and laugh together. Our teachers help children grow and develop by using patience, love, and understanding – and we instill a strong sense of self-esteem and competence by nurturing each child. This developmentally appropriate approach offers each child the opportunity to:

    Develop a positive self-image by learning self-control, handling self-direction, and exploring independence within the guidelines of a safe and loving environment.
    Develop intellectually through specifically planned activities that will orient him/her to pre-academic skills in social interaction, reading, math and science.
    Develop fine and gross motor skills with daily activities that encourage the use of large and small muscles.

Activities at the center are geared to enrichment; those that will help a child develop socially, emotionally, mentally and physically while permitting them to achieve the independence they need.

name: Mustard Seed Preschool & Daycare
details:
Mustard Seed School was established in 1983 by volunteers from Hope, and quickly grew into an active pre-school and after-school program. Our primary goal is to provide learning experiences at age-appropriate levels that will meet the needs of the whole child, with academic, social, physical, and spiritual teachings – including moral values, self-discipline and Christian discipleship, strongly backed by the word of God.

In the mornings during the school year we have 3 Year Olds Pre-Kindergarten, and Kindergarten classes. In the afternoons we have a day-care program for children through age 10.

Klamath KID Center Inc
details:
The Klamath KID Center is a non-profit organization that strives to offer affordable, high quality child care, and education for children ages 6 weeks to 10 years. We provide quality and age appropriate activites with the goal in mind that each child leaves us ready and excited for Kindergarten. 
We provide transportation to and from school, and set aside time to assist students with homework as well as providing a safe environment for school age children after school and on school release days. We provide healthy meals and snacks for proper development.

Miss Muffett’s Learning Center, operated under the auspices of First Church of God, seeks to provide a warm, loving, caring and safe environment for children to grow and learn.
Miss Muffett’s serves children from many faiths and economic backgrounds. We strive to provide a nurturing and safe environment for these children as well as a solid Christian foundation while they are in our care.

details:
Tiny Hopefuls Mission Statement:
Tiny Hopefuls exists as a ministry of Hope Lutheran Church to provide Christian day care to the Klamath Falls community. We strive to provide a stable, safe, loving and Christian atmosphere for those children in need of care outside their home. The staff is the vehicle through which these mission objectives are carried out through their daily contact with the children and their families.

name: Triad School
details: Triad School was founded in the fall of 1995 as a non-denominational ministry of Bible Baptist Church. Bible Baptist Church desired to impact the Klamath Basin with the truth of Christ using the tool of a high quality preparatory school. Triad began with 4 teachers and 60 students. It has now grown to 230 students with a professional faculty of over 20. These students represent over 20 different churches, and 25% of them do not have a church home. Triad School has achieved the church's goal of a high quality preparatory school as evidenced by winning the highest award given to any school, the Oregonian Cup, the last 9 years in a row. This award is given for academic achievement and participation in a wide range of OSAA events, from football to band.

name: Growing Tree Children's Center
details:
The Growing Tree Children’s Center was established in 1979 as a non-profit childcare center serving children ages 6 weeks through Pre-Kindergarten. A Board of Directors comprised of parents and members of the business community governs the Center. The Board generally meets on the second Wednesday of each month and parents and community members are encouraged to participate.

The Center is certified by the Child Care Division of the State of Oregon. A yearly review is conducted, including an on-site visit. Growing Tree Children’s Center is in full compliance with the laws of the State of Oregon and applicable administrative rules.

The Growing Tree Children’s Center was specifically designed and built in 1987 as a childcare facility. Each classroom provides a wide range of activities and is furnished with age appropriate equipment and furnishings. Special features include observation windows in each classroom to watch your child in action, well-fenced playgrounds, a van equipped with booster seats for field trips, onsite laundry, separate staff lounge and a reception area for daily greetings and communication.
business hours: 6:00 am to 6:00 pm, Monday through Friday

name: Kid Works
details:
Each classroom will have Lesson Plans developing a weekly theme and daily events. Integrated within these weekly themes will be age appropriate math, science, pre-reading and writing activities as well as art projects, free play and outdoor time. Your child will have a number of activities to experience throughout the day.

Our classrooms will be a safe and encouraging environment that allows children to explore and learn. Each child will be given the opportunity to interact in a positive manner with peers and adults in one-on-one and group settings. The children will able to communicate their individual needs and wants in a variety of situations as well as apply reasoning capabilities in those situations. By placing the child in an environment that has a number of activities and projects, they will be developiing decision making skills by choosing different activities and completing tasks that accompany each activity.

Through play, the children will develop social skills such as language, cooperation, sharing, and negotiating. large and fine motor skills will also develop in daily activities such as paper cutting and physical education. We will strive to make sure each child has a successful learning experience in their classroom.

Daily schedules are flexible and provide for quiet and active play, indoor and outdoor activities, individual and group times, snacks, lunch, and naps.

name: The Montessori Center
details:
The Montessori Center is a private, independent school for children ages three through six with two locations in Bend, Oregon. We invite you to explore this website to discover what makes our school truly special. If you would like to schedule a visit, please contact us.

The mission of the Montessori Center is to prepare students to be life-long learners and responsible citizens of the world community. Through the use of Montessori methods and philosophy, an individualized approach in multi-age groupings encourages developmentally appropriate learning of academics, and social and life skills. All children are given the freedom – in a structured environment that is nurturing, child centered and supportive – to develop their gifts and pursue their interests.

name: Evergreen Academy
details:
Evergreen Academy was established in 2005 in Redmond, OR; and later expanded into Prineville in 2007. In Redmond they are conveniently located at the corner of 10th and Evergreen, across the street from what was Evergreen Elementary School. Prineville’s school is located on the corner of SW 4th and Elm, just four blocks South of Pioneer Park.

We are state certified and professionally trained to serve children’s fine motor, gross motor, cognitive, music, and movement needs. Along with these needs we are here to allow children to have fun and to provide a safe and trustworthy environment for parents to leave their children during the day.

Our Redmond facility serves children ages 2-9, and are open for all families in need of before and after school care. Our Redmond’s facility also offers a private Kindergarten class to their families. In Prineville we serve children ages 6 months-9 years and we work with the bus systems to serve a mid-day kindergarten transportation.

In August, 2014 we will celebrate our ninth anniversary in Redmond and our seventh anniversary in Prineville. We are so excited to say that in this time we have filled our facility with wonderful children and great staff. Our registry is very full, so please call to check availability. We couldn’t be happier with what we have been able to offer in both Redmond and Prineville.

Our Prineville facility is currently THE ONLY CERTIFIED CHILDCARE CENTER IN PRINEVILLE, and we are filling up quickly, so call now to reserve your spot.

name: Little Friends Christian Preschool and Child Care
details: Children are precious. It is our desire to create an environment for children that teaches the Christian values of honesty, respect, love and integrity along with developmentally appropriate learning and play activities. By recognizing different temperaments and learning styles, by challenging and encouraging, by nurturing and developing, and by working as a team, we will help them grow in their identity, self-esteem, and dignity.  The Seventh-day Adventist church has a long and rich history of education. We are committed to the training of young people for a productive life here and for a life with Jesus in heaven. The La Grande Adventist School built and moved to its present location in 1975. Because of declining enrollment and an increased need for the care of young children, it was decided in the spring of 2006 to use a classroom in the school and open a childcare center. Little Friends was open to childcare in the fall of that same year. In September of 2008 Little Friends added a preschool program. Currently the La Grande Adventist School is an educational opportunity for children ages 3 through 8th grade.

name: Monkey Tree Learning Center
details:
Locally and privately owned and operated, we are one of Columbia County’s largest state certified childcare centers, striving to keep kids happy and healthy and learning the fun way!  We opened Monkey Tree Learning Center in 2012 and are so happy that we did. We are open from 6 am-6 pm Monday through Friday and accept children 6 weeks through 12 years old.  You can call to schedule a tour between 8 am and 6 pm and one of our knowledgeable staff will give you a complete look into the care your child will receive. You can download enrollment forms or pick one up on your tour. On this website you can find classroom specific summaries so you know exactly what to expect on your child’s first day.

If you have any questions please feel free to contact us and we would be happy to help. We are very proud of our facility and encourage you and your child to join us for a tour.

name: Country Club Head Start Center
details: Country Club Head Start and Early Head Start serves children from birth to five years old, expectant moms and their families.   We currently have 2  preschool classes for  3-5 year olds and 1 class for 2 year olds.  We also have Early Head Start home based programs for pregnant moms and children from 0-3.   We welcome you to stop by our center, meet our staff, pick up an application or observe a classroom in action.

name: Rainbow Garden School
details:
Rainbow Garden School in an intimate, enriching, loving, educational and childcare facility located in the beautiful wooded natural environment of South Eugene, Oregon.  We are state-certified and privately owned and operated.  Our mission at Rainbow Garden is to provide a safe, interesting, nurturing and developmentally appropriate environment for children from infancy to school age.  We strive to educate the children as well as the parents to help guide and strengthen relationships in our world and to create independent self empowered people who may someday be the leaders of our cities, states, country, or world.

We have 2 different locations to better serve our local community.  The first location 1901 Pierce Street, began in June of 1997.  This location is a State Certified Child Care Group Home with a total of 16 children serving ages 2 to 6 years.

The second location is at 5310 Fox Hollow Road and is a State Certified Child Care Center serving 56 children from 8 weeks to 6 years in the lower building, and the upper building will provide before school and after school educational care for children 6 to 12 years of age.
business hours: 6:30 am to 6:30 pm, Monday through Friday

name: Head Start North Powellhurst (MHCC)
details: Child development and family support services available for pregnant women and families of children age birth – 5 who are low income and reside in East Multnomah County outside Portland Public Schools. Services include comprehensive preschool and child care programs, home visits, parent and child activities, health screenings, meals, transportation, opportunities to volunteer, and parent involvement activities. Some programs operate year-round.

details:

We pride ourselves in our ability to work with parents to offer the greatest flexibility in our schedule. We offer both after hours and Saturday care options as well.

name: The Jackson Club (at Jackson Middle School)
Neveh Shalom Foundation School
details: For 60 years, the Neveh Shalom Foundation School has embraced our youngest learners - sparking imaginations, instilling a sense of wonder, and providing the building blocks for the next generation of creative problem-solvers. The children who are part of the Foundation School legacy embrace an “anything is possible” approach to life where they are asked to wonder, encouraged to inquire, and participate in the process of bringing young families together for a life time of friendship and to dream BIG!

name: Foresight Learning Center
details:
Foresight Learning Center provides a clean, safe, healthy environment where every child can develop emotionally, physically, intellectually, and socially. We are committed to providing safety and security for all children. Foresight Learning Center encourages learning and growth through play in an environment designed so that children may strengthen muscles, build coordination, stretch their imaginations, and have fun.

 We believe that children should be allowed to grow at their own pace, and to learn in ways that help them become confident in themselves as learners. Our goal is to provide all of the children with a clean, safe, comfortable, and nurturing environment. Respect toward self, others and the environment will be emphasized. We believe in the value of both structured and non-structured activities. Structured activities will include the use of a preschool curriculum, regular reading times, circle times, arts and crafts, and musical activities. Outdoor play and center times are some of the more flexible activities we have. It is our goal to create an environment and program where the child’s natural desire to learn is stimulated through meaningful, appropriate, and playful learning experiences, one that meets the needs of each child as an individual.

 Another overlooked, yet crucial part of the learning process is the atmosphere of the educational facility. Children are VERY sensitive to the textures and sounds of their surroundings. We strive to showcase our students work and creations, and have lots of educational materials for them to gaze at. Many factors contribute to a welcoming atmosphere, such as:

 Lighting- Our facility has a well balanced mix of natural and artificial light. Shades are left open during the day so that the children don’t feel like they are trapped in a dark room all day.

Music- Background music makes all the difference in the world! At Foresight Kids music is a crucial fiber of our day. Sounds stimulate children in many different ways. We like to play lots of educational songs so that they are learning while they are singing.

Textures- Surrounding our facility we have pillows and blankets for the children to use at any time they would like. Children are especially sensitive to textures and we aim to make them as comfortable as possible!

Happy Staff- Making sure our staff is happy will result in happy kids and the eagerness to learn, develop, and grow.

name: Footsteps Preschool LLC
details:
"We recognize all children have different learning styles and we have been trained to meet each child's individual needs in a safe, nurturing envionment
 We encourage cooperative play and social interactions. Teaching children how to share, play, and be respectful of their peers and teachers. Our curriculum includes many book themed learning pages and fun activities that encourage literacy. 
We use Handwriting Without Tears curriculum to teach writing and we work closely wtih the School District  making sure the children are prepared to enter Kindergarten.
Footsteps Preschool
....leaving imprints on childrens lives"

NeighborImpact Head Start- South Bend
details:
Your child’s well-being matters to you and it matters to our communities. NeighborImpact’s Head Start program is here to help your family build skills and connect with resources to prepare your child to be successful in school. Our quality pre-school program offers much more than classroom learning. We partner with parents and caregivers to make sure that families have access to:

    quality pre-kindergarten education
    health and dental care
    family support
    nutritional meals

Every day, our Head Start program is proving to increase school readiness and provide children and families with the skills and resources they need be successful.

name: Head Start Merrill
details:

name: Early Head Start - Grants Pass Center
details:
Head Start is a federally funded program for preschool children from low-income families. Head Start Oregon Preschool Kindergarten Program (OPK) is the same program but is state funded. Children who attend Head Start participate in a variety of educational activities in stimulating settings to help them grow mentally, socially, emotionally, and physically. They also receive free medical and dental care, have healthy meals and snacks, and enjoy playing indoors and outdoors in a safe setting. Head Start helps all children succeed. Services are offered to meet the special needs of children with disabilities.

Early Head Start services are available for pregnant women, infants and toddlers in selected communities.

Head Start and Early Head Start works with the family, offering a sense of belonging, support services, and a chance to be involved in activities to help the whole family.

We assess children’s skills and abilities three times a year and use the data to plan for individual children and to make program improvements to ensure children are ready for kindergarten.

name: River Valley Child Care
details: The River Valley Preschool and Child Care Center provides a Christian environment for children from 8 weeks through 6 years of age where children are encouraged to grow and develop. Learning takes place as each child explores his or her environment, both individually and in groups. Individual differences in growth rates and styles of learning are respected. The goal is to promote a balance between the spiritual, intellectual, social and physical areas of development. The Preschool and Child Care Center was developed as a ministry within the church, but focuses on serving and loving the whole community.

name: Grace Episcopal Church Preschool
details:
Spiritual Foundation:Spiritual growth is an essential part of human growth. We strive to be a community which grows in its awareness of God’s unconditional and fathomless love for all of creation as we aspire to share that same love with one another. 
The Episcopal Tradition:Grace Episcopal Preschool’s commitment to the Episcopal tradition shapes us as a community of welcome and inclusion as inspired by the life and teachings of Jesus Christ. We are committed to upholding and respecting the dignity of every human being. Students of all faiths and traditions are welcomed. All are encouraged to seek clarity about their own system of belief and to live more fully and faithfully within them. We seek to provide age appropriate opportunities for our students to experience and explore spirituality, to learn by questioning, and to begin to understand that knowledge of the world and spiritual development are intertwined.

name: Lil Sprouts Academy
details: We are fast approaching our 4 year anniversary at Lil' Sprouts Academy! We're on to something BIG! A great place for your child to learn and grow! Serving children ages 6 weeks to 6 years (Infants, Toddlers, and Preschool Age), with a full time and drop-in spaces available. Take advantage of our punch card option for those times you need just a few hours of childcare, or look into our full time option with monthly tution. Lil' Sprouts Academy provides a fun, active, and encouraging environment for your sprout, focusing on healthy, positive experiences! $7 per Hour Drop-In or $5 per Hour Punch Pass Drop-in Fee. Open Monday - Friday from 7:30am - 5:30pm.  *Please call ahead for drop-ins.*

name: Mini -Hearts Preschool @ St Francis
details: Mini - Hearts Preschool is a play based program. We provide a safe and loving environment for our children to learn and grow.

name: Hillsboro Knowledge Beginnings
details: KinderCare Learning Centers is committed to your child's future. With our experienced staff and innovative programs unlike any other, we provide your child with an unsurpassed learning experience. Your child will discover that learning is fun, while making new friends and building strong relationships with teachers who partner with you in your child's education.

name: Early Learning Center (WPC)
details:
The Early Learning Center (ELC) is a nationally accredited by the NAEYC (National Association for the Education of Young Children) and state licensed part-day preschool program.  The Warner Pacific College ELC provides developmentally appropriate early childhood laboratory school for students in teacher education and related fields of study.

The ELC  also provides, under the guidance of a director and qualified teachers, a play-based, anti-bias, Christ-centered preschool program for young children in the community.

Early Learn Center Warner PacificBelieving that the family is the child’s primary environment of learning, the ELC offers opportunities for parent participation, education, and support.

name: Good Shepherd Lutheran School and Child Care
details: At Good Shepherd Lutheran School & Child Care, we approach each child as their own individual with their own personalities and one-of-a-kind needs. We will get to know your child and give them personalized care.  Our mission is to be a loving, nurturing home away from home.  Our child care staff is highly-qualified with both experience and education.  You can rest assured that your children are in wonderful hands.  Our Preschool, Pre-K and Full-Day Kindergarten teachers and their assistants are amazing!  They all have degrees in Early Childhood Education and are awesome at what they do.  We focus on early academics in a fun, engaging, hands-on environment. We offer a low teacher-child ratio, small class size and lots of individual attention.  We offer an excellent educational foundation for your child.  Many families have been sending their children to Good Shepherd for generations.  We are proud of our long history.  We even have several staff members that went to Good Shepherd when they were preschoolers.  We are that awesome, they just can't stay away!

name: Hand in Hand Early Learning Center at Zion
details: The purpose of Hand in Hand is to share the love of God by caring for infants and young children in a loving, nurturing manner while providing opportunities for their spiritual, physical, intellectual, social, emotional, and creative growth.  The qualified staff promotes Christian values and provides a safe environment for the children’s growth.  Children of all faiths are welcome at the center.
business hours: Monday through Friday – 7:30 a.m. to 6:00 p.m.

name: SCDC - Whitworth/Oakdale Merged Latchkey
details:
SCDC strives to provide consistent environments in which children can discover their own capabilities and creativity.  Children are encouraged to develop self-discipline and a respect for others.  We maintain a nonsexist, non-racist setting for children's learning.  We believe it is important to enhance the development of a positive self-image in each child.  We accomplish this by providing warmth and nurturing in a growth-facilitating environment rich with opportunities to learn and discover. 

 

Our goal is to provide parents with an open, welcoming atmosphere to encourage and promote parent involvement and parent peace of mind.  We work to develop a one-to-one relationship with each child and parent, communicating to the child that they are "cared about" as well as "cared for".  We accomplish this by providing the best suited staff; qualified and dedicated to understanding the needs of the children and families.

Further, we seek to extend the children's environment beyond the classroom and into the community.
We are committed to advocating for all children, reaching out into the community and the state to advocate for high quality care for all families.
 

It is the policy of Salem Child Development Center that no person shall be discriminated against by reason of race, color, religion, disability, sex, age or national origin. SCDC accepts all children that are able to function within staff ratio and within the environments we maintain.
business hours: 6:45 am to 6:00 pm, Monday through Friday

name: Cubby Preschool
details: Cubby Preschool opened at Newport High School in the fall of 1992 with a dual purpose: to provide childcare services to the community and to serve as a teaching lab for the high school students. We believe that children of all ages and abilities deserve the opportunity to develop a strong sense of self-worth and to receive the education and support needed for positive life decisions. Our goal is to strengthen, support and facilitate the development of healthy individuals. We value respect, responsibility, kindness and watching young children grow academically, socially and emotionally.

name: Taft High School - Preschool
details:
Taft High School is located in Lincoln City, Oregon overlooking the beautiful Pacific Ocean.
It serves students from Depoe Bay through Lincoln City to the Rose Lodge area.

name: King's Valley Preschool
details: So much learning takes place as children socialize & learn of others’ needs & feelings. Their play time is their work. We have fun ways to learn through field trips, cooking, guests, writing, cutting, pasting, planting, painting, studying outdoors & more. We use our imaginations to learn as we play!

name: Little Hearts Childcare Center
details:
Little Hearts Childcare in Rickreall (near Dallas) is a licensed registered Daycare and Childcare provider with openings currently for kids age 30 months to 12 years. We are located in the Rickreall school house - easy to access from both Highway 22 and Highway 99.

We have affordable rates for hourly, full-time and part-time, and we accept DHS funding as well. Childcare and Afterschool care for school age children is available as well – and afterschool bus service can be arranged for those enrolled in the Dallas School District.

We offer a structured, safe and enriching learning environment for your kids to play and learn in. Our children are fed breakfast, lunch, and 2 healthy snacks daily, and get a great headstart on their education with our interactive curriculum!
In addition to our classroom, our children have access to an outdoor play area with swings and slides, and a full-size indoor gym, so kids have access to fun and physical activity regardless of weather.
Our hours are Monday through Friday from 7:00 am to 6:00pm, and We have openings for Hourly, Full or Part time currently.

name: Kids Unlimited Summer Camp Jefferson
details:
Welcome to Kids Unlimited’s 14th Annual summer camp.   Kids Unlimited is a local non-profit youth development agency dedicated to providing empowerment opportunities.   Each, Kids Unlimited serve over a thousand youth through after school programs, enrichment clubs, mentoring, tutoring, sports and much more.   Our Main 1 Center for the Arts offers an ever evolving center of resources including art lab and gallery, technology center with integrated computers and film, Olsrud court basketball gyms and a commercial kitchen capable of hosting a variety of culinary classes and activities.

Our clinics and enrichment club structure provides campers the opportunity engage in many different activities, allowing for campers to try new things as well as choosing areas of their interest.  Camps are led by a staff of certified teachers, educational assistants, coaches, community members, youth development professionals and mentors. The staffing creates an environment committed to healthy learning, leadership, diversity and FUN!  Our staff to camper relationship allows for great relationship building, mentoring and small group dynamics.

This year’s summer academy is aimed at integrating technology and project learning through our weekly world themes which include activities in the arts, music, sport and dance.

name: Mary Jude Montessori Children's House
details: Mary Jude Montessori is preschool for children ages 3 to 5. Using the Montessori method to give your child a good foundation in education for life!

name: Lil' Cubs Preschool
details:
At Little Cubs Preschool we believe that children learn best through play. Equally important, we feel that a safe, nurturing environment that provides opportunities for children to learn and develop through activities which are age and individually appropriate is important as well. Our program provides a rich inclusive environment that promotes children's active exploration in all areas of development: physical, emotional, linguistic, aesthetic and cognitive. Little Cubs Preschool teachers show their respect for all children by encouraging them to think for themselves, make decisions, work toward their own situations, and express their own ideas and feelings.

Our program is child centered and flexible. We use a curriculum that is integrated and introduces meaningful projects that sparks the children's natural curiosities, interests, and enthusiasm. While introducing various topics and weekly themes, the children explore by hands-on experience within the classroom centers and circle time. We feel that learning opportunities for children are endless. And even though it may seem like they are just playing, in reality they are developing and polishing many skills needed for formal education.

We believe that a good parent-teacher relationship is necessary for maximum school success. Having open communication with parents is very important and critical for each child's success. This is done by continually keeping our daily communication connections open. Our open door policy allows parents the opportunity to come in anytime to help out in our classroom, visit, or observe their child whenever they would like to. We strive on offering a warm and welcoming environment to our preschool families, educators and community members while respecting the diversity of each and everyone's cultures and beliefs.

The knowledge our families share with us about their children is greatly appreciated. We use this information to enhance and enrich our program. We also seek input as well as feedback of any and all aspects of our program from our families.

name: Pacific Camps St. Helens
details: Mission Statement Pacific Camp's mission is to provide children with a safe environment and engaging programs, to provide their parents with a viable option for reasonable child care, and to provide a spiritual atmosphere where the children and their families will develop a personal relationship with Jesus Christ.
business hours: Monday - Friday from 7:00 a.m. to 6:00 p.m.

name: Berry Bright Preschool
details:
We are Christian teachers who believe that each child is a gift from God. It is our desire to work with parents to provide a positive, first-school experience. We offer a safe, fun environment for learning social skills and building friendships.

For our curriculum, we use a variety of methods and materials, many of which are adapted or custom designed for our program. We have adopted "Spell to Write and Read", as our phonics program. This program focuses on teaching all the sounds of the letters and then sounds of letter combinations, known as phonograms. We also use manipulatives, art projects, activities, and worksheets to teach many other things, such as patterning, number recognition, colors, writing, and science.

name: Holcomb On-Site Program (Oregon City Extended Day)
OCDC Clackamas County - Mulino Site
details:
Our Mission
Oregon Child Development Coalition (OCDC) provides early childhood education, care and advocacy with unique and supportive services to enhance family growth and community success.
Our Vision and Values
We believe that every single child should be cared for, educated and loved. We prepare young children for success in school, which prepares them for success in life. We also support parents to help families learn and grow together, and we help families engage with their community.

name: Rivergate Adventist Elementary
details:
Rivergate Adventist Elementary
Mission Statement and Values
The Rivergate staff is determined to provide our students with a safe physical and emotional environment where they can develop a relationship with God and acquire an education that will instill in each of them Christian values, high self-esteem, high academic achievement, and responsible behavior.

name: Estacada Day Care and Preschool Learning Center
Sweetpea's Early Learning Center
details: We want to let you know that it is our desire for every child who enters the doors of Sweetpea’s to be happy here. Our goal is to provide a safe, secure and caring environment for your child that fosters physical, social, emotional, and cognitive development. Our hope is to develop a partnership, between home and school, which benefits the development and growth of your child.

name: Beavercreek On-Site Program (Oregon City Extended Day)
Rising Star Chinese School
details:
We are a small Bilingual and Reggio Inspired preschool community (age 3-6 potty trained) located inside Beaverton First United Methodist Church Preschool Room. Teacher to child ratio is 1:8. We do walking field trip weekly to near by park, stores or city library.

Our Mandarin Chinese and English program is state certified and endorsed as ECO-HEALTHY Child Care Program and we serve healthy snacks.

Your child is welcome to enroll anytime throughout the year based on the availability. We have periodically open houses and private tour is also available upon request.

name: Bethany on site, Bethany Childcare Inc.
Tiny Blessings Montessori Preschool Child Care
The Doctors Luce
details: This daycare center integrates proven educational systems to maximize school performance with the piece of mind of oversight by board-certified Pediatricians

name: Children's Time Preschool
details: Every child is unique and we believe that success and growth come from encouragement and praise. Our teachers focus on building every child’s self esteem and confidence through positive feedback and rewards. We nurture their natural strengths. A child see’s the world around them with wonder and awe, we believe in encouraging their natural curiosity.

name: Twin Oaks Child Development Center
details: Twin Oaks Child Development Center strives to provide caring, developmentally appropriate care. We offer a variety of scheduling options and welcome children 5 and younger. Give us a call today to see our facility and meet our teachers.

name: Westside Montessori International
details: We are an early childhood education center backed by more than 15 years of Montessori experience that is founded on the vision of "Equipping the Next Generation" fostered through the value of training in the formative years to allow them to reach their full potential in all areas and stages of life from infancy to their adult years. Our school is focused on the ages 2.5 - 6 and implements the Montessori Approach to education. It is a teaching philosophy that uses individualized and independent approach in a child-sized and prepared environment with the use of multisensory/didactic materials that provide the children the best opportunity for their natural and innate capability to work, learn, develop creativity and curiosity through questions, explorations, experimentations and investigation led by their inner directive and interest. Working in our newly built facility, our Montessori trained and certified staff will support and guide each child compassionately, joyfully and enthusiastically in achieving their learning goals and developmental milestones.

name: Little Lambs Too
details: Since 2007, Little Lambs, Too has served and educated our early learners in all areas of their development: academic, physical, social, emotional and spiritual. We are a Christian Montessori school, not affiliated with any particular church or denomination. We invite you to schedule a tour today so you can see what we are all about!

name: Bethlehem Lutheran Preschool
details:
Bethlehem Preschool has been serving the Aloha community for more than 25 years. Our families come from Beaverton, Tigard and Hillsboro.  Our program is strong. Our staff is experienced. Our purpose is clear – we want to share Jesus with children.  Our facilities are first rate. Preschool is a vital contributor to your child’s growth and development. Children at these ages are like wet concrete. They can be shaped and molded and their experiences shape them for the rest of their lives. Check out our program on the pages of this website. Drive by and look at our campus. Call Brenda in our office and come for a personal look. Meet our teachers. We are here to serve you and your family with an experience that will help your child grow in body, mind and spirit. Come and find out how.

We offer a three-day-per-week program (Monday, Wednesday, Friday) for 4-year olds and a two-day-per-week (Tuesday, Thursday) program for 3-year olds.  A daily “lunch bunch” is offered from 11:30 to 1:00 pm every day of the week.  Call or visit for more information.

name: Kids Of The Kingdom - Lutheran Church
details:
Kids of the Kingdom Christian Preschool and Kindergarten, located in Beaverton, Oregon, welcomes your child to grow in God's love and learn about the world around them. We believe all children are precious gifts of God, created in His image and loved unconditionally by Him.

Our teachers have created classrooms where children can learn and create at their own pace. Children will:

    Learn to be good stewards of God's natural world through observation and care of creation
    Learn respect for themselves and others through play
    Learn to cooperate and socialize during free choice, small group time and outdoor play
    Learn songs, finger plays, rhythm, and movement
    Listen to and act out stories using magnet boards, masks and puppets
    Actively participate at Pastor's Chapel time through interactive stories and songs
    Create art through various media such as paint, clay, and collage
    Recognize letters, letter sounds, numbers, shapes, and colors

We feature small class sizes offering stimulating learning environments that will engage your child. We also have a large playground surrounded by wetlands for the children to enjoy nature.

name: Kid's Discovery Academy
details:
Kids Discovery Academy is an academically-focused and play-based child care and early childhood education center.  Our team of staff and teachers are committed to providing an environment rich in the things your child needs - individual attention, emotional support and encouragement, exciting activities and lots of opportunities to discover and explore the world around them. 
 
        We believe that children learn best when given the opportunity to experience learning through play, exploration and self-expression.  And families do best when they are confident their child is safe, cared for and developing to their fullest potential while away from home!

name: Faith Bible Christian School
details:
Ours is a mission of the heart ...

We're dedicated to building academic excellence, developing Christ-like character and equipping our students to serve others.
_____________________________________
The Country Fair & Auction in March proved to be a tremendous success! Our thanks to each of you for your generous support and kind words as we started what appears to be a new tradition at Faith Bible Christian School. We had three main goals—(1) to build community, (2) raise some additional funds for the school, and (3) provide an event where God’s glory would be evident. From our perspective, we reached each of our three goals! The funds raised will help jump-start our STEM program and will go directly to FBCS programs.

details:
Creative Minds Learning Centers (CMLC) was founded by the Mckinster family in 1997 due to an overwhelming demand for high quality preschool programs.

Creative Minds operates seven eco-friendly and certified preschools and child development centers in the Portland, Metropolitan Area. Our schools are proud to offer media-free educational and healthy environments with the children's interests and parent's needs in mind. Creative Minds’ mission is to provide a progressive preschool program that helps foster life-long learning and developmental growth.

Creative Minds Learning Centers have been designed to encourage children to explore their interests in a creative and artistic setting. Certified with the State of Oregon and members of NAEYC, OAEYC, Oregon Environmental Council and other Early Childhood organizations, CMLC schools provide a progressive and positive environment for children, staff and families. Creative Minds has also been recognized as members of QRIS, selected as one of 25 Oregon Program of Quality schools and continues to be a leader in the Early Childhood Education field.

Our philosophy is to enrich children's lives with creative arts and accredited educational materials while developing self esteem, confidence and a sense of independence. While there are many approaches and "labels" for teaching young children, Creative Minds schools focuses on the basis of early childhood development being "trichotomized" into a trio of goals: (1) social/emotional development and (2) intellectual development and (3) the acquisition of meaningful and useful academic skills. Children are capable and willing to learn and naturally can begin to read at Pre-Kindergarten grade. It is our duty to guide the children during the day in a structured setting. The children depend on the security of a daily routine and come to school excited to see their friends and teachers.

name: Our Children's Place
details:
We believe that each child is a unique individual who needs a secure, caring, and stimulating atmosphere in which to grow and mature emotionally, intellectually, physically, and socially. It is our desire as educators and caregivers to help children meet their fullest potential in these areas by providing an environment that is safe, supports risk-taking, and invites a sharing of ideas. There are three elements that we believe are conducive to establishing such an environment: (1) The teacher/caregiver acting as a guide; (2) The child's natural curiosity to direct his/her learning is encouraged; and (3) Promotion of respect for all things and all people. 
>
>     Providing students access to hands-on activities and allowing adequate time and space to use materials that reinforce the lesson being studied creates an opportunity for individual discovery and construction of knowledge to occur. Equally important to self-discovery is having the opportunity to study things that are meaningful and relevant to one's life and interests. Developing a curriculum around student interests fosters intrinsic motivation and stimulates a passion to learn. One way to take learning in a direction relevant to student interest is to invite student dialogue about the lessons and units of study. Given the opportunity for input, students generate ideas and set goals that make for much richer activities than we could have created. 
>     Helping children to develop a deep love and respect for themselves, others, and their environment occurs through an open sharing of ideas. When the voice of each child is heard, an environment evolves where students feel free to express themselves. We continuously encourage such dialogue. We believe children have greater respect for their teachers, their peers, and the lessons presented when they feel safe and sure of what is expected of them. In setting fair and consistent rules initially and stating the importance of every activity, students are shown respect for their presence and time. In turn they learn to respect themselves, others, and their environment. 
>
>     One of our hopes as educators/caregivers is to instill a love of learning in our students, as we share our passion for learning with them. In our competitive society it is important for students to not only receive a solid education, but to work with someone who is aware of and sensitive to their individual needs. We are such people and will always strive to be the best educators/caregivers that we can be.
>

name: Oswego Playschool
details:
Founded by a group of forward-thinking parents committed to creating a cooperative school, Oswego Playschool shared space in a church for the first two years of operation, opening its doors to 20 wide-eyed youngsters in 1953.

By 1955, the growing enrollment made it obvious that a permanent home for the school was needed and in the summer of that year charter members John and Betty Gray donated the lot and materials to construct a new facility - from the ground up. Designed by noted Northwest architect Van Evera Bailey with the needs of a child in mind, all construction was done by the parents of the school.

Because the building and grounds were designed as a preschool from the start, Oswego Playschool includes built-in features and play apparatus unique to the area's preschools. In addition, the hundreds of toys and teaching aids accumulated through sixty years of play have become a priceless learning resource benefiting Oswego Playschool children to this day. Oswego Playschool is still one of the few cooperative preschools in Oregon that own their own facility, and the benefits are bountiful.

Oswego Playschool is a member of Parent Child Preschools of Oregon (PCPO), an organization consisting of approximately 60 parent cooperative preschools in Oregon. They provide parent education, family enrichment programs, training for school officers, teacher programs, and act as a resource for cooperative preschools.

name: Oregon City Preschool
details:
We accept children of all colors, race and creed at their own level of development.  We strive to create a comfortable learning environment.  Most of our learning is done through play (songs, games, free exploration and discussion).  We strive to give the children an opportunity to establish life long social skills.

Children develop and mature greatly in preschool years. At this age children need to form social contacts with others of their own age. Preschool provides the opportunity for group play with friends under careful supervision and conditions not possible at home. Our school provides a physical environment set up to scale for a child’s size and level of maturity trying to eliminate some of the feelings of frustration that comes from living in a world set up for adults. Our teacher works with each child according to his/her needs. She understands the child’s point of view, addresses any problems and desires.

details:
Welcome to the digital home of Scappoose Adventist School (SAS), a place of belonging!  Established in 1935, SAS is a Pre-Kindergarten-8th grade elementary school that is internationally networked, with over 120 schools in the Pacific Northwest alone, and impacts the lives of over 1.2 million students world-wide.

Adventist education is much more than the academic excellence for which it is renowned. It also fosters a faith in God, respect for others, independent thinking and moral integrity. It is education based on the development of the whole person ─ building mind, body, spirit and community one student at a time.

We invite you to make an appointment and take a tour, visit with classroom teachers and meet the principal and discover what many families are learning: Scappoose Adventist School is a safe place for young people to discover, grow and soar on their journey of learning to making this world a better place—it’s the place where you belong!

name: KinderCare - Hillsboro 1121
details: KinderCare Learning Centers is committed to your child's future. With our experienced staff and innovative programs unlike any other, we provide your child with an unsurpassed learning experience. Your child will discover that learning is fun, while making new friends and building strong relationships with teachers who partner with you in your child's education.

name: Roots&Wings Montessori School
details: The Montessori philosophy and scientific method of education is based on facilitating a safe, nurturing, and enriched environment for the child to discover the sheer joy of learning through self-paced exploration of specifically designed educational materials. The teachers give each child individualized lessons after assessing their interests and sensitive period of learning. The multi-age class allows younger children to also learn from their older peers; this not only makes learning much more effective, but also brings order to the classroom. This 100-yr old technique was devised by Italy’s first female medical doctor, Dr. Maria Montessori, and has been accepted around the world.

name: Hawthorn Farms Learning Years Day School
details: Learning Years Day School at Hawthorn Farm welcomes your inquiry into our excellent day school program for children 6 weeks to 10 years of age. Our Hawthorn Farm School is located in the Hawthorn Farm Industrial Park where many of our families work and live nearby. Our school is filled with very talented and dedicated teachers who work hard to provide your child with a safe and nurturing environment. Sandi Bailey, the Director of the center, is celebrating her 25th year at Learning Years in 2001! Tina McDaniel and her husband, Joe, own and operate the Hawthorn Farm School. Tina is a 1988 Graduate of Portland State University and has been a full-time staff member since 1983. Together, Sandi & Tina strive for a daily goal of excellence in early childhood education, a clean school, a friendly staff, and a safe and loving environment for children. Our philosophy is simple, but so important, and serves as a fundamental basis of our program. Although we offer a fantastic and age-appropriate preschool program and many extra programs to enrich and satisfy the children's natural curiosity, we feel that the stability of the staff and the loving environment that they experience far outweighs any other aspect of our program. When you enroll your child at Learning Years, we hope to become not just your "child care" provider, but also a part of your extended family! Come in for a tour at any time. We would love to show you around!

name: The Goddard School - Hillsboro
details: The Goddard School uses the most current, academically endorsed methods to ensure that children have fun while learning the skills they need for long-term success in school and in life. Our talented teachers also collaborate with parents to nurture children into respectful, confident and joyful learners.

name: Hillsboro Parent Preschool
details: Hillsboro Parent Preschool is a community that inspires children’s creativity, wonder and love of learning. In this safe, nurturing environment, preschoolers are valued and respected as they build a foundation for future learning. Children are encouraged to develop a stronger sense of self, learn problem solving skills, and build relationships. Active parent participation allows families to feel connected and valued for their capabilities and differences as they gain insight into child development, guidance, discipline, and learning styles.

name: Head Start of Yamhill Co. McMinnville Center
Kids on the block/Sue Buel
details:
The Kids on the Block After-School Enrichment program is collaboratively provided by the City of McMinnville Parks & Recreation Department and McMinnville School District #40 in partnership with the KOB Inc. Foundation.

Our Mission is to provide safe, fun, enriching after-school opportunities that help build successful kids. The KOB After-School Enrichment program currently serves more than 800 students.

KOB After-School Enrichment is open to all 1st through 5th grade students who attend the six public elementary schools in McMinnville School District, including Sue Buel, Columbus, Grandhaven, Memorial, Newby, and Wascher Elementary.

Coordinated by a professional Program Manager and on-site program supervisors, the KOB After-School Enrichment program is staffed by energetic and fun recreation leaders with training and experience in youth development.

The KOB After-School Enrichment program includes a healthy snack, 30 minutes of Homework Help and reading time, and 3 recreation enrichment activity stations: Creation Station (arts, crafts, music, writing, drama), Fit Zone (sports, games, healthy lifestyles, nutrition), and STEM & Strategy (science, technology, engineering, math, group problem solving).  KOB also includes numerous special enrichment opportunities such as Outdoor School, Science Week, Global Youth Service Week, Artists-in-Residence, and numerous special guests and assemblies.
- See more at: http://www.mcminnvillekob.org/after-school-program/#sthash.Wwun8QL1.dpuf
business hours:
Tuesday – Friday 9 a.m. to 9 pm.
Saturday  9 a.m. to 6 p.m. - See more at: http://www.mcminnvillekob.org/contact-us/#sthash.SLGMBok0.dpuf

name: Chehalem Parks and Recreation District CARE Program
Vermont Hills - North Plains
details: VHFLC is dedicated to enriching the lives of children through a secure and warm environment that promotes self-esteem.  Our program involves each child in his/her various developmental stages.  We support the family as it encourages each child’s special worth.

name: Neah-Kah-Nie Preschool
details:
Welcome to the webpage for Neah-Kah-Nie Preschool.  We are located on the same property as the District Office, on 3rd Street in Rockaway Beach.  We are able to serve up to 40 students, between our morning and afternoon sessions of preschool.   We are currently staffed with one licensed teacher and one instructional assistant in each of our two sessions of preschool.  This enables us to maintain a teacher to student ratio of no more than 1:10.

The learning space at Neah-Kah-Nie Preschool is warm, spacious, and engaging.  We have a well-equipped classroom that offers our students opportunities to explore, play and develop important social, cognitive, and physical skills.  We also have a fenced playground, with developmentally appropriate equipment for young children to enable outdoor play.  For those days when outdoor recreation is not an option, we have tricycles and scooters that can be ridden in the breezeway.
business hours:
8:15 am to 11:15 am, Monday through Friday
11:15 am to 2:15 pm, Monday through Friday

name: Mrs. Tami's Daycare & Preschool
details: Here at Mrs Tami's Daycare & Preschool, LLC we provide a developmentally age appropriate curriculum. Children explore social & emotional interaction, fine motor skills, language skills and learn to use a creative mind for growing and learning. We offer a safe, loving and learning experience for children 6 weeks to 12 years old. We have certified teachers and knowledgeable aides. All staff are enrolled in the central background registry, infant first aid/cpr certified and current food handlers card.

name: Champions - Middleton Elementary
details: Champions has a great solution for busy working families: activities that combine fun and learning, together with the safety and convenience of a high-quality program right inside your school. Champions offers a variety of group and individual activities designed to keep your child exploring and growing. From art, dramatic play, math and science to problem-solving, language, motor skills and more, we help your child continue learning and developing essential life skills – whether school is in session or not.

name: Sherwood Health & Wellness B/A School Program
SUN Community School - Robert Gray Middle
details:
SUN Community Schools in Multnomah County (link is external) are full-service neighborhood hubs where the school and partners from across the community come together to make sure kids and families have what they need to be successful - in school and in life.

SUN Community Schools mobilize and strategically organize community resources to provide:

    Strong core instructional program
    Educational support and skill development for youth and adults
    Enrichment and recreation activities
    Family involvement and support
    Social, health and mental health resources
    Family and community events

At SUN Community Schools, the collective efforts of youth, parents, businesses, faith communities, libraries, and community organizations create a network of supports that ensure academic success, family self-sufficiency, and economic prosperity. SUN Community Schools are open to all ages, preschool to seniors, with a focus on students in the immediate school community.

SUN Community Schools are the school-based service delivery sites for the SUN Service System, a broader system of community-based care and support for children and their families.

name: Grandma's Place Annex- Clark Family Annex
details:
Family owned Grandma's Place Child Development Centers are committed to valuing individual families and their children’s unique needs and learning styles by providing loving, developmentally appropriate care and education in a positive, professional environment.

Our centers offer The Creative Curriculum. This program model allows your child to choose and study areas that (s)he is interested in. Using guided free choice, teachers use these opportunities to work on skills. In this way we are able to teach your child while (s)he is playing in areas that spark interest.

details:

name: Kenilworth Community Preschool
details: We support one another with compassion seeking to model fairness and peaceful resolution. We provide an affirming atmosphere to promote each child's growth physically, spiritually and emotionally. The diversity and traditions of each family are honored. Kenilworth Community Preschool welcomes students of any race, color, national origin or religion.

name: Whole Child Montessori Center
details: We invite you to explore our website to learn more about Montessori education and Whole Child! Since 1983, Whole Child Montessori Center of Portland, Oregon has offered children 3-6 years of age the opportunity to explore and embrace natural learning under the guidance of highly qualified, dedicated teachers. We honor the importance of the collaborative spirit and are not simply a preschool, but a vibrant community of children, parents and educators.  Our school consists of two beautiful and carefully appointed mixed-age classrooms complemented by a lush children’s garden located in the Woodstock neighborhood of SE Portland (map). We draw children and families from all four quadrants of the city with our outstanding reputation for providing a professional, respectful and nurturing environment dedicated to authentic Montessori practice (Association Montessori Internationale/AMI).

name: The Montessori House
details:
The Montessori House’s mission is to provide a nurturing environment for the holistic development of children, six months to six years of age. Each child is recognized as a unique individual, as well as an integral part of our community.

The Montessori House strives to guide the child along his or her own individual path of construction while nurturing the social responsibility needed to live within a cooperative community. It is our goal to provide an environment that recognizes the authentic nature of the child.

The Montessori teacher (guide) is trained to prepare the environment with activities that match the laws of development of the child and promote the children’s needs and desire for independence, language acquisition, social interaction, movement, and cognitive stimulation, as well as personal and environmental care.

We strive to have a strong, supportive, and vibrant learning community. We hope to create lasting relationships with the children and their families that are built on trust and mutual respect.

details: VHFLC is dedicated to enriching the lives of children through a secure and warm environment that promotes self-esteem.  Our program involves each child in his/her various developmental stages.  We support the family as it encourages each child’s special worth.

name: Head Start - (PPS) James John School
details: Portland Public Schools Head Start serves 844 low-income three and four year old children and their families. The Goal of Head Start is to build social competence in children. Social competence is the child’s everyday effectiveness in dealing with both his/her present and later responsibilities in school and life. We recognize parents as the primary educators in the life of their child. We provide quality comprehensive services that are family focused, including education, social and emotional development, physical and mental health, and nutrition. We offer both half day and extended day classrooms that operate September through June.

name: We Village - Pearl
details: Need a few hours to get things done? Or to do some quiet shopping? Need childcare a few days a week, but not everyday? Have an important meeting & no-one to watch the kids? Looking forward to a romantic evening with your partner? School holidays? WeVillage Drop-in Childcare has Portland & Hillsboro covered. We offer drop-in daily & hourly childcare, with beautiful, modern facilities right smack in Portland’s Pearl District and at Orenco Station in Hillsboro (right on BLUE Max line).

name: The Milt and Cissi Carl Parent-Child Preschool
details: Milt and Cissi (z”l) Carl founded our school at the Shaarie Torah synagogue to serve the Jewish community with a quality co-operative preschool. Their belief was that a cooperative preschool would allow parents to be included in their child's first school experience while incorporating Jewish values and teachings within the children's play.  The Carl prepares children for kindergarten while providing a background in Judaic history and holidays. Children form the Carl come from a wide range of Jewish households, from families who are very observant to families with Jewish roots who are just reconnecting to their Judaism for the first time.  We also have many children from various other religious backgrounds, which we welcome and brings a wonderful diversity to our school.  The children visit Rabbi Zuckerman in his office twice a month to hear stories, share Judaic experiences and a treat.

name: Jump for Joy Christian, LLC
details:
At Jump for Joy Christian Early Learning Community, the joy of learning is cultivated in everything we do. We embrace the best practices in Early Childhood Education. Our committed teaching staff collaborate to ensure each classroom environment is child inspired and fosters a joy for learning.

We are open year-round and offer part week (as few as 2 days a week) and full week care between 7:30am and 5:30pm daily.

    Our Learning Community supports learners as young as 6 weeks old up to Kindergarten Ready (age 6)
    Eco-friendly diapers are included in tuition for all children under 2 years of age
    Am Snack, Pm Snack and Lunch is also included in tuition for children 12 months and older. Organic fruits and vegetables, hormone free milk and healthy main dishes made by Fresh and Local are served
    Spanish is spoken in all classrooms
    The RIE and Reggio Philosophies inspire our Teaching Team in our learning spaces.

name: YMCA - Vernon
details:
YMCA school-age child care program at Vernon School provides opportunities and experiences that stimulate a child’s physical, social, intellectual, and emotional development. Structured activities including enrichment clubs, arts and crafts, literacy programs and homework support are offered throughout the day in order to develop leadership skills, social interaction, teamwork, and to build self-esteem.

Programming times are from 6:30 AM until school starts and from school release until 6:00 PM weekdays including full day programming from 6:30 AM until 6:00 PM for in-service days. Winter Break and Spring Break locations to be announced.

name: YMCA - Faubian
details: We work closely with the SUN program at the school. We also provide care for students who attend Woodlawn Elementary School. Students who attend Woodlawn are transported via school bus, provided by the Portland School District.

name: Hancock Street Preschool, Inc
details:
We are a cooperative preschool for three and four-year-old children located in Northeast Portland at Hancock & 16th Ave. We utilize facilities inside the Westminster Presbyterian Church, where we have four classrooms for the kids to explore, banks of windows that fill the rooms with light, and a beautiful enclosed courtyard where the children can safely express their exuberance. Our secure building is handicap accessible.

We have two classes: the three-year-old “Red Class” meets Tuesdays and Thursdays, and the four-year-old “Blue Class” meets Mondays, Wednesdays, and Fridays. Both classes are held from 9:30 AM to noon. There are 18 students in each class. After-school Spanish and yoga classes are also available.

Since 1984, Hancock Street Preschool (HSP) has been inspiring the wonder and joy of life-long learning for children and adults. We believe that children are curious, competent individuals. We understand that children are capable of constructing knowledge through play and meaningful real-world experiences. We believe in the importance of relationships and community, and we value the uniqueness of each child and family.

At HSP, the teacher and families work together to create an environment that facilitates play for deeper interaction and inquiry. We encourage young children’s play by valuing their eagerness to learn, by providing them with space and time, by paying attention to their spontaneous interests, by presenting new inquiries and exploration activities, and by offering support as they problem solve. Children are compelled to connect with one another and are genuinely fascinated with one another’s words, ideas and actions. We encourage and respect those social connections and the resulting growth in social skills.

name: The Portland Montessori School
details:
The Portland Montessori School, formerly Providence Montessori School, has over a 50-year history of educating Portland’s children according to the Montessori educational method. Located in Northeast Portland, just one block north of East Burnside Street, our campus offers a convenient location for many Portland-area neighborhoods.

We currently serve approximately 150 students with our thriving primary program for ages 2 1/2 through 6 and our growing elementary program for grades 1 through 6. We also offer before and after care as well as holiday and summer camps. Our school hours are from 8:30 AM to 3:00 PM, with before and after care hours extending the day from 7:00 AM to 6:00 PM Monday through Friday.

Mary Hicks serves as the Head of School. During her tenure, she has expanded the elementary program to include upper elementary grades. She also helped shepherd the school’s smooth and successful transition to independent, non-profit status. The school officially became The Portland Montessori School on January 1, 2013.

Our guides, head of school and most staff members are certified by the Association Montessori Internationale (AMI) to ensure we guide our students using internationally recognized standards of educational excellence.
business hours: 7:00 AM to 6:00 PM Monday through Friday

details:
The YMCA at Arthur Academy Portland currently offers a variety of fun activities that help children develop their academic and social skills in an enriching atmosphere. Educational and recreational opportunities are offered in an environment that allows children to develop at their own pace, working independently and in a group setting. A strong emphasis is placed in our daily programming on the YMCA five core values of love, respect, honesty, responsibility, and service.

In-service care for Arthur Academy may happen at Arthur Academy or at Vestal Elementary.

name: Little Hands Garden School
details: Our goal is to foster in children the belief that school is a place to have fun, socialize, create, be active, and learn.  A positive attitude towards school created in the early years benefits children throughout their lives. Because children in the early years learn though play, we offer a play-based curriculum filled with dress-up costumes, play houses, play kitchens, and plenty of easily accessible props for kids to use in their imaginary play.  Children have time for free play, exposure to a variety materials, plenty of playmates, and teachers ready support their creative process. We are interested in the way children organize their world when adults step back and allow them to make messes and interact with their environment in their own way. Children at our school will get messy, get muddy, get wet, and get covered in sand in the sand pit when they want to. They will run some, scream some, dance some, and laugh often! A child's brain is at it's highest level of functioning during play, which makes play the real foundation for learning during the early years.

name: Peninsula Childrens Center-Maryland
details: Our Children. Our Community. Growing Together. Peninsula Children’s Learning Center’s mission is to provide high-quality, affordable childcare and education as well as family support programs that contribute to the vitality of North and Northeast Portland. Peninsula’s unique economically and racially integrated program is built on a foundation of positive relationships with and between diverse children and families. We provide full-day, 2-day, 3-day and 5-day, year-round education and child care, and we are committed to the social, intellectual and emotional development of every child.

name: Discovery Gardens-Kenton
details: At Discovery Gardens, we pledge to provide a safe, enthusiastic and non-intimidating learning environment, where the number one focus is on meeting the individual needs of each child.

name: Trillium Preschool
details:
Mission
Our mission is to create an academically rigorous constructivist learning environment that engages each student’s unique spirit and intellect, develops creative, critical thinking skills, and cultivates compassionate, active citizens.
Vision
Our vision at Trillium is to create an inclusive, equitable and intellectually rigorous culture where knowledge is built through experience.  Students and staff are expected and empowered to reach their full potential.  It is our goal to be an innovative model for other schools, and a leader within the larger educational community.
We cultivate critical thinking and participatory learning so that students who graduate from Trillium meet or exceed state standards, possess effective leadership and communication skills, and have a desire to be lifelong learners and problem solvers. We honor and nurture the individual spirit of each child, recognizing that intellectual, emotional and social needs must be met for the healthy development of a successful individual.
We strive for respectful communication and work to mediate conflicts peacefully.  We create and use collaborative learning, planning, and decision-making processes.  All members of our school community support the work of our school by giving generously of their time, resources and talents.
