name: Atlas Immersion Academy
details: We serve infants, toddlers, preschoolers and pre-kindergarteners in five classes. We are a full-French immersion school, and additionally offer nutritious organic meals and snacks included in the tuition. Come check us out at a community event, or attend a monthly Open House on the third Tuesday of the month.

name: St. Clare Preschool & Daycare (St. Clare Church)
details:
St. Clare is a preschool and daycare provider that cares for children from ages six weeks through six years old. We offer a nurturing and safe environment for children while teaching good Christian values hand in hand with learning and play activities.

We believe that we all have a personal responsibility to care for and contribute to our world and our community. Change begins with just one person. You can make a difference.

name: West Hills Montessori School
details:
The Montessori Method boasts a 100-year track record of success that is revealed in the lifelong achievement of its students. West Hills has been an established leader in Montessori education in the Portland area for almost 50 years. Read more about Our Story…

    Toddler Community – serves children ages 15 months – 3 years, Lake Oswego Campus
    Primary Classes serve children ages 3 to 6 years
    Elementary Program serves children ages 6 to 12 years

In Montessori classrooms your child learns by doing, thus developing mastery that is born of experience, confidence and self-reliance. At each level,  a rich and diverse curriculum prepares your child for intellectual, academic, social and emotional success in school and in life. Multi-age classes foster social cohesion and peer-to-peer teaching and learning. All West Hills classrooms are staffed by AMI-certified Montessori teachers and trained classroom assistants.

name: Vermont Hills Family Life Center-Wilson High School
West Hills Learning Center
details:
At West Hills Learning Center, we are proud to offer nurturing care, quality learning environments, and a blended creative and emergent curriculum that prepares your child for school… and for life.

Tucked away in the quaint “Multnomah Village” area of SW Portland, West Hills Learning Center is a safe haven where your young child will play and learn, grow and thrive.

Serving Portland families since 1950, we offer customized programs to meet the developmental needs of your child and accommodate your needs and schedule. Multi-age classes foster social unity and peer-to-peer learning under the expert guidance of our trained and experienced staff.  All of our classrooms from the Rose Room (Toddler’s) through the Aspen Room (Older Preschool) are introduced to basic Spanish vocabulary; and the older children (Willow and Azalea rooms) benefit from the richness of an immersive afternoon Spanish program.

Classroom teachers observe and document the children’s progress regularly and formally evaluate them four times throughout the school year. These evaluations are always available to parents and are utilized during parent/teacher conferences in the Fall and Spring.

Enriched creative and emergent curriculum, engaging classrooms, nutritional lunch and snacks, and expansive playgrounds with outdoor gardens provide your child a rich and diverse environment in which to learn and grow. Your child will be more than prepared to transition on to a public or private school after spending their foundational years at the West Hills Learning Center.

name: Blue Skies and Butterflies-Portland
details:
Our philosophy is centered around Developmentally Appropriate Practices and an attempt to be Reggio Inspired. Our curriculum is designed to develop children’s knowledge and skills in all developmental areas and establish a foundation for lifelong learning. The curriculum and instruction is age-appropriate, integrated, hands-on, and responsive to individual differences in ability and interests.

We believe that education is a process, brought on by the child’s interaction with their immediate world. It is through playing in this world that each child is encouraged and stimulated to explore, to experiment and to discover, using their own unique learning style and interests. We use an emergent curriculum that builds upon the interests of the children. Teachers document children’s work, validating the children’s abilities and enabling ongoing assessment. This approach helps children to develop curiosity, creativity, differing modes of communication, concentration, listening, negotiation and observation skills.

name: Portland Kinderschule
details:
Portland Kinderschule is a German immersion cooperative preschool where parents and teachers work together to provide a fun, caring and creative environment for children ages 3 to 5.

Children are encouraged to learn at their own pace through multisensory exploration and social interaction. By listening to stories, playing games, drawing, and singing, children develop fine and gross motor skills, learn about relationships and feelings, and gain critical-thinking and language abilities that will serve them throughout their lives.

At the same time, the preschool's German language setting supports German-speaking children who are learning the language from their parents outside their native country, and also allows non-German speakers a chance to learn a second language at an age when it comes most easily.

The mixed-age classroom experience provides opportunities for the older children to serve as role models for the younger ones.

name: PPark&Rec - Little Artists Preschool - Multnomah Arts Center
Burlingame Preschool
details:
At Burlingame Preschool, we believe in a play-based curriculum and for good reason. Much research on children's learning and development documents the benefits of play for children's intellectual, social, emotional, physical, and language development. Our students develop through their experiences with art, song, movement, games, stories, yoga, poems, sign language, outdoor activity, and guided discussion.

    Children at play are actively involved in creating themes, exploring and establishing relationships, solving problems and developing shared understanding.
    Children engage in "parallel play" — near each other but with each child engrossed in his own activity.
    As children get older, they play cooperatively, organizing roles and scenarios for group play.
    When kids play with each other, they learn to see other children's points of view and begin to understand customs and rules in their own culture and to appreciate those of others.
    They learn to use language in new ways to describe their play and interact with others.
    They develop early math and science skills, while improving on their imagination and creativity.
    And in play, children develop their muscles and coordination.

name: Southwest Parent-Child Collective
details:
Established in 1970, the Southwest Parent Child Collective (SWPCC) is a vibrant cooperative preschool run completely by parents. SWPCC provides a nurturing environment for young children to grow socially, learn to cooperate and resolve conflicts, make choices, explore, experiment, and create within safe limits. Learning unfolds naturally at our hands-on, play-based co-op. Professional teachers work with parents to guide children in developmentally appropriate activities including dramatic play, art, music, construction and block play, manipulative toys, cooperative games, storytelling, cooking, creative movement, and outdoor free play.

SWPCC offers a 4 hour per day preschool. Children from 2 to 5 years old can attend up to four days a week; children between 1 and 2 years old can attend up to three days a week. Prospective members should plan to make 2 two-hour visits to the co-op before joining. You and your child will enjoy seeing our classrooms and meeting the children and teacher.

SWPCC is affiliated with Parent-Child Preschools of Oregon. SWPCC is committed to an anti-biased and multicultural play curriculum and welcomes diversity in its member families. SWPCC does not discriminate on the basis of race, national or ethnic origin, gender, religious preference, sexual orientation, gender identity or expression, disability, language, age, color, veteran status or family composition.

name: Gabriel Park Preschool
details: The Gabriel Park Preschool curriculum is based on a "learn through play" philosophy. Through their natural love of play, children explore and manipulate their environment to discover and learn new things, developing and growing at their own rate. To encourage this type of learning, the GPPS classroom is set up in learning centers. With the teacher’s gentle guiding, children will explore each area at their leisure. Learning centers emphasize socialization, group skills, fine motor skills, literacy, math, science and artistic expression.

name: Baerly Big
details:
Got errands? Need a break? Have work commitments? Whatever the occasion, Baerly Big can help! Baerly Big is a state licensed and certified drop-in child care center that provides a fun and safe environment for children 2 1/2 to 12 years of age.

​Accomplishing everything on your to-do list is tough for everyone. Baerly Big Childcare is here to help. It's your friendly, warm, inviting daycare space that watches your kids so you can do what you need to do. We offer a safe and nurturing environment with art projects, movies, field trips and a strong sense of community. Reserve a spot for your children and go out to dinner, finish your errands, or even get your nails done. Finally, a little relief!

​We offer flexible scheduling 6 days a week. Drop-ins are accepted when space is available. Reservations are not required, but recommended to guarantee spots. Pay only for hours used at our affordable rates.

Baerly Big prides itself on having an open door policy.  We accept all children.  If your child has Autism, Down Syndrome, ADD, ADHD or just needs a fun and safe environment we can provide a space for them.  

 

We are conveniently located near Washington Square Mall at the corner of Hall and Greenburg Road. Easy parking, easy access to Hwy. 217.

details:
Our Philosophy
Our goal is to provide a developmentally appropriate, early childhood educational program in partnership with teachers, parents, and children.

 Our Beliefs
We believe each child deserves an emotionally and a physically safe world in which to explore, experiment, take risks and make constructive errors; a world in which to experience unconditional love, acceptance, and belonging.

name: My Little Waiting Room - Providence St. Vincent
details:
My Little Waiting Room® is a non-profit started by two Oregon moms who are bringing drop-in child care to the hospital.  

Our mission is to promote the health and well-being of families by bringing drop-in child care to the hospital so that children can thrive as families heal, according to the My Little Waiting Room Child's Bill of Rights.

We figure since grocery stores, gyms, community centers and other locations offer this needed service, hospitals should too. Especially since families at the hospital are often in crisis and could really use the help. That's why we're working with two local hospitals and a professional child care provider to help families in need. 

We believe for families to realize the brightest possible futures together, their ability to obtain medical attention is vital. We further believe children have the right to thrive as their family members seek that care. That's why we've written the following Bill of Rights which guides our project:

name: Bethany Village Montessori
details:
At Montessori Unlimited, we offer a unique, open environment that emphasizes your child’s natural interests and allows your child to set his or her own developmental pace.

The Montessori education journey all began with Dr. Maria Montessori. Through scientific observations, she determined children learn best at their own pace and given the choice of activities. At Montessori Unlimited, the practical application of sensory-based and self-directed learning is the most important thread across all our programs:

    Montessori Toddler
    Montessori Primary
    Montessori Elementary

Each program builds on the one before it, providing challenges appropriate to both age and skill levels. Language, mathematics, spatial learning, self-discovery, music, and art are all incorporated into our approach. In addition, we offer enrichment programs to enhance learning and Summer Camp to continue Montessori learning during the summer.

name: The Goddard School - B Building
details: The Goddard School uses the most current, academically endorsed methods to ensure that children have fun while learning the skills they need for long-term success in school and in life. name: Joyful Noise - East
details:
Together we will be partners in providing a child-oriented environment that embraces the concept of the whole child. Our activities stimulate children’s physical and intellectual development and foster social and emotional growth. Our program seeks to encourage children to think, reason, question and experiment. Through hands-on activities and challenges, the children become willing participants in their own learning cognitively, emotionally, socially, physically and culturally.

When you entrust the care and early education of your child to us, you can expect that the principles guiding that care are rooted in manifesting the following goals cited by the National Association for the Education of Young Children (NAEYC):

Relationships: That interactions between children and adults provide opportunities for children to develop an understanding of self and others and are characterized by warmth, personal respect, individuality, positive support and responsiveness. Our teachers facilitate interactions among children to provide opportunities for the development of self-esteem, social competence and intellectual growth.

Curriculum: That our curriculum implementation “reflects the knowledge that young children are active learners, drawing on direct physical and social experience as well as culturally transmitted knowledge to construct their understanding of the world around them.” Program quality is enhanced when “the curriculum encourages children to be actively involved in the learning process, to experience a variety of developmentally appropriate activities and materials. Young children learn through active manipulation of the environment and concrete experiences that contribute to concept development.”

Partnership: That teachers and families work closely in partnership to ensure high-quality care and education for children, and parents feel supported and welcomed as observers and contributors to the program. We believe in empowering parents by involving them in ongoing relationships as full partners with teachers in supporting their child’s development. “Young children are integrally connected to their families. Programs cannot adequately meet the needs of children unless they also recognize the importance of the child’s family and establish positive relationships with families based on mutual trust and respect. All communication between programs and families should be two-way, but also based on the concept that parents are and should be the principal influence in their children’s lives.”

At Joyful Noise Child Development Centers we plan activities that encourage cooperation, experimentation, and communication among children. We do not force children to operate as a large group for long periods of time. Instead we encourage children to let their curiosity and initiative drive them to make choices from a variety of classroom activities. Our teachers act as guides for these explorations, and investigators along side the children. Our Emergent Curriculum and extensive Projects speak to the children’s individual interests and allow learning within a meaningful context. The children in our centers learn to negotiate, solve problems, and construct their own code of ethics; thereby learning true compassion and developing intrinsically motivated empathy.

Parents who choose such developmentally appropriate environments for their children give them a much greater gift than any rote math or phonics lesson can. Combine this with stability, interaction, communication, and love, within the context of firm boundaries, and their children will have the foundations for successful future learning.

name: CCLC - Healthy Starts Childrens Center at OHSU
details: Healthy Starts Children’s Center at OHSU is passionate about the learning process of young children. Our center was created to help your children explore, learn and grow. Whether your child has first words or first grade on the horizon, we excel at preparing children for school success. At Healthy Starts Children's Center we have a room fully devoted to art that focuses on the artistic process. The building is equipped with an indoor playground as well as an outdoor playground, so children can play outdoors year round. Children have access to an interactive smart board as well as computers in our Preschool and Pre-Kindergarten programs; using technology to explore concepts and build their math, language and science skills. Our Guided Discovery approach is proprietary and play-based; guiding each child’s discovery of the world around them. We provide a stimulating and caring environment designed to promote social, emotional, cognitive and physical development as well as ensuring the health and safety of each child.

name: Multnomah Playschool
details:
Multnomah Playschool (MPS) is a parent-cooperative preschool for children ages 2.5 through Pre-K.
We seek to provide a safe, healthy, developmentally appropriate environment for children to explore their growing sense of self and understanding of the world.

Incorporated into our play-based curriculum is an emphasis on social anti-bias, understanding and acceptance of diversity.

In our program, children learn to get along with others, exercise their developing gross and fine motor skills, communicate verbally and explore creative materials. Abundant opportunities for self-expression are offered. Outdoor play is integral to our daily curriculum.[pb_builder]

name: Head Start - (PPS) Kelly Center
details: Portland Public Schools Head Start serves 844 low-income three and four year old children and their families. The Goal of Head Start is to build social competence in children. Social competence is the child’s everyday effectiveness in dealing with both his/her present and later responsibilities in school and life. We recognize parents as the primary educators in the life of their child. We provide quality comprehensive services that are family focused, including education, social and emotional development, physical and mental health, and nutrition. We offer both half day and extended day classrooms that operate September through June.

name: SUN Community School - Earl Boyles Elementary School
details:
SUN Community Schools in Multnomah County (link is external) are full-service neighborhood hubs where the school and partners from across the community come together to make sure kids and families have what they need to be successful - in school and in life.

SUN Community Schools mobilize and strategically organize community resources to provide:

    Strong core instructional program
    Educational support and skill development for youth and adults
    Enrichment and recreation activities
    Family involvement and support
    Social, health and mental health resources
    Family and community events

At SUN Community Schools, the collective efforts of youth, parents, businesses, faith communities, libraries, and community organizations create a network of supports that ensure academic success, family self-sufficiency, and economic prosperity. SUN Community Schools are open to all ages, preschool to seniors, with a focus on students in the immediate school community.

SUN Community Schools are the school-based service delivery sites for the SUN Service System, a broader system of community-based care and support for children and their families.

name: Boy's and Girl's Club/ Richmond Extension
details:
Our Mission:
To inspire and enable all youth, grades 1-12, especially those who need us most, to realize their full potential as productive, responsible and caring citizens through the development of a positive self-image and self-reliance.
Why Great Futures Start Here:
For over 45 years, the Boys & Girls Club of Salem, Marion and Polk Counties has delivered on our promise to provide the youth who need us most with support to reach their full potential. Through a comprehensive continuum of services, we provide children and teens with a platform for success by equipping them with the necessary life, academic and career-related skills to thrive in a 21st Century global society.

We operate 8 Clubhouses and Teen Centers in addition to a Health & Dental Services Center, T3: Training Teens for Tomorrow workforce development program, community athletic leagues, and outreach programs to schools and communities. Currently, we serve over 11,600 youth, many of whom are from economically disadvantaged homes, qualify for free or reduced lunch, and live in single-parent households.

Our goal is to deliver programs that prepare youth for a great future. This begins with the imperative to provide a safe environment that keeps kids engaged, active and happy in the hours after school and during the summer and prepares them with the a skill set that aligns academics with future career pathways and industry trends.

name: SCDC- Liberty Gardens
details:
SCDC strives to provide consistent environments in which children can discover their own capabilities and creativity.  Children are encouraged to develop self-discipline and a respect for others.  We maintain a nonsexist, non-racist setting for children's learning.  We believe it is important to enhance the development of a positive self-image in each child.  We accomplish this by providing warmth and nurturing in a growth-facilitating environment rich with opportunities to learn and discover. 

 

Our goal is to provide parents with an open, welcoming atmosphere to encourage and promote parent involvement and parent peace of mind.  We work to develop a one-to-one relationship with each child and parent, communicating to the child that they are "cared about" as well as "cared for".  We accomplish this by providing the best suited staff; qualified and dedicated to understanding the needs of the children and families.

Further, we seek to extend the children's environment beyond the classroom and into the community.
We are committed to advocating for all children, reaching out into the community and the state to advocate for high quality care for all families.
 

It is the policy of Salem Child Development Center that no person shall be discriminated against by reason of race, color, religion, disability, sex, age or national origin. SCDC accepts all children that are able to function within staff ratio and within the environments we maintain.
business hours: 6:45 am to 6:00 pm, Monday through Friday

name: Kidco Head Start - Periwinkle Center
details: Kidco Head Start/Early Head Start is a free infant/toddler and preschool program that serves families from Linn, Benton and Marion Counties. Enrollment is based on age, income and special need. The infant/toddler program serves pregnant mothers and newborns to children turning 24 months old by September 1st.  The preschool program serves children who turn three or four years old on or before September 1st.  Four year olds are given priority at most centers.

name: Kidco Head Start - South Albany Center

name: LBCC Cooperative Preschool - Albany
details: In a Cooperative Preschool parents join the teacher in providing a positive learning environment for children ages 3-5.  Children attend preschool for two-and-a-half hour sessions, two to three days (depending on the class) per week.  Parents take turns assisting the teacher in the classroom.  At parent meetings, class activities are planned, and parenting topics are discussed.

name: Kountry Kids Early Learning Center
details: Our mission is to provide a safe and developmentally stimulating environment for your child. We will be teaching education through hands-on interactive activities that are child centered and a blend of academic programs as well. Our program will stimulate physical, social, intellectual,and emotional development in every child. Our goal is to meet every child’s needs and have fun learning in a safe environment.

details:
Busy Bees Preschool opened in September 2007 by Tammy Stapley.  Tammy has worked in early childhood education for over 21 years and is passionate about providing young children with a positive introduction to school and to make sure every day is full of fun and smiles!    Located upstairs, inside Our Redeemer Lutheran Church is the perfect set up for Busy Bees Preschool.  To enter the preschool areas uspstairs parents have a code to punch in to enter.  Visitors can ring a bell and enter when a staff member lets him/her inside.   We are currently running two classrooms (3-4 yr olds and 4-5 yr olds).  There are bathrooms suited for preschoolers and a water fountain for their use.  Busy Bees has a wonderful fenced playground that provides opportunities for running, jumping, climbing, swinging, sliding, and sand play.  On rainy days the children can play and run inside the social hall where they are provided with balls, hoops, tunnels, parachutes, and other games. 

The staff members at Busy Bees Preschool are chosen on the basis of their personal and professional qualifications.  Each staff member is CPR/first aide qualified, has a background check with the Department of Oregon, and is encouraged to continue education in the Early Childhood Education (ECD) field.

name: Eugene Waldorf After School Program
details:
After School Care (ASC) is available for all enrolled children through grade 5, between the hours of 12:30 and 5:30 pm. After School Care is designed to be a home-like atmosphere offering the comfort of rhythm in the afternoon schedule, without the demands of structured activities. This allows for the children to have the kind of "outbreathing" that they need after a day of more focused activities at school. Space is provided for creative play both indoors and outside, and craft materials are available for activities such as finger knitting or coloring. Occasionally, the ASC teacher will lead a craft activity or a game. Donations of yarn and other material for the ASC program are always welcomed.

From 12:30 until 2:45 pm, After School Care is divided into two groups according to age. Early childhood ASC is held in the early childhood building by an early childhood teacher. At 2:45, the younger children join the older students in the grades ASC room, located across from the reception office. All children must be supervised after school; any child grade 4 and younger will be brought to ASC if not picked up within 15 minutes of school dismissal.

Early childhood ASC is contracted on a term basis; click the link below to print a copy of the contract. Grades ASC is scheduled monthly, as well as care for children 6 and under from 2:45 - 5:30 pm ASC may also be scheduled on a daily basis if space is available. For information about the monthly care option, click the "Information and Agreement" link below.

ASC is mostly used by working parents as a safe and convenient option for child care during working hours. The ASC program is available for currently-enrolled students only. After School Care may be free to parents at the time they are engaged in volunteer work at the school, such as attending an official meeting, preparing for a school festival, etc. If you are in doubt about whether your activity qualifies you for this, ask at the reception office. Children using ASC in this capacity should still be prescheduled in order to assure that the appropriate amount of adult supervision is arranged.

name: Far Horizons Montessori
details:
Far Horizons Montessori School follows the teaching methods developed by Maria Montessori (1870-1952). We are also dedicated to maintaining the high academic standards established by the Oregon Department of Education.

The Montessori method is based on a respect for children and the individual’s desire to learn. The children at Far Horizons are aided and directed in the process of self education by trained Montessori teachers and the Montessori learning materials. A natural inner order leads the child from interest to interest and subject to subject. The curriculum is individualized, although group lessons are regularly scheduled to present new subjects.

Our Montessori classrooms develop the privileges and responsibilities of freedom. The child learns care of the environment and the person as well as following his or her sensitive learning periods to more specific types of knowledge and subject matter.

Montessori learning materials and apparatus help the child master practical life experiences building concentration which progresses to math, language, geography, history, etc. The materials are sensorial based, aiding the child to develop a well defined concrete concept which leads to abstract concept formulation.

Far Horizons Montessori School, a private school, offers a curriculum including the Montessori method, art, music, drama, foreign languages, computer use, and physical education as well as the traditional subjects; mathematics, reading, social studies, handwriting, health, and science.

name: Little Red Barn Montessori
details:
Our Purpose and Objectives
To cultivate the child’s own natural curiosity and love of learning To foster independence and a positive self image.
To develop respect for each other and the creatures and things around us.
To prepare them for life.
The Environment
For the parents who value and love learning, we have created a rich learning environment in a rural setting. Our staff love their work and the children do too. In this place the children can explore their environment and improve their skills.
They learn to “play well with others”, listening respectfully (and quietly) while teachers and friends are talking, and learn to make choices for themselves. With this foundation our children will have the confidence, skills and tools necessary to creatively meet the yet unknown challenges in the future.
If this sounds like a match for you and your child…give us a call.

name: Kids Unlimited Mountain View
details:
Welcome to Kids Unlimited’s 14th Annual summer camp.   Kids Unlimited is a local non-profit youth development agency dedicated to providing empowerment opportunities.   Each, Kids Unlimited serve over a thousand youth through after school programs, enrichment clubs, mentoring, tutoring, sports and much more.   Our Main 1 Center for the Arts offers an ever evolving center of resources including art lab and gallery, technology center with integrated computers and film, Olsrud court basketball gyms and a commercial kitchen capable of hosting a variety of culinary classes and activities.

Our clinics and enrichment club structure provides campers the opportunity engage in many different activities, allowing for campers to try new things as well as choosing areas of their interest.  Camps are led by a staff of certified teachers, educational assistants, coaches, community members, youth development professionals and mentors. The staffing creates an environment committed to healthy learning, leadership, diversity and FUN!  Our staff to camper relationship allows for great relationship building, mentoring and small group dynamics.

This year’s summer academy is aimed at integrating technology and project learning through our weekly world themes which include activities in the arts, music, sport and dance.

name: SO Oregon Head Start Wilson Center
details:
Head Start is a federally funded program for preschool children from low-income families. Head Start Oregon Preschool Kindergarten Program (OPK) is the same program but is state funded. Children who attend Head Start participate in a variety of educational activities in stimulating settings to help them grow mentally, socially, emotionally, and physically. They also receive free medical and dental care, have healthy meals and snacks, and enjoy playing indoors and outdoors in a safe setting. Head Start helps all children succeed. Services are offered to meet the special needs of children with disabilities.

Early Head Start services are available for pregnant women, infants and toddlers in selected communities.

Head Start and Early Head Start works with the family, offering a sense of belonging, support services, and a chance to be involved in activities to help the whole family.

We assess children’s skills and abilities three times a year and use the data to plan for individual children and to make program improvements to ensure children are ready for kindergarten.

name: New Horizons Preschool & Daycare
details:
New Horizons was established in July 1989. Over the past 25 years, we have had the pleasure of weaving many memories and even more educational inspirations into the lives of hundreds of children. We know that children can only learn to their full potential when they are enveloped in a nurturing environment that they trust and feel comfortable in. It is because of that understanding that we strive to build meaningful relationships with the children we work with and with their families.

New Horizons Preschool and Day Care offers so much more than your average preschool or daycare. All of our teachers are state certified and take pride in what they do every day. We are excited to offer an extensive program that will give your child the opportunity to engage in both guided and free play, language arts activities, hands-on math and science work, extensive arts and crafts and so much more.

details:

name: The Wonder Years Preschool & Child Care Center
St Francis Daycare
details:
Being a student at Saint Francis is like being a member of an enormous extended family.

Older students support and encourage younger students in their Buddy classrooms.  Younger students are invited to older students academic or artistic presentations to view exemplary work and preview grade-level expectations.  Buddies greet each other in the hall and on the playground as occasionally sit together at Mass.

Students take part in governance by participating in student council.  Two members of each class act as elected representatives for the middle school run council.

Middle School Students chronicle our year and produce our annual year book with support and guidance from parent volunteers.

Parents provide community building events such as Bingo Night, Family Fun Night, Open Houses, and our Annual Auction.

Parents are welcome to have lunch with their children and get to know all the children.

All families are invited to participate in the spiritual growth activities of the parish,including sacramental programs and service activities.

We offer preschool and kindergarten in a warm environment with a professional staff who are dedicated to working with your child’s best interests at heart. Located by the hospital in a safe and secure neighborhood (just 3 doors down from Central Oregon Pediatrics), we are open year ‘round. Our hours are Monday through Friday, 6:30 a.m. to 6:00 p.m.

We are licensed by Child Care Division and registered as a private school in the state of Oregon. We offer care for children aged 30 months (& toilet trained) through age 8. Come visit us! Come see our bright sunny classrooms, our wonderful teachers, our happy family of children!

name: Crawmers Critterz Preschool Inc.
details:
Here you will find valuable information about our program that you simply can’t get anywhere else.  Information about our programming, staff, menu and more is all here.  If after reading through our site and you still have questions, contact our Bend preschool and we’ll be in touch.

The decision to place your child in a childcare center, home, day care or preschool in Bend is one of the tough decisions we as parents face.  From placing a 6 week old, newborn child – to potty training toddlers and working with special needs or the gifted and talented, we at Crawmer’s aim to makes this road a little easier with some guidance along the way.

Did you know that recent research shows children learn the most rapidly before the age of six?  This is why at Crawmer’s Critterz we strive to teach them skills that will prepare them for their future.  We teach common skills such as table manners, please and thank you, but also we reach for more then just common, we aim for the heart.

Using American Sign Language our students learn to communicate with both the hearing and deaf.  ASL is the second language used daily for children from 6 weeks to 12 years.  Children learn how to read words in sign before they can read letters in a book!

Humor is a daily part of our lesson plans.  Students learn to laugh out loud at the ridiculous adults that fit right in as children.  Drama and the arts are a passion of ours.  We hold a daily art class; teaching the children about the technical, creative and free style art in our culture. This allows them to experience art in their own way.

Our curriculum Mother Goose Time teaches students phonics, math, science, weather, geography, rhymes, finger plays, letters, numbers and counting all through daily art, crafts and circle time.  As Bend preschool teachers we enjoy bringing a flare of drama to the program—engaging each other and our students to act out good, bad and just plain crazy behaviors, short stories and famous events.

Our final love is music— bringing a sparkle to each child’s eye.  With the wide variety available children should not become bored with the mundane but be excited about the varieties from classical to hip-hop.  In the summer session we teach rhythm and musical patterns.

Here at Crawmer’s, our days are so packed full of fun our students just don’t want to go home!  TV, you ask… what TV?  There is simply not enough time to watch it nor does our programming allow for it.  Dive on it and check it out…

name: A Childs Garden and Preschool
details:
A Child’s Garden LLC is a Waldorf-inspired preschool and kindergarten with daycare options  in both the morning and afternoon for children 1 through 6.  It is situated in beautiful Bend, Oregon, and was established in 1998. Our goal has been to provide quality programs throughout the year in a warm, calm, and nurturing environment in which the imagination and creativity of the child will flourish. In addition to the preschool and kindergarten, we also provide full day care for children starting at one year of age.

Inspired by the Waldorf Philosophy, at A Child’s Garden we promote reverence and respect towards nature, our toys, classrooms and our relationships with classmates, teachers and family. We create an environment in which the child can grow and learn through his/her imitation of the healthy experiences around them in daily life. This environment lays the foundation for the wonder of learning and teaches them the skills needed for their life’s work of discovery.

Our community of enthusiastic and dedicated teachers work to foster in each child a lifetime love of learning through our daily rhythm which integrates arts, movement, music, crafts, drama, and play guides that support the children as they grow.

A Child’s Garden is committed to equal-opportunity education and welcomes families of all ethnic, social, and religious backgrounds.

The Juniper Junction Relief Nursery provides therapeutic early childhood services and family support to those most at risk.

We do this by:
    Providing a therapeutic classroom experience for the children, with a focus on their social and emotional development, and with the goal of meeting their unmet needs.

name: Crook County After The Bell
details:
Crook County After the Bell is a cooperative after school program made up of a variety of youth serving organizations including Crook County 4-H, Crook County Parks and Recreation, SMART, Crook County High School, Big Brothers and Big Sisters of Crook County and Crooked River Elementary School. The program operates at Crooked River Elementary school on school days between 3 and 6 p.m. The program occasionally operates on non-school days (week days) between 7:45 a.m. and 6 p.m. Every day, students can get a snack, receive help with homework, mentoring and reading, participate in recreation activities and explore science rich activities through Crook County 4-H. All students K-5th grade are welcome to sign up, but space is limited so there may be a waiting list.

The collaborating partners of Crook County After the Bell believe positive youth development does not happen by chance. It results from intentional efforts of parents, schools, youth organizations, and communities. The approach of this after school program is simple: to provide a safe, academic, and enriching environment for elementary school aged youth throughout the community, whom engage in research based activities which help develop five core competencies needed by youth to experience economic and social success in adulthood while making positive contributions to their communities. The five core competencies include: competence, confidence, connection, character and compassion.Through this dynamic collaboration, children participating in the program will have the opportunity to achieve such competencies through programming intended to improve academic achievement, through the opportunity to experience relationship with caring adults, and through engagement in mentoring programs with high school aged youth. The program will intentionally implement and foster these experiences through three main programming thrusts: science, healthy living, and civic engagement.
- See more at: http://www.ccafterthebell.org/about#sthash.6N4WraG3.dpuf

name: Start Here Preschool
details:
Start Here Preschool is a unique early childhood program designed for parents who have both the time and the interest in being involved in their preschoolers' first educational experience. The school's philosophy is that children's learning should be developmentally appropriate and facilitated through play, and also that parents are an important part of a child's education.

Incorporated as a co-op preschool, Start Here has only two paid staff-members, the teachers. The school operates through the daily efforts of parents. It is parents who keep the child to adult ratio low by volunteering in class on a rotating basis. Parents also oversee the day-to-day operation of the school through filling positions on the school's non-profit board of directors. The building maintenance is also completed by parents. As a result of this level of participation, parents have a familiarity with all aspects of their children's preschool experience that simply isn't possible through any other program structure.

When children walk in the door at Start Here preschool, they want to stay. Start Here provides a classroom environment that is welcoming to children and supports learning. The space is divided into interest areas that appeal to children and encourage distinct kinds of play. Throughout the school year, children see their artwork on the wall or hanging from the ceiling and feel a sense of belonging. Start Here prepares children for kindergarten first through social and emotional development. The school functions on the belief that in order for children to be ready for a traditional classroom setting, they first must learn how to interact constructively with their teachers and peers. This social and emotional instruction comes in a variety of ways. In circle time, children learn to expand their levels of self-control, to listen when their teachers are talking, and to take turns speaking. Children also learn these important social skills during free-play time, when the teachers and parent volunteers model how to give and take through play.    Children's natural interests are encouraged at Start Here through the constantly changing themed units incorporated throughout the year. While the teachers continue to expand and add to the themes used, some long-standing units include dinosaurs, space, oceans, and transportation. For each unit, the teachers transform the classroom using decorations, books, manipulatives, puzzles, and theme- appropriate toys. In circle time, the teachers expand upon the current theme with books and songs.

At Start Here, children's academic instruction is given at a developmentally appropriate level. Children learn early academic skills during circle time, with its focus on literacy, but also during learning center times. These small-group settings involve no more than five children to one adult and allow children to explore at a deeper level a topic or project within the school's current themed unit. Founded in 1973, Start Here has been an enduring contributor to the school community in Redmond. The long-standing success of the preschool is the best evidence for the quality of education that the school provides for the preschool child. The requirements of the program on the part of parents mean it is not the right choice for every family, but for those who do choose it, Start Here becomes a memorable and treasured part of the special preschool years for both parent and child.

Champions, through its affiliation with Knowledge Universe, delivers local learning programs backed by the resources and expertise of one of the world’s largest education companies.

name: Discovery World
details: Our environment at Discovery World is very friendly, academic, structured, dedicated, and nurturing. Parents are welcome to visit our center with or without an appointment. The needs of our parents and children come first

name: Bremerton Infant Toddler Center
details:
Child Development Centers (CDC) offer center based care for children 6 weeks to 3 years of age. Care at our centers is primarily geared toward those needing full-time child care. Our centers are based on the developmental program model which focuses on play and its importance in a child's learning process. Our centers are also a part of the 7% of programs in the United States accredited or pursuing accreditation by the National Association for the Education of Young Children (NAEYC).

We are committed to supporting the military family by recognizing the uniqueness of each family's lifestyle and cultural heritage. Parents are encouraged to participate in center events and activities.

We strive to meet each child's social, emotional and intellectual needs to instill in each child a feeling of competence and positive self-concept. We value and support our staff through staff development and continuing education so they become even better equipped to support the individual needs of children.

name: BOYS & GIRLS CLUB - TRI- TECH
details:
Our Tri-Tech Nursery is a licensed childcare center located on the Tri-Tech Skills Center campus in Kennewick. We provide childcare for the infants and toddlers of the teen parents at an on-campus location so that they can continue their education and graduate with a high school diploma.

In addition to being able to provide care for the infants and toddlers, we are able to establish mentoring relationships with the teen parents, providing them with guidance in parenting, academics and assist them in overcoming obstacles that arise in their lives.
business hours:
M-F 7:00-3:00
*Hours of operation may vary due to early release days, no school days, conference days and school breaks

name: Academy for Leadership & Lifeskills for Youth
Cascade Christian Puyallup Extended School Program
FRUITLAND DAY CARE
details:
At Fruitland Daycare your child will get the individual attention and care that are important to you.  From the moment your child enters our care, they will be immersed in a happy, comfortable and a safe environment, our cozy classrooms are clean and free of any unsafe settings, our play areas are very comfortable and naturally lit. To aid in your child's development, we have many stimulating games and activities, children's music and books, etc. We PROVIDE very healthy, nutritional snacks as well as BREAKFAST. YOU MUST PROVIDE YOUR CHILDS LUNCH. Feel free to visit us and see first hand.

We celebrate every child and staff's birthdays here at Fruitland Daycare by having a special day with all of our friends. Parents are always welcome to bring in sealed store bought item(s) for the celebration.

Every classroom follows a weekly themed curriculum that is completed by our Program Supervisor and approved by the Department of Early Learning of Pierce County in Washington State.

Each of our staff are state approved to care for children by approval of a Washington State Background check. Each staff is up to date on all required training including first aid and CPR + Current WA State Food Handlers Card  to provide the best care for your little ones!
business hours: 6:30 a.m. to 6:00 p.m. Monday through Friday

name: BATES EARLY CHILDHOOD LEARNING CENTER
details:
Bates offers an ECEAP preschool program for children who are four years old before Aug. 31 in several convenient Pierce County locations. The program is free for low income families who qualify.

This high-quality preschool program offers monthly family activities, hot meals, children's health and developmental screenings and community resource referrals for parents and families. Classes are Monday-Thursday, 9 a.m.-12:30 p.m.

Should you need additional childcare, our Downtown Campus offers a preschool program for children ages three to five on a sliding fee scale for students. The center accepts children from families who are not Bates students, though they do not recieve tuition based on a sliding fee scale.

name: BOTHELL DAYCARE & PRESCHL
details:
Bothell Daycare and Preschool is pleased to be the first, and at this time, only childcare in the North Shore area to receive the Quality Level of Excellence Award from Early Achievers. Early Achievers is Washington Department of Early Learning’s Quality Rating and Improvement System (QRIS). The Early Achievers program is voluntary for licensed child care providers and ensures early learning programs offer high-quality care.
Bothell Daycare and Preschool has been serving the Bothell community for more than 30 years. We provide quality child care for children age 16 months (and walking) through 4th grade. Bothell Daycare and Preschool is a non-profit, Christian Day care Center.

name: TRINITY EDUCARE CENTER
details: Trinity Catholic School and Educare Center is a Christian community based in St. Anthony's and St. Joseph's parishes. We offer solid academic education based on Catholic values, traditions and formation of a strong relationship with God in a safe environment for people of diverse economic situations and cultures. We strive to enrich the lives of all students and we encourage students to become creative, responsible members of both Church and society.

name: BEGINNINGS CC #1
details:
We at Beginnings believe strongly in the need to foster individual growth and self-esteem for every child.

The particular needs of each child and each family are our priority. We strive to maintain an atmosphere of emotional trust and a respect of open communication. At the same time, we provide a physical environment in which cognitive, physical and social development are all richly interwoven. This is made possible by a staff of teachers that comprise our greatest asset.

We are committed to the idea of parental involvement and have made available a range of possibilities for such involvement. Parents are encouraged to voice their ideas and concerns and to participate directly in the life and health of our schools. Beginnings Schools are cooperative early learning programs.

name: YMCA DOWNTOWN/BAILEY GATZERT
details: Our program at Bailey Gatzert Elementary School helps kids reach their fullest potential by promoting education, health, and social development. Your child will have many opportunities to spend time reading or studying with one of our caring staff, participate in fun, physical activities, or learn a new skill. Most importantly, children learn how to be their best selves. That makes for confident kids today and contributing, engaged adults tomorrow. - See more at: http://ykids.seattleymca.org/west-seattle-fauntleroy-ymca/child-care/school-age-care/bailey-gatzert-elementary-school#sthash.1xAfUYcb.dpuf
business hours:
7:00 am - school day start
school day dismissal - 6:00 pm

name: ST LUKES CHRISTIAN CHILD CARE CENTER
LUV N CARE DAYCARE MINISTRIES
details:
At Luv-N-Care, we believe in the dignity and self-worth of every staff person.  We are committed to providing a positive work environment, which stimulates personal growth, spiritual growth, and fulfillment.

As a ministry of Auburn Church of the Nazarene we are committed to being living proof of Christ’s love and to make him known in every relationship.  Our vision is to radiate Christ’s life to our world by building strong families.

Our mission at Luv-N-Care Daycare is to surround children in a caring and safe environment where mutual respect between teachers and children exists.  We will provide Christ-centered, age appropriate and creative curriculum’s that will stimulate learning for both children and staff.

name: WESTMINSTER PRE-SCHOOL & DAY CARE
details:
The children are encouraged to work and play together while being guided toward a happy, wholesome development (mentally, physically, socially, and spiritually).

We strive to create an atmosphere of cultural diversity and appreciation, welcoming children of all races and religions.

Every organization must have an underlying purpose which drives it forward and keeps it healthy. At Westminster Child Care our motivation is what we call “The Westminster Vision” and it is simply this: “The terms ‘children’ and ‘future’ are synonymous.”

Anything we do to assist children in their development prepares them for the future. We know we have succeeded in our aim when children grow up feeling secure with who they are. Not just ready to face the future, but anticipating their opportunity to lead it.

name: PRIMM TABERNACLE DAY CARE CENTER
details:
Primm is a fully licensed child care center with the City of Seattle and the State of Washington with a curriculum based on real life events as a foundation for learning for ages 1 to 12.

In 1970, Primm Day Care Center was established by Rev. and Mrs. Edward N. Smith Jr. and the members of Primm Tabernacle AME Church.  Friends of Primm at the Holy Trinity Lutheran Church of Mercer Island also assisted.  Until 1975, the center was licensed for 21 children from ages 21/2 to 12 years when a second site was purchased on Rainier Avenue South.  This expanded our services to care for 28 additional children.

In 1977, the center relocated to its present location and is now licensed for 45 children, from toddlers to pre-adolescent age.  Donations of services and equipment have come from many sources:  the City's Department of Human Resources, the Boeing Employees Good Neighbore Fund, board members and many friends.  They have provided us the opportunity to serve many families through the years.

The program is child-centered and offers a variety of challenging activities and materials to enable each child to create and to discover the joys learning has to offer.

In the past, we have been able to offer before and after school enrichment programs for schoolagers at the original MLK school and Dearborn Park elementary schools.

We offer a free full-day preschool for children who are 4 years old by August 31st under the Early Childhood Education and Assistance Program (ECEAP) on Mondays through Thursdays from 8:30 am to 3:00 pm.  Click here for a flyer with additional information and the current income guidelines for the program.

Our center hours are 7:00 am to 6:00 pm during the year.  Childcare is available for full or part-time care and before and after school.  We accept childcare subsidies.

name: A BIT OF HOME DAY CARE
CHAPEL CHILDRENS CENTER
details:
Colbert Chapel has been in the North Spokane area since 1906.  In 1973, Pastor Walt Henderson began directing a new Colbert Chapel Preschool.  After working with the preschool for three years, a need became clear for a Christian-based daycare in the area.  Together with his wife Geri, and a fellow church member, Billye Anderson, Chapel Children's Center was formed.  In the words of Billye Anderson, "This was a time when families were stil adjusting to both parents working.  We knew that if children had to be out of the home we wanted them to be in a good safe place, in the love of Christian people."

Years later, our center still has the same goals.  Family has stayed close.  Two main supervisors in the Daycare are Ms. Jackie, daughter of Walt and Geri Henderson, and Ms. Shelly, niece of Billye Anderson.  Current director, Elaine Sherer, has attended Colbert Chapel church since early childhood, worked at the Daycare during high school and has been in the position as director since 1997.

Our center has a unique experience to offer your family.  Many of our current families have been with us for years, and have come to know Colbert Chapel and Chapel Children's Center as their "home away from home".  We hope your family can join them.  Please look through our information and contact our director with any questions.  Thank you again for your consideration.

name: VALLEY LEARNING CENTER
details:
Whether you are a working couple, or balancing other responsibilities, life as parents of little children is demanding. At Preschool or Daycare Centers, little children's well-rounded development and happiness is our central mission. Your children will always be in good hands at ANY of our learning centers.

Spokane learning Centers are professionally managed pre-school and day care offering programs for children from three months to five years. In addition, we also offer after-school programs for children up-to twelve years of age.

To view directions and a google map to a specific center, click the buttons on the right. For more details about our centers and for contact info, click the buttons on the left.

name: CHILDRENS HOUSE
details: The Children's House Childcare Center in Brewster, WA has been in business for over 30 years, providing licensed, educational programming for children.

name: TEEN FAMILY DAY CARE
details: Thank you for your interest in using the Teen Family Childcare Program at Sequoia High School available for Sequoia students. We are a small program with a caring staff of school employees and volunteer workers. We strive to create a safe, caring, comfortable, and stimulating environment for your children.

name: ST FRANCIS CHILDCARE CENTER
details:
Generations Early Learning & Family Center is a division of The St. Francis Foundation, a non-profit corporation established in 1985. From 1985 to 2015, the Center operated as St. Francis Childcare and was located within St. Francis of Bellingham, a skilled nursing facility and rehabilitation center. In order to expand our program, we moved to partner with the Mt. Baker Care Center and Summit Place Assisted Living in early 2015.

The primary purpose of our center has always been to provide a unique early childhood education program within a residential care facility, which will benefit the residents, children, families, and staff members through mutual interactions and continuing relationships. Quality early childhood care and education programs allow parents to engage in work and other activities with the assurance that their children are in a safe environment that promotes health, happiness, and well-being.

name: RAGGEDY ANN & ANDY 2
details:
Our goal is to have a program designed to kindle each child’s natural urge to discover, to think creatively and find joy and sensitivity in life.

We provide a place where children can advance intellectually while they mature emotionally, developing positive feelings about themselves and others.

name: BETHEL CHRISTIAN PRSCH & DC
details:
Bethel Christian Preschool and Daycare is a non-profit establishment ministry of Spokane Bethel Church of the Nazarene.  We desire to give each child that attends a place that is safe and secure with a spirit of Christian love shown through a Christian staff that nurtures each child according to his or her needs.   We are a fully licensed facility, which complies with all the requirements and regulations of the state of Washington.  We strive to provide a loving, educational, Christian environment for children. 

Each staff member professes to being a Christian and has current First Aid, CPR, and HIV training along with passing a Washington State Patrol background check.  Each member is learning each year through STARS training to stay current on the issues of Early Childhood Education.

name: ST ALOYSIUS EARLY LEARNING & EXTENDED CA
details: The St. Aloysius Gonzaga Early Learning Center (ELC) and Montessori Preschool is one of the largest childcare centers/licensed preschools in Spokane. Enrollment in ELC begins at 12 months and continues through pre-kindergarten. Enrollment in Montessori begins at preschool and continues through kindergarten. The ELC and its associated childcare is open twelve months a year.

name: WHITWORTH CHURCH CHILD CARE
details: We offer a full day Extended Care, Half Day, Junior Kindergarten and Before and After School Programs.  We are open from 6:30am-6:00pm Monday-Friday.

name: GINGERBREAD HOUSE DAYCARE
details: The Gingerbread House Daycare and Preschool has been a family run center for the last 25 years! Owner/Director Kerry Seraji has a Ph. D. in Early Childhood Education and carefully selects each staff member to ensure the highest standards of care for the children. Each teacher at our center is well trained in child development, children’s first-aid+CPR, safe food handling techniques (and each teacher also undergoes a thorough background check/screen).

name: ADAMS KIDS
details: Kids Co. at Adams is located on the grounds of Adams Elementary in a quiet Ballard neighborhood. The site offers large and colorful play spaces for kids—perfect for the active imaginations of the young—and conveniently located drop-off/pick-up parking for parents and guardians. Kids Co. offers four programs at Adams: Preschool, Before-School Care, After-School Care, and Summer Day Camp.

name: FIRST FLIGHT CHILD CARE
details:
First Flight Child Care Center is privately owned company that has operated for Walla Walla Community College since 1989. Owners Bill and Eileen Wolford are highly trained educators who work with their staff and children to provide the best learning experience possible in a safe and healthy environment.

Developmentally appropriate curriculum and practices are used for young children. Activities are implemented with attention to the different needs, interests, and developmental levels of individual children. Although groupings are generally based on the child's age, groupings are flexible and a child may be moved from one group to another to meet special needs. All but the youngest group intermingles freely throughout the school day according to individual interests, needs, differences, and capabilities.

All full time staff members are experienced early childhood educators. They participate in a continuous program of in-service educational studies for professional advancement in order to remain alert to the ever-changing needs of today's families and to the finding of current research.

The center is open to all children, ages six weeks to six years (not already enrolled in kindergarten).
business hours:
7:15 am to 5:30 pm

Monday through Friday

name: GROW WITH US
details: At Grow With Us Preschool and Child Care we strive to provide a setting that is nurturing and warm, yet structured and attuned to individual needs. Our proactive and dedicated staff offers programs designed for the successful participation of each child. Our program is based on the premise that children learn through play, so we provide an activity-based learning curriculum. It is our hope that you'll feel confident in our ability to meet all of your expectations and know that your children are always our number one focus.

name: AMERICAS BEST CHILDCARE
details:
America’s Best Childcare in Silver Lake and Another Best Childcare in Everett, Lynnwood, and Marysville are committed to providing a safe, nurturing, and educational Christian environment for children 1-12 years of age.  

As a Christian childcare center we are dedicated to equipping each child with a positive and loving atmosphere. Along with educational basics, children are taught life-skills, manners, and values to apply as they grow through their formative years and beyond. 

With our affordable rates and quality, loving instruction from our well-trained staff, we are certain that your child will consistently thrive and learn throughout their time with us. We have delivered a loving and rewarding experience to hundreds of families over the years and look forward to working with yours.

name: KIDS PLACE THE
details: Our school is a small community that encourages children to develop healthy relationships and to become active agents in their own education. We provide a climate for growth in which children have opportunities through play and real work to explore their ideas and realize their capacities. Led by the Reggio Emilia method of teaching, children at Kids' Place are immersed in an environment dense with potential that promotes literacy, numeracy, problem-solving collaboration, and respect.

name: COMMUNITY DAY SCHOOL MONTLAKE
details:
We provide high-quality, affordable preschool, kindergarten-readiness, before- and after-school extended learning opportunities, and summer-long learning camp programs. Families who enter our program are entering a network of assistance that fosters long-term benefits.

Our programs are located onsite at 9 Seattle Public Schools (SPS) in Central, West, and Southeast Seattle and serve a diverse population of students. All of the SPS schools we serve except one are Title I schools, meaning that they receive additional federal funding because they serve a disproportionate amount of lower-income students and need additional support to ensure that all children meet challenging state academic standards.

Due to budget cuts, public schools are increasingly relying on our services and programs to help students who are in need of extra support. At CDSA we teach the academic and social skills needed for long-term success: science and math through nature walks, cooking, music, building models, and science experiments; empathy through arts and drama; self-expression through music and dance; and other hands-on learning opportunities. We individualize our learning plans for our children and focus on decision-making and empowering them to grow an internal compass to guide them toward good choices in life.

All six of our preschool programs have been awarded a Quality Level of Excellence rating by Early Achievers (Washington State’s quality rating and improvement system) and are accredited by the National Association for the Education of Young Children (NAEYC).

name: PROMISE DAY CARE
details: At Promise, our purpose is to provide quality childcare to the community of Bellingham. Our philosophy is to use creative ideas to meet the needs of the child in a distinctively Christian context and atmosphere.
business hours: 6:45 a.m. to 6:15 p.m., Monday through Friday

name: LITTLE STAR SCHOOL MONTESSORI
details:
Our school is dedicated to ensuring that children in the Methow Valley have the opportunity for a  healthy and joyful early childhood education. Cultivating children’s natural curiosity and creativity  lies at 
the heart of our Montessori program. We encourage each child to develop as a whole person and acquire a lifelong love of learning.

name: KIDS COUNTRY MONROE
details:
As a full-service, licensed, and family owned business, Kid’s Country was established with the goal to promote a safe and nurturing learning environment that stimulates your child’s growth. Our curriculum, activities, and room arrangements are all tailored to be age appropriate. Additionally, our curriculum follows both weekly and monthly themes.

A typical day at Kid’s Country will include activities like reading, looking at books, writing, drawing, dancing, singing, cutting, pasting, painting, assembling art projects, experimenting, exploring, and enjoying the environment. One of our primary areas of focus is meeting each child’s individual needs. We encourage children to progress at their own pace and they are placed in the classroom that will help them the best. This encourages self-confidence and healthy growth which results in a strong, positive self-image.

In fact, the Kid’s Country motto is to allow children to love, laugh, learn, and grow. By keeping the environment fun and positive, we create a safe haven—a home away from home—for your children. All of our classrooms are warm, cozy, and filled with personal touches that allow your kids to feel comfortable. It is our responsibility to work in partnership with your family and help enhance and support, not replace, the relationship between parents and children.

One of the ways we do this is by placing a high priority on ongoing training for our managers and staff. Every month each of our teachers is trained on a different topic relating to child care and the issues we face in providing for your children. This allows us to better meet the needs of the kids we care for, as well as to provide a better, cleaner, happier, and safer environment.

At Kid’s Country, we take the safety of your children very seriously. All of our facilities are equipped with pass card protected entrances. We are also alerted to those arriving and exiting through the main entrance. In order to gain admittance, an entry reader card must be used, though we do have a doorbell available to notify our staff of any guests or parents who need access.

We hope you can see how important caring for your children is to all of us at Kid’s Country. We pride ourselves on being a premier and trustworthy child care provider for the Seattle area. Watching your kids grow and learn gives us joy and fulfillment. If you like what you see, we invite you to learn more by touring one of our facilities. Hopefully you’ll then apply for admission, which is granted without discrimination or regard to race, color, national or ethnic origin, sex, or religion.

name: A HEART FOR THE HOME CHILDCARE
VALLEYPOINT AT PINES EARLY CHILDHOOD LC
details: Valeypoint Learning Center was started as a ministry to the community of working parents. Through our childcare program we seek to meet your child's individual needs and enhance his or her growth throughout their childhood years. We seek to reflect the highest Christian values and provide the best care for children.
business hours:
Monday to Friday
6:30 am to 6:00 pm

name: OUR SAVIOURS LUTHERAN CHILDCARE
details:
Our Mission:

 To care for and teach children through faith and by loving example to make a positive difference in their family and community.

name: TODDLERS UNIVERSITY DC #2
details:
When you visit, you'll see what "play with a purpose" really means. Every child is engaged in an activity that not only stimulates learning, it stimulates fun, too. Whether it's reading a book, playing a game, working in a learning center, or improving skills on the playground, we make early childhood development interesting and engaging.

We help prepare children for kindergarten and for life, through activities that help them learn language, math, science, dexterity, expression, imagination and social skills. Come see for yourself. You'll find that when learning is fun, kids love to learn.

We have an open door policy. Parents may walk in to any of our centers at any time to meet our staff and take a tour of our facility.

name: ANOTHER BEST CHILDCARE & LEARNING CTR
details:
America’s Best Childcare in Silver Lake and Another Best Childcare in Everett, Lynnwood and Marysville are committed to providing a safe, nurturing, and educational Christian environment for children 1-12 years of age.  

As a Christian childcare center we are dedicated to equipping each child with a positive and loving atmosphere. Along with educational basics, children are taught life-skills, manners, and values to apply as they grow through their formative years and beyond. 

With our affordable rates and quality, loving instruction from our well-trained staff, we are certain that your child will consistently thrive and learn throughout their time with us. We have delivered a loving and rewarding experience to hundreds of families over the years and look forward to working with yours.

name: BEYOND THE RAINBOW
details: We believe that each child deserves to have access to a quality early childhood education, since their early years provide the foundation for the rest of their lives. Children will enjoy learning when  provided a fun, safe, and nurturing environment.  By instilling a joy of learning in young children, we believe that will give them a good start for success.
business hours:
6 am to 6 pm Monday through Friday. 
            *Infant room is open 7 am to 5 pm

name: LOVING HEARTS DAYCARE
details: Loving Hearts was established in 1987 as an outreach ministry of Spokane Christian Center. Our main focus is to supply quality childcare in a loving, nurturing environment. Loving Hearts is licensed for 85 children with the Washington State DSHS Office of Child Care Policy. Our mission is  to  assist parents in training up Godly Toddlers, Preschoolers, Pre-Kindergartners, and School Age Children with love and security, equality, and individuality. Allowing each child to grow and blossom to their full potential with love and acceptance to become who God has created them to be.

name: LEARNING WAY SCHOOL & DAYCARE
details:
Learning Way School and Daycare is a not for profit 501C3 which was established in 1984 to serve the children and families of the White Center, West Seattle and Burien area.

The center is licensed for 38 children ages 6 weeks to 12 years although the main emphasis is on children up to age 6. The program is divided into 4 classrooms, 4 infants at a 2 to 1 ratio, 10 toddlers at a 5 to 1 ratio, 14 preschool children at a 7 to 1 ratio and 10 pre-kindergarten students.

Learning Way has an experienced, educated and well trained staff. The teachers create a partnership with the parents in educating and caring for the children.

name: ST THOMAS MORE EXT CARE
details:
Each individual is created by God with a unique mind, heart, body, and spirit. St. Thomas More Catholic School, in partnership with the home, ministers to our children in developing his/her intellectual, spiritual, social, and physical potential.

Christ as the servant model guides us to know, love, and serve God. Through traditional education and the use of current technology, we emphasize the importance of acquiring foundational knowledge and critical thinking skills. We integrate citizenship and faith throughout the curriculum to develop responsible stewards who live Gospel values.

name: FANTASY FARM CHILD DEV CR
details:
Fantasy Farm Children's Center is locally owned and proudly takes care of children throughout the Spokane, Washington area. We provide the most caring and attentive child care services and know that each day your child visits us, you’ll both feel completely at ease! We specialize in assisting childhood development and truly care about the well-being and education of the children we supervise.

We offer full time programs and we are open early and open late! We focus on literacy, music and creativity! We also have a large outdoor play area for your children to enjoy!

name: TEDDY BEAR CORNER INC
details:
Teddy Bear Corner, Inc.  strives to offer a safe environment in which children love to learn, teachers love to teach and families feel at home. We believe that self-esteem is the critical component to optimal growth in young children. In order for a child to have high self-esteem, we focus on the socialization and self-help skills needed to succeed in other areas of development.

 We teach children through the use of a Developmentally Appropriate Theme Based curriculum.  Not only are the children at Teddy Bear Corner given the opportunity to explore, experiment and create in a safe and nurturing environment, they are exposed to children of different cultures and ethnical backgrounds. To enhance learning in our program, we incorporate multi-cultural, anti-biased activities.

name: CUP CHILDCARE
details:
Central United Protestant's Central Christian Daycare and Drop-in Child Care is located at 1124 Stevens Dr., Richland, Washington. 
It is a licensed childcare that serves children ages Birth-5. Central Christian Daycare and Drop-in Child Care is church related (religious affiliated).

name: PHANTOM LAKE CHILD CARE CENTER/BELL PUB
HUTCH KIDS CHILD CARE
details: Hutch Kids is the NAEYC accredited, employer sponsored child care center for employees of Fred Hutchinson Cancer Research Center.
