As parents enroll their child in the center, they become members of the corporation, which allows them to participate in the decision making of the organization.

name: KIDS COUNTRY DAY CARE
details:
As a full-service, licensed, and family owned business, Kid’s Country was established with the goal to promote a safe and nurturing learning environment that stimulates your child’s growth. Our curriculum, activities, and room arrangements are all tailored to be age appropriate. Additionally, our curriculum follows both weekly and monthly themes.

A typical day at Kid’s Country will include activities like reading, looking at books, writing, drawing, dancing, singing, cutting, pasting, painting, assembling art projects, experimenting, exploring, and enjoying the environment. One of our primary areas of focus is meeting each child’s individual needs. We encourage children to progress at their own pace and they are placed in the classroom that will help them the best. This encourages self-confidence and healthy growth which results in a strong, positive self-image.

In fact, the Kid’s Country motto is to allow children to love, laugh, learn, and grow. By keeping the environment fun and positive, we create a safe haven—a home away from home—for your children. All of our classrooms are warm, cozy, and filled with personal touches that allow your kids to feel comfortable. It is our responsibility to work in partnership with your family and help enhance and support, not replace, the relationship between parents and children.

One of the ways we do this is by placing a high priority on ongoing training for our managers and staff. Every month each of our teachers is trained on a different topic relating to child care and the issues we face in providing for your children. This allows us to better meet the needs of the kids we care for, as well as to provide a better, cleaner, happier, and safer environment.

At Kid’s Country, we take the safety of your children very seriously. All of our facilities are equipped with pass card protected entrances. We are also alerted to those arriving and exiting through the main entrance. In order to gain admittance, an entry reader card must be used, though we do have a doorbell available to notify our staff of any guests or parents who need access.

We hope you can see how important caring for your children is to all of us at Kid’s Country. We pride ourselves on being a premier and trustworthy child care provider for the Seattle area. Watching your kids grow and learn gives us joy and fulfillment. If you like what you see, we invite you to learn more by touring one of our facilities. Hopefully you’ll then apply for admission, which is granted without discrimination or regard to race, color, national or ethnic origin, sex, or religion.

name: SMALL WONDERS LEARNING CENTER
details: Small Wonders has been in Bellevue for 20 years providing quality childcare committed to the development and education of the whole child intellectually, emotonally, socially, and physically. At Small Wonders we believe that children are capable, talented little people, who construct their knowledge of the world around them through investigation, exploration, literature, art, music and good old fashioned play. Born with a natural curiosity and sense of wonder they are encouraged to openly express their feelings, ideas and experiences in many different ways.

name: DISCOVERY MONTESSORI
details:
The Montessori method of Education is a special program especially geared to respect children and their needs. Maria Montessori, Italy's first woman doctor developed it, in the early 1900's. Her materials and methods have withstood the test of time. The adults who work in the Montessori program are trained to be observers of the children and preparers of the children's environment. The emphasis is on learning rather than on teaching. The materials in the program are intended to help the children in their drive to sort out their experiences and master the skills they need. As children become more and more competent, the confidence is reinforced and they develop good feeling about themselves. The unique materials Montessori created are perhaps the best known aspect of the system.

There are practical life materials. These materials are designed to prepare children for real-life experiences. They help children develop skills, which will increase their independence and confidence in themselves. There are sensorial materials. These materials are designed to isolate for the children the properties of thins and to help them refine and organize in their mind what they are absorbing through their senses. There are math materials. The purpose of these materials in to ensure that the process of mathematical abstraction is based on concrete experiences with manipulative materials. There are language materials. These materials offer a systematic breakdown of the elements of reading that enables children to experience concretely the structure of the language. There are also cultural materials. These materials include geography, botany, history, astronomy zoology, physical science, art, and languages. The purpose of these materials is to sharpen the child's powers of observation and understanding of the world around him.

One of Dr. Montessori's observations about children was that there are certain stages when children are especially ready to learn a particular thing. She called them "sensitive periods." She observed that if children were given the opportunity to learn a particular skill during their sensitive periods that never again could they learn it so easily or so well. The Montessori classroom is designed to offer children the opportunity to learn and develop according to their sensitive periods.

Maria Montessori also discovered that young children are able to concentrate to a far greater extent than adults realized if an activity meets their needs, and if the process allows physical involvement. Adults often think young children have short attention spans when the problem is that they are seldom given activities worthy of their attention or appropriate to their style of learning. To encourage concentration in children their needs for repetition must be met, and time allowed practicing that particular skill. The Montessori classroom encourages concentration by offering a wide variety of materials from which children can choose according to their needs and by allowing children to use them repetitively until their needs are met.

The Montessori Classroom tries to foster and nourish the fundamental needs of children. In the Montessori classroom the fundamental needs of children are considered to be the need for movement, the need for language development, the need for independence, the need for love and security, the need for discipline, and the need for order.

After a while, with cooperation of the school and the home and a real understanding of how to cater to the child's needs, Maria Montessori described how children become normalized. The normalized child is one who has a love of order, a love of work, a love of silence and working alone, profound spontaneous concentration, obedience, independence and initiative, spontaneous self-discipline, attachment to reality, and joy.

name: COUNTRY FRIENDS DAY CARE
details:
Promote self-confidence; To achieve this, we provide success-oriented activities.

Listen to children and respond to their needs so that they believe their feelings and opinions are important. We give encouragement and positive reinforcement without over praising.

Socially well-adjusted; We give guidance in this area when needed. We act as a role model by talking politely and with interest to children and adults in the room. We joke and laugh with the children.

Make choices of their own; We provide many opportunities for children to do this.

Problem solving skills; We use every opportunity possible to let the child solve a problem. Rather than provide an answer, we ask leading questions so that the child may find the answer for her/himself. We provide activities that allow for problem solving - maybe on the science table, in a game, or working out rules together.

Encourage independence; We let children do as much as they possibly can for themselves. We acknowledge their efforts in a positive way.

Creativity is very important. Each child's creation is unique. We provide guidance if asked but always make it clear that the creation belongs to the child and can be done any way he/she wants.


Parents are the child's most important teachers, and of course, care givers. We communicate daily.

We want the children in the daycare to enjoy being here, to be really happy. We provide activities that are interesting, fun, and developmentally appropriate. We recognize each child's uniqueness and provide for it.

We pay attention to every child, every day. We try to use a kind and gentle approach at all times.

The goal of our programs is to provide a warm, loving, creative atmosphere for your children, where independence and individuality along with learning are encouraged.
    Developing a good self-image is emphasized by increasing the child's awareness of themselves and their environment. This goal is realized through creating a desire to attend school, providing opportunities to experience recognition and acceptance of and by others. The use of oral language is encouraged by the staff to express feelings and knowledge. The children are stimulated by a variety of activities, such as music, art, literature and science, according to the child's developmental level. While participating in the various activities, your children learn to develop a positive attitude towards their teachers, peers, family and others.The Preschool program is filled with everything to get your child ready for Kindergarten. Parkside Christian is a distinctively and thoroughly Christian program. Children of any race, color, sex, national or ethnic origin are welcome. name: COMMUNITY BUILDING CHILDRENS CENTER
details:
The Community Building Children's Center is one part school, one part home and one part museum.  Children in this school are seen as being fully competent and capable of learning about the world around them through discovery and investigation.  Teachers listen to the children’s interests and questions and provide props and materials to help the children follow their investigations.  The teachers learn with the children as they explore the environment of the school and neighborhood community.

The homelike atmosphere comes in part from the size of the Center, with eight toddlers and eighteen preschoolers.  CBCC maintains a low teacher to child ratio, 1:4 for toddlers and 1:6 for preschool.  This allows more one on one time for caring and nurturing the children and their learning.

The CBCC environment is beautiful and homelike, and stimulating to children’s curiosity and learning.  Materials and natural elements are displayed beautifully and thoughtfully throughout the environment.  Children’s work is given value and importance through documentation and display.  The environment conveys the clear sense that children and their work are valued and appreciated.

name: TINY TOTS DEVELOPMENT CENTER/WING LUKE
details:
Tiny Tots Development Center celebrated the opening of its newest facility – The Helen Hicks Building (below) in the Othello neighborhood. Established in the Rainier Valley in 1969, Tiny Tots Development Center (TTDC) provides child care services and early childhood education at several sites throughout South Seattle. Its main campus (above) – located at 8302 Renton Avenue South – is the organization’s largest site.

Seven long years in the making, the new campus is named after Tiny Tots founder and CEO Helen Hicks – known affectionately throughout the community as “Mama Hicks” (cutting the ribbon below).

Executive Director Angelia Maxie (below) welcomed friends, family and guests, including the fathers of former students who attended the Main Campus more than 25 years ago and are now attending college, teaching English abroad and raising their own families.

The school’s bright new building was made possible with assistance from the Rainier Valley Community Development Fund, the City of Seattle, Bank of America and others.

The Tiny Tots-Bright Bell Birds program and an Early Childhood Education and Assistance Program (ECEAP) preschool program will move in this summer and begin educational programs in the new building in September 2010.

Meanwhile, Tiny Tots Main, the site of our original program, will continue to house preschool, infant care, and childcare at 8318 Renton Avenue South (below).

details:
Northwest’s Child serves kids, teens and young adults between the ages of 5 and 21. We are a year round program. During the school year we are open after school until 6:00pm. When school is out, due to no-school days, holidays, spring break and summer vacation, Northwest’s Child is open from 7:00am until 6:00pm.
We are closed for a few major Holidays, for the first full week of August, and the week between Christmas and New Years.  However, all of our staff are trained to provide respite care during the times our program is closed.

During the day, staff work with the students to continue and build upon the IEP’s put in place by each child’s school district. The staff also take the kids on field trips, lead them in arts and crafts, group activities, social and independent living skills.

name: RAINBOWS END CHILDRENS CENTER
details:
We are here to provide your children with the best care possible. Our staff is knowledgeable and trained in all areas. We have a carefully planned program with age appropriate, structured activities, as well as supervised free time.

Our goal is to provide opportunities for growth in all areas of development. We realize that in the early years it is critical in the development of your child for there to be challenges as they grow and mature. We want to provide challenges, but not make unreasonable demands that only make the child feel defeated.

We will provide opportunities for your child’s optimal growth and development such as:
·         Group activities that foster skills such as following directions and cooperation
·         Cutting, gluing, and drawing to develop fine motor skills.
·         Language skills are fostered in choice centers such as blocks and house keeping
·         Gross motor skills are also developed through organized and free choice activities.

All of these activities provide a structured environment for developing personal and group socialization as well as a basic preparation for their school year.        
As the child progresses into kindergarten, our goal is to enhance their success in school. We continue to work on cooperation, creativity, and individuality while preparing them with age appropriate activities to ensure their success in school.
At Rainbow’s End we strive to be an extension of home. In addition to providing a strong curriculum for our Preschool, we assist parents of school age children by providing homework help, individual reading times, journaling and using “calming cards” to problem solve and release stress from the school day.
Professional referrals will be posted in the front office to assist parents with the needs of their children.

Our goal is to provide a safe and happy place for children where they can learn and grow physically, emotionally, intellectually and socially at their own pace. We'll provide your child with lots of attention, a variety of appropriate activities, and abundant conversation and nurturing so your child's world is fun, interesting, safe, and loving. Concepts from art, science, drama, music, literature/language, multi-cultural, and nutrition education are an integral part of our curriculum activities. name: COTTESMORE CHRISTIAN CCC
details: Cottesmore Child Care Centers are committed to offering the highest quality of care to children in the Tacoma, Gig Harbor, and Greater Key Peninsula area. These sites include special programs for: inter-generational partnerships; partnerships with Peninsula School District and Tacoma School District to address the needs of teen parents; early intervention services; inclusive programming for special needs children; family support programs through Early Head Start; and advisory training from Bates Vocational College. These comprehensive services are evidence of our holistic approach to family support and child care.

name: CELAS CREATIVE LEARNING
details:
Cela’s Creative Learning Center believes that learning starts with families and communities, that every child and family has unique gifts and abilities. Children learn through relationships, play and active exploration, and learn best when they are healthy, safe, and free of hunger.
We support children’s learning by focusing on the Washington State Developmental guideline competency areas: About me and my family and my culture; Building relationships; Touching, seeing, hearing and moving around; Growing up healthy; Communicating; and Learning about my world. By incorporating these guidelines into our curriculum, we establish the foundation that prepares children for school and life.

name: CHILDRENS ADVEN
details:
Children’s Adventure Learning Center strives to provide a safe, healthy, and nurturing environment in a way that facilitates children to grow, discover, and learn through a variety of age and developmental appropriate practices. Our daycare center philosophy is designed to enhance the whole child in a positive atmosphere of warmth and caring. Through our awareness of child development and consistency in our care, our goal is to meet the physical, intellectual, emotional, and social needs that are unique to each child.

Children learn through their daily experiences and routines to make decisions, to carry out responsibilities, to express him/herself creatively and to discover friendships. Children are exposed to movement, art, music, reading, science, dramatic play, life skills, blocks, outdoor play, and manipulative experiences. Themes are planned around the interests of each group of new children and staff. A daily schedule helps to provide familiar flow to each day. We make every effort to achieve these goals through the partnership of child, parent, and childcare center staff.
business hours: Monday - Friday,  from 7:00 am to 6:00 pm

name: YMCA AT GRAHAM
details:
OUR MISSION
To put Christian principles into practice through programs that build a healthy spirit, mind and body for all.

name: RAINBOW CONNECTION CHILDCARE & PRESCHOOL
details:
We, at Rainbow Connection, are proud of our motto "A Loving and Learning Place" and we are committed to living and sharing it every day.  All children are lovingly accepted regardless of race, faith, ethnic group or physical limitations.  By providing appropriate activities, materials and  equipment,  we enable each and every child to achieve his/her optimum learning experience.

In our facilities, we provide a  variety of “Learning Centers”.  These learning centers help each child to grow and develop physically, academically, socially and emotionally.   Also, we believe it is greatly important for the children to learn to respect themselves, one another, their teachers, and their physical environment.  We teach this by applying rules consistently, emphasizing cooperation and sharing, and by providing discipline through teaching.  We also believe it is vitally important that children learn to independently resolve issues with each other.  With appropriate supervision, we encourage this wholeheartedly!

name: EARLY CONNECTIONS LEARNIN
details: Our primary goal is to create a setting in which children find warmth, comfort, and gentleness as well as an abundance of opportunities for movement, exploration, and self-discovery according to their individual needs, interests and abilities.

name: SOUTH PARK COMMUNITY CENTER
details:
South Park Seattle is a small neighborhood with a big voice. Nearly 4,000 people live, work, study, play, farm, and raise families in this river-hugging community wedged at the heart of the Duwamish Valley industrial corridor. Students, parents, business owners, artists, machinists, environmentalists, and civic leaders all call South Park home.

Seattle’s only riverfront neighborhood is also home to the city’s only working farm: Marra Farm, which generates tons of fresh, organic produce each year. The popular South Park Community Center offers numerous activities that are open to the public, including recreation and sports, after school and senior activities, and community events and meetings.

Environmental stewardship is present in the South Park consciousness. Despite the proximate Duwamish Waterway Superfund site, residents envision a cleaner, greener future for their community and for the Duwamish River wildlife corridor. Anyone can join the residents of South Park to participate in the annual Duwamish Alive! community cleanup events.

Neighborhood parks provide islands of open space for play, gatherings, and relaxation, including the Duwamish Waterway Park, Cesar Chavez Park, South Park Playground, and Marra-Desimone Park, plus the newly constructed River City Skate Park for skate rats.

name: CREATIVE MINDS ACADEMY LLC
details: Creative Montessori was launched in 2005 by Will and Yvette Henricus with the mission of providing Burien children with a world-class Montessori education. Creative Montessori has grown to two centers- Creative Minds Academy, for children 3-6 years old, and Creative Steps, for children 18 months-3 years old. Both programs aim to foster lifelong learners and cultivate psychological independence by encouraging your child's creativity, independence, and personal strengths. Children are motivated with creative play and exposure to math, reading, science, social studies, and the arts. Creative Montessori students and staff are actively involved in our community and frequently take their learning outside of the classroom with visits to local businesses, parks, libraries, and to interact with our local "superheroes" such as firefighters and police officers. We provide a truly world-class education with teachers who speak over 5 different languages and come from many different cultures and backgrounds. Creative Montessori has become a renowned Montessori institution with children from Federal Way to Seattle attending our two schools.

name: So Sound YMCA McLane Elementary
details:
Our lives are so busy today that families need to know where they can turn for support. At the Y we provide more than a place for kids to go. We care for kids by providing nurturing development, healthy lifestyle choices, self-reliance through positive relationships, and value-based learning.

Safe kids…Our commitment. Families place their trust in the Y to help their children and youth thrive. Our core values (caring, honesty, respect, and responsibility) are at the heart of everything we do. Because of this, we place great value on ensuring a safe environment.

name: KID CITY CHILD DEVELOPMENT
details:
After getting my degree in Early Childhood Education and working with children of drug addicts as well as being a teacher and director at several other centers, I decided in 1985 it was time to open my own center. After finding the perfect location, and with lots and lots of work, Kid City was open. 

  It was rough at first, two years of working open to close, being young and inexperienced in business, but it was all worth it and I am still loving everyday I come to work! Raising my 3 children here has been the greatest benefit and enjoying all of the other families makes me feel so privileged to have this career.

name: Messiah Lutheran School-age Program
details: The focus of Messiah Lutheran Preschool is to offer a Christian setting in which young children can grow, learn and develop physically, socially, mentally and strengthen their spiritual lives. We believe that the church life and mission includes assisting parents in the development of their children, and the school is one branch of the congregation furthering this goal.

name: BONNEY LAKE MONTESSORI
details:
Bonney Lake Montessori offers a traditional Montessori setting for children ages 30 months to five years.  Our experienced staff support a beautiful, child sized environment designed with fun and learning in mind for preschool aged children. 

Through our monthly thematic units, we spark interest and a love for learning unique to Montessori students.  Our multi-age classroom provides a wonderful  sibling partnership between the children and an individualized curriculum to meet the varying needs of each child.  Preschool and Child Care students enjoy our vibrant classroom, nature trail and outdoor playground Monday through Friday, between 6am and 6pm.

name: YMCA AT NORTH STAR ELEMENTARY
details:
OUR MISSION
To put Christian principles into practice through programs that build a healthy spirit, mind and body for all.

name: GIGGLING GUEST AGAIN CHILDCARE LLC
details: Giggling Guest Childcare started by Debi Hammel in Spokane, Washington in the year 2000. At the time there was only one location and no immediate plans to start another location. Debi continues to manage the capable teams of qualified care givers at each of our two locations. Even though there wasn't a desire to grow Giggling Guest Childcare rapidly, our reputation for quality childcare with an educational emphasis continued to bring new families. Once suitable alternate locations become available we decided to slowly take on the additional responsibility of replicating what had been working so well at our original location. We now have two childcare centers in Spokane, Washington and we're loving every minute we get to spend with our little customers!

name: KIDSAFARI
details:
KidSafari is our licensed, Bible-based childcare center.
KidSafari is a place where children can feel welcome and loved exactly as they are. Parents can feel confident that their children are being cared for in a safe and loving environment. We help children grow socially, emotionally, physically, and intellectually.

name: ENCHANTED LITTLE FOREST
details:
Let’s face it: every parent wants the best for their children. At Enchanted Little Forest Child Care Center, we embrace the idea that every child is precious. And, we agree with the Old African Proverb-it takes a village to raise a child—because we know that life is easier for both parents and children when there is a supportive and nurturing community to help out.

We offer this service to you and your children. Join our community. We offer more than just daycare service. We offer community.

So, if your children are between the ages of 4 months and 6 years, contact us to see if we may become the community to share the privilege of raising your child.
business hours: Monday through Friday, 5:30 AM to 7:00 PM.

name: ECHO After School Program at Betz Elementary
CHAMPIONS @ WESTHILL
details: Champions has a great solution for busy working families: activities that combine fun and learning, together with the safety and convenience of a high-quality program right inside your school. Champions offers a variety of group and individual activities designed to keep your child exploring and growing. From art, dramatic play, math and science to problem-solving, language, motor skills and more, we help your child continue learning and developing essential life skills – whether school is in session or not.
business hours:
Hours of Operation:

Before School: 6:45am - 9:15am

After School: 3:40am -6:30pm

After School Wednesdays: 2:05pm-6:30pm

name: Cottesmore Christian Child Care
details: Cottesmore Child Care Centers has three convenient locations that provide quality early childhood programs meeting the needs of families in the greater Tacoma and Gig Harbor Peninsula areas

name: Cornerstone Early Education Center
details: At Cornerstone Early Education Center, we are committed to lead your children as they grow up in these very formative years.  When your child enters Kindergarten, we want them to be educationally prepared for the big world that awaits them.  We also want your child to be prepared for life, and so we teach and reinforce life principles from the Bible as well as Bible Stories that will serve to guide and shape them as they get grow up.  We love parents.  Our desire is to be a resource for you in any way that we can.  Raising children is not easy, and we want to help you by giving you opportunities to grow in your parenting.  We live Jesus.  As people to follow Jesus, we desire that every interaction with you and your children be guided and influenced by our faith in Christ.  We lead children like Jesus would.  We love parents like Jesus would.  It's who we strive to be and what we strive to do.  We are Cornerstone Early Education Center.

name: Guardian Angel Academy Child Care Center 4
details: Guardian Angel Academy enhances the greater Spokane community by providing childcare with a curriculum in order to support our children’s physical, emotional, and academic growth as they prepare for kindergarten and beyond.

name: Community Child Care Center St James
details: Welcome to Community Child Care Center, a non-profit agency serving local children and families since 1970! Today, through our Early Head Start, Head Start, ECEAP, and Child Care programs we provide comprehensive preschool, childcare, and family support services to over 300 children throughout Whitman County, Washington. We are proud to be accredited by the National Association for the Education of Young Children (NAEYC) – the nation’s leading organization of early childhood professionals.  Less than 10 percent of all programs nationwide have reached this mark of quality and are recognized for their continued commitment towards reaching the highest professional early childhood standards.

name: Goddard School Bellevue
details: The Goddard School uses the most current, academically endorsed methods to ensure that children have fun while learning the skills they need for long-term success in school and in life. Our talented teachers also collaborate with parents to nurture children into respectful, confident and joyful learners.

name: Community Child Care Center Greyhound Way
details: Welcome to Community Child Care Center, a non-profit agency serving local children and families since 1970! Today, through our Early Head Start, Head Start, ECEAP, and Child Care programs we provide comprehensive preschool, childcare, and family support services to over 300 children throughout Whitman County, Washington. We are proud to be accredited by the National Association for the Education of Young Children (NAEYC) – the nation’s leading organization of early childhood professionals.  Less than 10 percent of all programs nationwide have reached this mark of quality and are recognized for their continued commitment towards reaching the highest professional early childhood standards.

name: Genesee Early Learning Center
details:
Surround your child with a supportive learning environment that prepares him or her for school. 

Located in the heart of the vibrant and growing community of Rainier Valley, the Genesee Early Learning Center provides high-quality, full-time preschool and Head Start for children ages 2.5 to 5 years old. 

Head Start gets your child ready for the first day of kindergarten while building social, emotional and learning skills. It also offers your families education, health, nutrition and social resources and tools. 

Our program is available for families who qualify and acc

name: Gateway Learning Center
details:
Gateway Learning Center is in its 33rd year of providing quality early care and school readiness programs for children and their families all over Kitsap County. As a non-profit child-care center, we are licensed through the Department of Early Learning, County Health Department, and State and Local Fire Departments. We are a ministry of Gateway Fellowship in Poulsbo and are located on its campus.

We provide a balance of active and quiet activities, which are of a rich and diverse range. This offers open-ended activities where children can make choices based on their own development and interests.

name: Community Child Care Center Colfax
details: Welcome to Community Child Care Center, a non-profit agency serving local children and families since 1970! Today, through our Early Head Start, Head Start, ECEAP, and Child Care programs we provide comprehensive preschool, childcare, and family support services to over 300 children throughout Whitman County, Washington. We are proud to be accredited by the National Association for the Education of Young Children (NAEYC) – the nation’s leading organization of early childhood professionals.  Less than 10 percent of all programs nationwide have reached this mark of quality and are recognized for their continued commitment towards reaching the highest professional early childhood standards.

name: Gabriels Art Kids
details:
We provide a supportive, unhurried, and non-judgmental environment, with focus on the arts; visual, music, dance and theater and self-expression. We are a Multiple Intelligence School that puts a strong focus on a well rounded education. Art is incorporated into their daily lesson plans, and we often try to create interdisciplinary connections between the students' art lessons and their other classes.

A process-oriented approach, not ‘product’, but an opportunity to explore a 
medium with the satisfaction of involvement. We hope children will begin to comfortably use different media to articulate themselves, their emotions and ideas. We provide a variety of arts materials for the students free use and celebrate creativity!

name: Champions at Covington Elementary
details: Champions has a great solution for busy working families: activities that combine fun and learning, together with the safety and convenience of a high-quality program right inside your school. Champions offers a variety of group and individual activities designed to keep your child exploring and growing. From art, dramatic play, math and science to problem-solving, language, motor skills and more, we help your child continue learning and developing essential life skills – whether school is in session or not.
business hours:
Before School: 6:30am - start of school
After School: End of school - 6:30pm*

name: Arcadia Learning Center Inc Gig Harbor
details:
Arcadia was established in 1975. It originally opened in a store front on South 12th and Proctor where it was purchased by Carmela Micheli. In 1978 we moved to a home on North 12th and Monroe. In 1990 we moved to our present location at 6312 North 30th Street.
In 2012 We built and added a new location in Gig Harbor, Wa. at 13302 Crescent Valley Dr NW.

At Arcadia we promote a strong peace & environmental curriculum and appreciate the importance of non-violent communication in our classroom as well as the world.

We realize the importance of the children learning & living outdoors. We have created a large garden that the children till, weed, plant, water, harvest and eat from.

Each year the children participate in raising money to donate to a global &/or local cause.
business hours:
Class times 9:00-12:00, extended day class 1:00-3:00

Child care available 7:00am-6:00pm

name: A Childs Place Early Learning Center
details: Our purpose at A Child's Place Early Learning Center, is to empower children to become confident, respectful, lifelong learners. Our mission is to help children see the world as an invitation to learn, grow, to live fully, and to see the world full of possibilities that are within their reach. Our commitment is to provide a loving, nurturing and safe place for children to begin their journey.

name: ABC Early Learning Academy
details:
Our Philosophy
Our program is built around the concept that children are born ready to learn. As caregivers, we strive to create a quality learning environment that is safe, stimulating and encouraging. We believe in learning through sensory and discovery experiences that are both challenging and enjoyable. We provide an environment that encourages each child to develop physically, intellectually, emotionally and socially. This is accomplished in a relaxed play and learning environment that balances structured and unstructured time, planned and emergent curriculum. We provide developmentally appropriate activities based upon child growth and development theories, recent research in child development, and the time-tested culture of childhood. We recognize that as we all learn and grow our thinking must be flexible and open to review, modification and change. We view parents as partners and we strive to support the family through involvement and educational opportunities at ABC Early Learning Academy.

name: Concordia Lutheran School Association of Greater Tacoma
CITY KIDS COUNTRY CABIN & PRESCHOOL
details:
City Kids provides quality childcare in a positive and friendly environment. Our programs are designed to meet the social, emotional, physical and intellectual need of children. Children are encouraged to make decisions to their own and learn because they are interested.

Our programs introduce ideas and concepts through monthly themes. Activities including Art, Calendar, Sign language, Spanish, Songs, Finger plays and Story telling are developed that are age appropriate.

The desired end result is to provide challenges that make children feel successful and to
build self esteem. City Kids has a loving, professional and educated staff that provides the highest quality of childcare. We believe that early learning is relationship based.

name: Ages In Stages Pre-K School Age
details:
At Ages in Stages Childcare we provide a home away from home.  We teach and care for your child as if they were family.  Our low turn over rate both with children and staff can ensure that your child can grow and develop in a familiar environment.

We do not discriminate against anyone based on race, color, gender, national origin or sexual orientation. Everyone is welcome at Ages in Stages Childcare.

We teach everything to prepare a child for school and life. Everyday we teach colors, numbers, shapes, letters, how to write their name, respect, manners, and how to be an independent person.

Once you sign your child up at Ages in Stages,  we have an open door policy and we welcome and encourage parents to come to us with any questions about the development of your child.   We work together to make your child be the best they can be.

name: Building Memories Early Learning Center
details: Building Memories Early Learning Center is a new child care center catering to children ages 12 months to 12 years. We are located in the Milton/ Federal Way, WA area.  We are family owned and operated facility with over 15 years of child care experience. Our employees are past daycare children as well. We want you and your children to feel safe, welcome, have fun and learn while at daycare.

name: Childrens Learning Center of Ephrata LLC
Oakbrook Children's Center LLC
details: Oakbrook Children's Center is in business for one thing and one thing only! Providing the best care possible to the children of our community. Safe, clean, positive, and educational child care are just some of the core values O.C.C. is built on. Put simply, the children come first.

name: Northgate Early Learning Center
details:
NELC Seattle serves children between the ages of 1 month to 5 years of age. It is a community service provided by International Full Gospel Fellowship Church and is licensed by the State of Washington.
​It is the mission of NELC Seattle to help families by giving children quality education, instilling Christian values and providing a safe, encouraging, and fun environment in which to grow.
We operate both our instruction and activities in a manner consistent with Christian values. We offer loving and accepting atmosphere. We expect at all times to maintain open communication with both students and parents as we realize that our contribution is not complete in itself. We view our service to be complimentary to that of the families, schools, and community.
﻿The curriculum and program used at NELC Seattle will include stories from the Bible, biblical concepts and values, and songs with religious content. We encourage kindness, thankfulness, and helpfulness, sharing and good moral standards according to the Bible. We also pray before the children eat and at other appropriate times.

name: Lil Kids N Me Children's Center
Ladders of Love Learning Center & Preschool
The Country Playhouse Club
details:
At The Country Playhouse Learning Center, we want each child to be the very best he/she can be.  We strive to create a caring, loving, and nurturing environment, one that promotes both individual learning as well as group learning.  Children learn in so many different ways, and we feel that it is necessary for them to have the proper tools that will lead to new experiences, and help to enhance their abilities and strengths even further.  Learning requires active thinking, and hands on activities to let them learn first hand about the world around them.  A child that is absorbed in the positive components of life has little time to focus on the negatives.

We want our children to grow up with the knowledge that they can make a positive difference in their life, as well as in the lives of others around them.  It is our goal as caregivers and educators to help each child achieve his/her own level of excellence.  To do this, we need to work as a team.  This means that our center will work with you, the parents, in projecting the most positive influence possible.

We all want the best for our children; they are our future, and we must never
lose sight of that fact.  As a community of caregivers and parents, we need to
work together to make that future as bright as it possibly can be;
for each and every child.

name: Lacey Learning Center South
details:
Lacey Learning Center will strive to provide childcare of the highest quality, stressing a safe, secure environment; a nurturing, professional team of staff; and the finest educational experiences. We are committed to providing a program that balances each child’s intellectual, physical, social, creative and emotional needs. We believe that early learning is relationship-based. Our fundamental goal is to establish trusting relationships among children, teachers, and parents. Therefore we will strive to establish relationships with our students and to model appropriate behaviors and social skills.

All children develop at a different pace and possess a wide range of strengths and weaknesses. It is our belief that children learn best through hands-on, stimulating, engaging activities. We are committed to providing a fun, educational atmosphere where children are challenged each day. Carefully constructed early education experiences promote exploration, critical thinking, cooperative play and the development of mutual respect.

If you are interested in touring the center call, email or stop in anytime during normal business hours. We provide the best in quality childcare and daycare.

name: BILLIES BUSY KIDS CHILD CARE AND PRESCHOOL
details:
At Billie’s Busy Kids Child Care and Preschool our commitment to each child is to create a fun and safe learning environment, that allows your child to nurture and explore at their own unique level of development.

We believe that every child at their own pace. Our goal is to assist your you and your child in fostering a deeper understanding of your child and allowing your child to develop to your child's fullest potential in all aspects of development, growth, and assist you child in meet their own unique needs.

We do this through observation of your child, planning the environment, then executing play, and assisting your child in exploring the environment to develop a deeper understanding.

We believe that children are constantly learning through play and the play is the work your child is doing...so if all you see is the "play" then your child is working very hard and we are all doing an excellent job.

name: ST. BRENDAN PRESCHOOL
details:
We prepare children to be successful in high school and compassionate active Catholics. Our alum families send their children to St. Brendan; their grandparents support the school with time and treasure; and our graduates are making the world a better place!

    Catholic faith and character development
    Excellent academics
    Strong family and student friendships
    Safe and secure building 
    Stable Catholic school for 49 years!
    Fully accredited school 
    Preschool (3s) and Pre-kindergarten (4s) classes
    Full and half-day Kindergarten class
    Weekly music, art, PE, and technology classes
    Science lab and daily science for grades 5-8
    Before and after school child care; hot lunch program

name: Best Beginnings Child Care and Preschool
details:
Serving the Yakima Valley, Union Gap, and the Lower Valley including Wapato, Toppenish and Sunnyside. We pride ourselves on having qualified, passionate care providers that have over 18 years experience and truly take an interest in watching your child grow and learn.

We accept children from the age of 4 weeks up to 12 and offer before and after school programs. Our facilities have two Preschool rooms, and is a secured building.

name: Bella Mente Early Learning Vita Center
Seed Of Life Center LLC At Martin Luther King Jr. School
details:
Seed of Life provides an academically enriched curriculum and environment through play that supports and creates a multi-cultural, multi-lingual community. We strive to provide a safe learning environment and atmosphere that is committed to diversity, social responsibility, and empowering competent life long learners.

We are a inclusive and supportive environment where each child’s gifts, talents, and cultures are nurtured to help enhance their development in: language, cognitive, physical, creative, independence, positive self-esteem, social-emotional growth and development, and conflict resolution. In addition, to preparing children to be Kindergarten ready and literacy enriched, we strive to create a sense of community through a culturally competent environment, which encourages educators and parents to have a strong collaborative partnership.

name: ABC LEARNING CENTER
details: ABC Learning Center is based on mentally stimulating and active learning: developmentally appropriate activities that facilitate and enhance and provide social, emotional cognitive and large and small muscle motor development, by age and individual readiness in an environment that provides nurturing support and intellectual stimulation with love. The primary emphasis is on social development and learning through active play how to play with our friends. ABC Learning Center supports parenting by enabling children to grow and learn in a safe, stimulating, loving environment.

name: VISION DREAM PRESCHOOL
details:
Vision Dream Preschool program encourages compassion and love in a Christian environment that enables children to learn and grow at their own pace.
Our teachers and staff are dedicated to providing and maintaining a safe and healthy atmosphere filled with nurture and love for each child. We wish to expose our students to learning new concepts as well as install a love of learning through play and exploration. Through guidance and direction, we would love to see our children build a personal relationship with God and practice individual social responsibilities. Children dream and have great vision of becoming important people in this world and we hope to spark and help that dream grow.

name: Scribbles and Giggles Learning Center
details: Scribbles And Giggles in Tumwater, WA offers fun and exciting learning activities for children 6 weeks to 12 years of age. Our director Carrie Beirman has been in the child care industry for over 16 years and is licensed in Tumwater for 7 years. We are committed to offering your child every opportunity to grow and develop emotionally, socially, morally, physically, and intellectually. We believe that children learn through hands-on activities, that is why we have a teacher-based learning curriculum for every group. We have a "Parents' Night" once every month to showcase what the children have learned.

name: The Learning Company, Inc.
details:
Welcome to The Learning Company Inc!
Whether you are a mom, dad, grandparent or guardian, you want your child to have a loving, caring, wholesome environment in which to play and learn! We understand the need to provide quality child care at a reasonable price and are excited to offer this service to Port Townsend and the surrounding communities! We offer options for full-time or part-time child care and before and after school care as well as school closing and snow days where space is avaliable!

name: Island of Angels Child Care Center
KIDS COUNTRY CANYON PARK
details:
As a full-service, licensed, and family owned business, Kid’s Country was established with the goal to promote a safe and nurturing learning environment that stimulates your child’s growth. Our curriculum, activities, and room arrangements are all tailored to be age appropriate. Additionally, our curriculum follows both weekly and monthly themes.

A typical day at Kid’s Country will include activities like reading, looking at books, writing, drawing, dancing, singing, cutting, pasting, painting, assembling art projects, experimenting, exploring, and enjoying the environment. One of our primary areas of focus is meeting each child’s individual needs. We encourage children to progress at their own pace and they are placed in the classroom that will help them the best. This encourages self-confidence and healthy growth which results in a strong, positive self-image.

In fact, the Kid’s Country motto is to allow children to love, laugh, learn, and grow. By keeping the environment fun and positive, we create a safe haven—a home away from home—for your children. All of our classrooms are warm, cozy, and filled with personal touches that allow your kids to feel comfortable. It is our responsibility to work in partnership with your family and help enhance and support, not replace, the relationship between parents and children.

One of the ways we do this is by placing a high priority on ongoing training for our managers and staff. Every month each of our teachers is trained on a different topic relating to child care and the issues we face in providing for your children. This allows us to better meet the needs of the kids we care for, as well as to provide a better, cleaner, happier, and safer environment.

At Kid’s Country, we take the safety of your children very seriously. All of our facilities are equipped with pass card protected entrances. We are also alerted to those arriving and exiting through the main entrance. In order to gain admittance, an entry reader card must be used, though we do have a doorbell available to notify our staff of any guests or parents who need access.

We hope you can see how important caring for your children is to all of us at Kid’s Country. We pride ourselves on being a premier and trustworthy child care provider for the Seattle area. Watching your kids grow and learn gives us joy and fulfillment. If you like what you see, we invite you to learn more by touring one of our facilities. Hopefully you’ll then apply for admission, which is granted without discrimination or regard to race, color, national or ethnic origin, sex, or religion.

name: Hillside Child Dvelopment Center
details:
Membership of the Hillside Development Council (HDC) consists of property owners, business owners, workers, and residents of the area on the "side of the hill" in Tacoma.

HDC's primary areas of emphasis are public safety and working to provide a more vibrant area to work, live and invest.

Come and join us at one of our meetings. We are always looking for new ideas, concerns, and most of all individuals wanting to help this area grow. Download our membership flyer for more information.

name: Eatonville Early Learning Center Inc
details: My door is always open and I encourage you to come by anytime and take a tour of the center. It is a pretty relaxed and comfortable atmosphere where the children can learn and grow.

name: PRIME TIME PRESCHOOL - I
details:
Prime Time Children Learning Center offers a contemporary, Montessori inspired program enriched with art, language (Spanish), creative play and music& movement activities.

At Prime Time your children will expose topics through traditional as well as Montessori materials while incorporating teaching methods based on Multiple Intelligences and Montessori principles. Daily curriculum adjusted to each child’s intellectual and developmental levels and lessons are presented with help of visual/sensorial two and three dimensional materials which are usually self- correcting that allow children to enhance their problem solving skills. Our lessons and environment are designed to address different learning styles.

name: ADVENTURE KIDS PLAYCARE
details:
Our mission is to provide a safe and fun environment for kids while giving parents the ability to take a little time for themselves without feeling guilty!

So many things to see and do!

name: YMCA BELLEVUE FAMILY @ CHILD DEVELOPMENT CENTER - PRESCHOOL
MT SI MONTESSORI LLC
details: Mt Si Montessori recently celebrated its 23rd year of educating children in the Snoqualmie Valley. Mt Si Montessori offers a unique environment blending the best of the Montessori philosophy in a warm relaxed setting. The 2 classroom building makes for an intimate family setting, and our extra large playground has plenty of room for the children to run and play. We are located inside the North Bend city limits on nearly an acre of property. Mt Si Montessori is a Washington State Licensed Childcare Center. Our teachers are certified through Nationally Accredited Teacher Training Programs. Mt Si Montessori offers mixed age classrooms for children between the ages of 2 1/2 and 6 years of age. Children are able to learn at their independent level, in a classroom that promotes social, emotional and intellectual growth. Students explore at their own pace using hands on materials designed specifically for them.

name: PRECIOUS BLESSINGS INFANT AND TODDLER DAY PROGRAM
CHSW Highline Early Learning Center
details:
Located on the Highline Community College campus, Children’s Home Society of Washington’s Early Learning Center offers preschool, Early Head Start, Head Start and Early Childhood Education and Assistance Program (ECEAP) programs. Children receive high-quality early learning in the areas of social and emotional development, cognitive and language skills, as well as creative arts, music, and exposure to a variety of cultures and languages. Trained professionals work individually and in group settings with your child to help them meet their developmental milestones and prepare them for success in school, and life.

The parent is recognized as the child's primary teacher, so we strive to keep parents involved in their child's development while encouraging parent/child interactions. On-site parent discussion rooms are available where educators and parents meet regularly to discuss the progress and needs of the child.   

The center serves the surrounding community and is also available for the children of students, staff, and faculty at Highline Community College, and is accredited by the National Association for the Education of Young Children.

name: Learning Land CCC Kent Campus
details:
Our Philosophy
Learning Land’s philosophy is to promote a positive sense of self in each child by developing interpersonal relationships combined with a loving and nurturing environment.  Our educator’s provide learning experiences that promote independence, social-emotional, physical, language, and cognitive skills.  Our curriculum is based on the whole child and emerges out of each child’s interests and personal needs.  We believe this approach to curriculum development engages the child in the learning experience and incorporates individual backgrounds and cultures.  Research shows that young children learn primarily through play.  During play children feel the freedom to explore new ideas and practice early learning skills.  As teachers plan activities and provide opportunities for children to work and play together; children learn valuable social skills and self-empowerment. These experiences positively affect their growth and learning throughout the rest of their lives.

We believe that families are the most important part of a child’s foundation. Effective communication between parents and teachers builds a level of trust, comfort, and enables us to make sure every child can be successful by reaching their full potential.  At Learning Land we engage our families in their child’s learning experience with parent-teacher conferences for preschool children and daily notes for toddlers and infants. We also have quarterly parent events that offer free childcare, dinner, and guest speakers as well as a yearly family Barbeque.  We are proud to offer these community based events at no additional charge.

name: CHILDRENS LIFE II
details:
Children's Life Child Care and Learning Center began in 1985 with one location, serving the North Tacoma area. We have since added two more locations, to broaden our service area to South Tacoma and the evolving Hilltop Neighborhood. Director, Peggy Burrows, sees Children's Life Child Care as a fulfillment of her life's mission, to provide quality Christian childcare and have a positive impact on the early development of children throughout Tacoma.

All of those on staff have one thing in common – the well being of your child. We are confident that you will find our staff to be loving, concerned and understanding, with the goal of providing your child with a positive, nurturing and happy daytime environment. All of our staff members have received training in Early Childhood Development and many have their degrees in Early Childhood Education.

name: Kids Country/Normandy Park
details: We are a full service, licensed childcare provider that strives to uphold our motto: LOVE, LAUGH, LEARN, AND GROW.

name: GO ZONE AFTER SCHOOL CARE PROGRAM

details:
Gateway Christian Schools is a K-12 multi-campus, multi-program school. Our Crosspoint campus is located in Bremerton, Washington.  Crosspoint is home to students kindergarten through grade 12, and hosts the international student program.  One of the two Arrowsmith program locations is also on this campus and provides services for those in 2nd through 12th grades.  Gateway Elementary at the Poulsbo campus, formerly called Christ the King Academy, was founded over 40 years ago. North Kitsap Preschool, located adjacent to our Gateway Elementary campus, has been an important part of the educational system for years.  Finally, The Learning Center is a before-and-after school program on the Poulsbo campus, and has been serving families for 30 years. 

We mentioned Arrowsmith earlier, but did you know we have a whole independent campus exclusively for our Arrowsmith program? This second campus is located on Bainbridge Island and provides services up through adult learners.

name: Beginnings 2 Child Care Center At Queen Anne
details:
We at Beginnings believe strongly in the need to foster individual growth and self-esteem for every child.

The particular needs of each child and each family are our priority. We strive to maintain an atmosphere of emotional trust and a respect of open communication. At the same time, we provide a physical environment in which cognitive, physical and social development are all richly interwoven. This is made possible by a staff of teachers that comprise our greatest asset.

We are committed to the idea of parental involvement and have made available a range of possibilities for such involvement. Parents are encouraged to voice their ideas and concerns and to participate directly in the life and health of our schools. Beginnings Schools are cooperative early learning programs.

details: Our goal and mission is to provide an academy where children (ages 4 weeks - 6 years) can be nurtured and cared for with equal opportunities to learn, play, and grow ~ in a loving and academic setting.

name: Eyas Global Montessori School
details:
Eyas Global Montessori School offers Montessori preschool and kindergarten programs for children 30 months through 6 years old and is located in the Lake Hills Neighborhood of Bellevue, Washington. Take a photo tour of our Montessori preschool classrooms.

The child is the center of the Montessori pedagogical approach to education. Through the hands-on work with the specifically designed materials the child gains real life experiences and builds independence. The Montessori preschool teacher as a keen observer, guides the child at the right moment to allow the child to develop to their fullest potential.

In our preschool and kindergarten environment, we will help the child fulfill his inner need for knowledge. This in turn helps the child self-construct his character and intellect while integrating his mind, body and spirit. Maria Montessori discovered through her studies that “Please help me to do it myself” is the inner voice of the child. We are guiding the children to build self-discipline, confidence and independence within themselves, both towards academic study and towards life, laying a solid foundation for their successful future.

name: Lewis County Adventist School
details: Lewis County Adventist School opened its doors in 1922, and was located in downtown Centralia, Washington. In 1952, the area Seventh-day Adventist churches came together to build LCAS at its current location on Scheuber Road. Students and faculty moved into the new school in 1953, and grades 9 and 10 were added to the curriculum. The constituency of the school is currently made up of the Centralia, Chehalis , and Winlock Seventh-day Adventist Churches. Formerly Oakville (dissolved), Onlalaska, and Morton ('74/'75) SDA Churches were part of the contituency.

We offer a child-centered environment rather than teacher centered. Our center's services are made available to all person's otherwise eligible without regard to race, color, religion, national origin or ancestry. We respect the dignity of each family and it's culture, customs, and beliefs.

Our program focuses on the whole child; providing opportunities for growth in cognitive, social, emotional, and physical development. It is the goal of our program to provide a safe nurturing environment where children can learn, grow, be themselves, relax, share time with friends, and most importantly have fun! We partner with classroom teachers and principals to provide valuable academic support for our students that enhances their learning day.

details:
LASER Childcare consists of three school age child care programs (LASER at Laurelhurst, LASER at Sand Point, and LASER at Bryant), a Pre-K Readiness Program, enrichment classes (offered at Laurelhurst and Sand Point), Day Camp (offered during school in-service days and school breaks), and Summer Camp! All these programs are located in Seattle's NE community. We provide child care in a safe, nurturing, and exciting environment for 76 children at our Laurelhurst campus, 81 children at our Sand Point campus, and 113 at our Bryant Campus, all accommodating children ages 5-12. Please see our tuition schedule for rates and fees.

LASER's focus is your child's social and emotional growth and we offer child care programs focused on that objective.

The Laurelhurst campus childcare program is located in the Laurelhurst neighborhood at Laurelhurst Elementary in Seattle, WA. The Sand Point campus childcare program is located in the Sand Point Neighborhood at Sand Point Elementary School in Seattle, WA. The Bryant campus childcare program is located in the Bryant neighborhood at Bryant Elementary in Seattle, WA. In all three programs, we offer children many choices in their daily routine and provide enriching activities in the mornings and afternoons. Close by neighborhoods include Wedgewood, View Ridge, Ravenna, and Montlake.

Seedlings also offers programs and education for parents to help them understand the development of their children thereby enriching the whole family’s life together. That’s Seedlings.

name: Sugas Place Childcare and Enrichment Center
details: At Suga's Place our philosophy is to support children to develop to their maximun potential in their social, emotional, moral, cognitive, and physical growth. We are committed to enhancing childrens self esteem through daily interactions, developmentally appropriate experiences and relationships based on mutual trust and respect. We strive to develop positive, supportive relationships with families based on open communication and sharing of knowledge and skills. We consider each family unique in its structure, culture and values, and respect the special relationship between children and their families, incorporating this perspective in all out interactions with children.

name: The Eastside Montessori School
details:
The Eastside Montessori School is a small AMI associated school in Bellevue, Washington. We are committed to providing an educational environment within which children can experience the joy and freedom that come with independence, confidence, and inner discipline.

We are a community that values respect and compassion.  We support the natural development of children and honor their important work of self-discovery.

We currently have two classrooms which are carefully and lovingly prepared to meet the developmental needs of the children in the class. The primary classroom supports children 2 ½ years old to 6 years old and the elementary classroom children aged 6-9 years old.

The beauty of Montessori education is its ability to work with the child, taking into account how children actually learn, allowing the child to fully prepare for their journey into society, and at the same time freeing him to fulfill his potential as an active contributing member of society. A love of life and learning follows naturally.

We are an AMI/USA Associated School, a status that recognizes our commitment to the highest standards of Montessori education.

name: TIME FOR TOTS CHILD CARE CENTER
UW Childrens Center At Laurel Village
details:
The University of Washington Children's Center at Laurel Village was originally founded as a parent co-op in 1976. The program offers a traditional early care and education program and includes one infant room, one toddler room and two preschool classrooms. The center is located U.W. Family Housing and is licensed for 70 children. The on-site Program Director is Jodi Eschenburg.

We believe that children grow and learn best in a warm, nurturing, well-organized environment. Our teachers are sensitive and respectful to each child's individuality and encourage each child to develop a joyful confidence with which to explore our constantly changing world. We welcome a multicultural community of families and are committed to supporting this diversity in all areas of our early childhood program.

A relationship of mutual respect and support between parents and teachers promotes a positive environment for children.

name: Wee Are The World Child Development Program
details: Mount Baker Preschool is based on the view that we need to address body, soul, mind, and spirit in all of our teachings. The core of Waldorf education is that human beings bear within themselves capacities for developing freedom of thought, balance in feeling, and conscious purpose in action that will enable them to realize meaning in their lives. We provide preschoolers with a warm, beautiful, loving, home-like environment, which is protective and secure, where the day unfolds in a predictable, regular way. This holistic educational experience addresses their intellectual capacities, stimulates their innate curiosity, and engages them through direct hands-on experience. The children are given a range of activities and the structure they need to prepare for the next phase of school life.

name: Wee Are The World Right Start
WEE CARE DAY CARE ST. JOHNS
details: We believe children learn best by interacting and exploring the world around them. Through their daily experiences in our care, we help them understand better the world in which they live.  By our words, actions, and the activities we plan, we facilitate a desire and excitement for learning and growth.  We nurture, encourage, and build the self-esteem of each child as they begin to develop the potential that each one has unique to him or her. It is our goal that each child will develop a positive self-image and a strong foundation of skills for future development and growth.

name: WHATCOM FAMILY YMCA AT CORDATA ELEMENTARY SCHOOL
YMCA Lake Spokane Childrens Center
details:
At the Y we believe every child can achieve their full potential. We believe every child should be in a safe, nurturing environment. We believe parents deserve peace of mind. At the Y, we strengthen community through youth development because we believe that a community is stronger when all children have the opportunity to discover who they are and what they can achieve.

When you enroll in the School Age Program you do so knowing that the Y impacts youth by nurturing them to their full potential through skill development, positive relationships, and inspiring opportunities to explore and discover.

Come join us for engaging activities in a safe place right in your school! Children build lasting friendships, interact with positive role models and have choices of activities such as arts & crafts, physical activity, clubs, and homework time.

Full time and part time options available to meet the needs of your family. Registration packets and pricing can be found below. You can also pick one up at your school office or at any YMCA location. Your hand-written signature is required on the registration packet, therefore online registration is not available. We accept state assistance and the YMCA also has financial assistance available to those who qualify.

name: Fun To Learn Child Care LLC
Cedar Crest Academy - Bellewood Campus
details: Cedar Crest Academy offers an academically enriching program for children ages thirty six months through fourth grade. Our unique program prepares children to excel academically by providing an environment where learning is tangible, engaging, and exciting. Our staff is comprised of nurturing, experienced teachers who are trained in individualizing the curriculum to provide the best possible learning outcomes for our students. Because we know learning does not end when the school doors close, our teachers strive to build strong relationships with parents in order to form a seamless transition from the home to the classroom. We are committed to creating a stimulating, safe, and creative environment to ensure the children in our program develop to their fullest potential.

The primary emphasis is on social development and learning through active play how to play with our friends. ABC Learning Center supports parenting by enabling children to grow and learn in a safe, stimulating, loving environment.

name: A Child's Journey School LLC
details: Here at A Child’s Journey School we believe in building and maintaining a strong sense of community. We encourage the active participation of families and want to make sure they are comfortable within community and our classrooms. Because of this, we ask that families schedule a visit before beginning the application process to see our classrooms and meet our teachers. At Easter Seals Growing Years Child Development Center we provide high quality care and education for children ages 6 weeks to 5 years old.  We are an inclusive center that supports the needs of children of all abilities through a developmentally appropriate curriculum that focuses on the needs of the individual child. We use Creative Curriculum approach that encourages children to learn through play, promotes strong social skills, and develops a foundation for a lifelong love of learning.

Growing Years is a small center with a big community of devoted teachers and involved families. We would love to have your family join ours, so please call to schedule a tour and discover what Easter Seals Growing Years Child Development Center is all about. Conveniently located at the Federal Center South Building serving Downtown, South and West Seattle. GSA affiliated. DSHS enrollment accepted. Federal employees receive 10% discount and priority enrollment at Growing Years, but enrollment is open to the community. NAEYC accredited. Offers Musically Minded and Creative Curriculum

From art, dramatic play, math and science to problem-solving, language, motor skills and more, we help your child continue learning and developing essential life skills – whether school is in session or not.

name: Happy Day Learning Center
details:
Happy Day Learning Center began as a ministry of Centralia Community Church of God in 1979. Our Learning Center is passionate about providing your children with the tools they ned to be successful in all aspects of their lives. We are designed to assist families who desire an educational experience with age-appropriate activities and social interaction with a Christian foundation. We provide a safe, secure and friendly environment for children ages 2 1/2-12 years of age. We cultivate the cognitive and social development of each child through fun learning programs that promote creativity and curiosity, language and vocabulary skills, critical thinking, and positive social interactions.

 All staff of Happy Day Learning Center undergo an extensive interview process, including thorough state required fingerprint and background checks before being hired. Every person on staff is dedicated to providing the highest quality of education for each child and supporting the families participating in Happy Day Learning Center with strategic approaches to the student's unique learning styles. Lead teachers have degrees in Early Childhood Education or Elementary Education. Assistant Teachers have 20 hours STARS training. All teachers are required to maintain current CPR and First Aid certification, as well as HIV training and Food Handler's permits through the State of WA. Lead teachers and assistants also attend ongoing state-required training throughout the year.

name: International Montessori Academy
details:
International Montessori Academy is an innovative multi-lingual Montessori school offering Montessori education in language immersion settings for children ages 13 month through 6 years. We currently offer Chinese, English, Japanese and Spanish.

IMA was founded in 2011 by a mom and a Montessori educator with the goal to educate children using a Montessori language immersion model. In less than 3 years, IMA expanded into two locations offering four different languages.

We’d like to be an integral part of your family life and help your child reach their highest potential while acquiring a 2nd or 3rd language. We are pleased you want to learn more about IMA and consider it a privilege to assist you in this important decision.

We invite you to be thorough in your school search. Come tour IMA. Ask questions. Spend time observing classrooms. You’ll not only hear students and teachers conversing in multiple languages and see the Montessori methodology in action; you’ll also feel the warmth that exists in our classrooms. This process will help you determine if IMA is a good choice for your child and your family.

name: Just Like Home Daycare Center of Lakewood
Kids Company At Lincoln
details:
Kids Co. launched in the spring of 1989 with the simple belief that every child needs a safe place to be while their parents are at work. Over time, this foundational idea grew to become a multi-site organization known for its quality childcare and for its leadership in advancing best practices in all aspects of its operation.

At present, Kids Co. offers before school and after school care, preschool programming, and summer day-camp for children ages 3 to 12, and has ten centers conveniently located on the grounds of Seattle and Greater Seattle area public schools.

The organization reflects the spirit and vision of its founders, Susan R. Brown and Elaine Matthes, in its aim to create engaging communities for kids that families can trust. The importance of trust is at the heart of all that we do. It shapes who we recruit and hire, how we interact with kids and families, and how we support the communities and schools where we are located. It even shapes how we treat one another.

Fundamentally, childcare is a profession of cultivating healthy, life-engaging relationships. We believe that in helping children discover their gifts, explore the world and make life-long friends, we help families in our community thrive for generations to come. Kids Co. frontline childcare professionals design curriculum that supports this ultimate aim, programming that is creative, fun and tailored to the unique needs of the kids and families they serve.

No family is ever turned away due to inability to pay, and Kids Co. strives to provide uninterrupted care for each child enrolled, because relationship disruptions can be devastating for kids—as well as for parents. Contributions to Kids Co. help underwrite the tuition assistance we provide to families experiencing financial distress.

We invite you to watch the video on this page and discover Kids Co. through the eyes of our kids.

Here at Tree Hill Learning Center we are trying to set ourselves apart from the typical large corporate owned childcare centers. We are a privately owned and independently operated early childhood education center. Since we are a smaller school, we are able to give more personal attention to the families and children we serve. We are a community within the walls of our delightful school and encourage parental involvement in many ways. We have created a distinctive atmosphere and a curriculum that is without comparison in the East Vancouver area. Your child's care and education is
of the utmost importance to us.

Our ultimate goal is to enable each child to have fun, explore and have the freedom to express their individuality, while providing a solid foundation for their future academic successes. We are a pre-school community that values kindness and respect for each other, our school, the environment and the world around us.

From our little Seedlings to our big Redwoods, we offer your child a nurturing, supportive and stimulating environment in which they can grow and blossom into self confident, self reliant and positive young people!
